B040C001V001	40	1	1	This is a record of the birth of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham fathered Isaac, Isaac fathered Jacob, and Jacob fathered Judah and his brothers.
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah fathered Perez and Zerah by Tamar, Perez fathered Hezron, Hezron fathered Aram,
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Aram fathered Aminidab, Aminidab fathered Nahshon, and Nahshon fathered Salmon.
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon fathered Boaz by Rahab, Boaz fathered Obed by Ruth, Obed fathered Jesse,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	and Jesse fathered King David.David fathered Solomon by the wife of Uriah,
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon fathered Rehoboam, Rehoboam fathered Abijah, Abijah fathered Asaph,
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asaph fathered Jehoshaphat, Jehoshaphat fathered Joram, Joram fathered Uzziah,
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah fathered Jotham, Jotham fathered Ahaz, Ahaz fathered Hezekiah,
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah fathered Manasseh, Manasseh fathered Amos, and Amos fathered Josiah.
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah fathered Jechoniah and his brothers at the time of the deportation to Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	After the deportation to Babylon, Jechoniah fathered Salathiel, Salathiel fathered Zerubbabel,
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel fathered Abiud, Abiud fathered Eliakim, Eliakim fathered Azor,
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor fathered Zadok, Zadok fathered Achim, Achim fathered Eliud,
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud fathered Eleazar, Eleazar fathered Matthan, and Matthan fathered Jacob.
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jacob fathered Joseph, the husband of Mary, who was the mother of Jesus, who is called the Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So all the generations from Abraham to David were fourteen generations, and from David to the deportation to Babylon were fourteen generations, and from the deportation to Babylon to the Christ were fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ happened in this way. When his mother Mary was engaged to Joseph, before they lived together she was discovered to be pregnant by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Her husband Joseph, being a righteous man and unwilling to disgrace her, decided to divorce her secretly.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	After he had thought about it, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream and said, “Joseph, son of David, don't be afraid to take Mary as your wife, for what has been conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	She will give birth to a son, and you are to name him Jesus, because he is the one who will save his people from their sins.”
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this happened to fulfill what was declared by the Lord through the prophet when he said,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	“See, a virgin will become pregnantand give birth to a son,	and they will name him Immanuel,”which means, “God with us.”
B040C001V024	40	1	24	When Joseph got up from his sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord had commanded him and took Mary as his wife.
B040C001V025	40	1	25	He did not have marital relations with her until she had given birth to a son; and he named him Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	After Jesus had been born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of King Herod, wise men from the east arrived in Jerusalem
B040C002V002	40	2	2	and asked, “Where is the one who was born king of the Jews? We saw his star in the east and have come to worship him.”
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When King Herod heard this he was troubled, and all the people of Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	He called together all the high priests and scribes of the people and asked them where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	They told him, “In Bethlehem of Judea. For that is what was written by the prophet:
B040C002V006	40	2	6	‘O Bethlehem in the land of Judah,you are by no means least among the rulers of Judah.	For from you will come a rulerwho will shepherd my people Israel.’”
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod secretly called together the wise men and found out from them the time the star had appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	Then he sent them to Bethlehem, saying, “As you go, search carefully for the child. When you find him, tell me so that I, too, may go and worship him.”
B040C002V009	40	2	9	After listening to the king, they set out, and the star they had seen in the east went ahead of them until it came and stopped over the place where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	When they saw the star, they were ecstatic with joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	After they went into the house and saw the child with his mother Mary, they fell down and worshiped him. Then they opened their treasure sacks and offered him gifts of gold, frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	Having been warned in a dream not to go back to Herod, they left for their own country by a different road.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	After they had gone, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream and said, “Get up, take the child and his mother, and flee to Egypt. Stay there until I tell you, because Herod intends to search for the child and kill him.”
B040C002V014	40	2	14	So Joseph got up and took the child and his mother and left at night for Egypt.
B040C002V015	40	2	15	He stayed there until Herod's death in order to fulfill what was declared by the Lord through the prophet when he said, “Out of Egypt I called my Son.”
B040C002V016	40	2	16	When Herod saw that he had been tricked by the wise men, he flew into a rage and ordered the execution of all the male children in Bethlehem and all its neighboring regions who were two years old and younger, according to the time that he had determined from the wise men.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then what was declared by the prophet Jeremiah was fulfilled when he said,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	“A voice was heard in Ramah:wailing and great mourning.	Rachel was crying for her children.She refused to be comforted,because they no longer existed.”
B040C002V019	40	2	19	But after Herod died, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt
B040C002V020	40	2	20	and said, “Get up, take the child and his mother, and go to the land of Israel, for those who were trying to kill the child are dead.”
B040C002V021	40	2	21	So Joseph got up and took the child and his mother and went into the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Archelaus was ruling over Judea in place of his father Herod, he was afraid to go there. Having been warned in a dream, he left for the region of Galilee
B040C002V023	40	2	23	and came and settled in a town called Nazareth in order to fulfill what was said by the prophets: “He will be called a Nazarene.”
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In those days John the Baptist appeared, preaching in the wilderness of Judea
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, “Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near!”
B040C003V003	40	3	3	He was the one the prophet Isaiah was referring to when he said,	“He is a voice calling out in the wilderness:‘Prepare the way for the Lord!Make his paths straight!’”
B040C003V004	40	3	4	John had clothing made of camel's hair and wore a leather belt around his waist. His diet consisted of locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then the people of Jerusalem and all Judea and all the region along the Jordan began flocking to him,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	being baptized by him in the Jordan River while they confessed their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when John saw many Pharisees and Sadducees coming to where he was baptizing, he said to them, “You children of serpents! Who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Produce fruit that is consistent with repentance!
B040C003V009	40	3	9	Don't think you can say to yourselves, ‘We have Abraham for our forefather.’ For I tell you that God can raise up descendants for Abraham from these stones!
B040C003V010	40	3	10	The ax already lies against the roots of the trees. So every tree not producing good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I am baptizing you with water as a token of repentance, but the one who is coming after me is stronger than I am, and I am not worthy to carry his sandals. It is he who will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing fork is in his hand. He will clean up his threshing floor and gather his grain into the barn, but he will burn the chaff with inextinguishable fire.”
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan to be baptized by John.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John tried to stop him, saying, “I need to be baptized by you, and are you coming to me?”
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jesus answered him,
B040C003V016	40	3	16	When Jesus had been baptized, he immediately came up out of the water. Suddenly the heavens opened up for him, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and coming to rest on him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	Then a voice from heaven said, “This is my Son, whom I love. I am pleased with him!”
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	After fasting for forty days and forty nights, he finally became hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	The tempter came and said to him, “If you are the Son of God, tell these stones to become loaves of bread.”
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answered,
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil took him to the Holy City and had him stand on the highest point of the temple.
B040C004V006	40	4	6	He said to Jesus, “If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down. For it is written,	‘God will put his angels in charge of you,’and	‘With their hands they will hold you up,so that you will never hit your foot against a rock.’”
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him,
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Once more the devil took him to a very high mountain and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their splendor.
B040C004V009	40	4	9	He said to Jesus, “I will give you all of these things if you will bow down and worship me!”
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then Jesus said to him,
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil left him, and angels came and began ministering to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now when Jesus heard that John had been arrested, he went back to Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	He left Nazareth and went and settled in Capernaum by the sea, in the regions of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	in order to fulfill what was declared by the prophet Isaiah when he said,
B040C004V015	40	4	15	“O Land of Zebulun and land of Naphtali,on the road to the sea, across the Jordan,Galilee of the Gentiles!
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people living in darkness have seen a great light,and for those living in the land and shadow of death,a light has risen.”
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From then on, Jesus began to preach and to say,
B040C004V018	40	4	18	While Jesus was walking beside the Sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers—Simon, who is called Peter, and his brother Andrew. They were throwing a net into the sea because they were fishermen.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	He said to them,
B040C004V020	40	4	20	So at once they left their nets and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	Going on from there he saw two other brothers—James, the son of Zebedee, and his brother John. They were in a boat with their father Zebedee repairing their nets. When he called them,
B040C004V022	40	4	22	they immediately left the boat and their father and followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	Then he went throughout Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, proclaiming the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every disease and every illness among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	His fame spread throughout Syria, and people brought to him all who were sick—those afflicted with various diseases and pains, the demon-possessed, the epileptics, and the paralyzed—and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	Large crowds followed him from Galilee, the Decapolis, Jerusalem, Judea, and from across the Jordan.
