B040C007V028	40	7	28	When Jesus had finished saying all these things, the crowds were utterly amazed at his teaching,
B040C007V029	40	7	29	for he was teaching them like a person who had authority, and not like their scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	When Jesus came down from the hillside, large crowds followed him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	Suddenly a leper came up to him, fell down before him, and said, “Sir, if you want to, you can make me clean.”
B040C008V003	40	8	3	So Jesus reached out his hand, touched him, and said,
B040C008V004	40	8	4	Then Jesus said to him,
B040C008V005	40	8	5	When Jesus returned to Capernaum, a centurion came up to him and begged him repeatedly,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	“Sir, my servant is lying at home paralyzed and in terrible pain.”
B040C008V007	40	8	7	Jesus said to him,
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion replied, “Sir, I am not worthy to have you come under my roof. But just say the word, and my servant will be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I, too, am a man under authority and have soldiers under me. I say to one ‘Go’ and he goes, to another ‘Come’ and he comes, and to my servant ‘Do this’ and he does it.”
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jesus heard this, he was amazed and said to those who were following him,
B040C008V011	40	8	11	
        
B040C008V012	40	8	12	
        
B040C008V013	40	8	13	Then Jesus said to the centurion,
B040C008V014	40	8	14	When Jesus went into Peter's house, he saw Peter's mother-in-law lying in bed, sick with a fever.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	He touched her hand, and the fever left her. Then she got up and began serving him.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	When evening came, people brought to him many who were possessed by demons. He drove out the spirits with a word and healed all those who were sick.
B040C008V017	40	8	17	This was to fulfill what was declared by the prophet Isaiah when he said,	“It was he who took our illnesses awayand removed our diseases.”
B040C008V018	40	8	18	When Jesus saw the large crowds around him, he gave orders to cross to the other side.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	Now a scribe came up and said to him, “Teacher, I will follow you wherever you go.”
B040C008V020	40	8	20	Jesus told him,	
B040C008V021	40	8	21	Then another of his disciples said to him, “Lord, first let me go and bury my father.”
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jesus told him,
B040C008V023	40	8	23	When Jesus got into the boat, his disciples went with him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	Suddenly a violent storm came up on the sea, so that the boat began to be swamped by the waves. Yet Jesus kept sleeping.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	They went to him and woke him up, saying, “Lord, save us! We're going to die!”
B040C008V026	40	8	26	He said to them,
B040C008V027	40	8	27	The men were amazed and said, “What kind of man is this? Even the winds and the sea obey him!”
B040C008V028	40	8	28	When Jesus arrived on the other side in the region of the Gerasenes, two demon-possessed men met him as they were coming out of the tombs. They were so violent that no one could travel on that road.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	Suddenly they screamed, “What do you want with us, Son of God? Did you come here to torture us before the proper time?”
B040C008V030	40	8	30	Now a large herd of pigs was grazing some distance away from them.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	So the demons began to plead with Jesus, saying, “If you drive us out, send us into that herd of pigs.”
B040C008V032	40	8	32	He said to them,
B040C008V033	40	8	33	Now when those who had been taking care of the pigs ran away, they came into the city and reported everything, especially what had happened to the demon-possessed men.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	Then the whole city went out to meet Jesus, and as soon as they saw him, they begged him to leave their region.
B040C009V001	40	9	1	After getting into a boat, Jesus crossed to the other side and came to his own city.
B040C009V002	40	9	2	All at once some people brought him a paralyzed man lying on a stretcher. When Jesus saw their faith, he said to the paralyzed man,
B040C009V003	40	9	3	Then some of the scribes said to themselves, “This fellow is blaspheming!”
B040C009V004	40	9	4	But Jesus knew their thoughts and said,
B040C009V005	40	9	5	
        
B040C009V006	40	9	6	
        
B040C009V007	40	9	7	So the man got up and went home.
B040C009V008	40	9	8	When the crowds saw this, they became frightened and glorified God for giving such authority to humans.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	As Jesus went on from there, he saw a man named Matthew sitting at the tax collector's desk and said to him,
B040C009V010	40	9	10	While he was having dinner at Matthew's home, many tax collectors and sinners arrived and began eating with Jesus and his disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	The Pharisees saw this and said to his disciples, “Why does your teacher eat with tax collectors and sinners?”
B040C009V012	40	9	12	When Jesus heard that, he said,
B040C009V013	40	9	13	
        
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then John's disciples came to Jesus and asked, “Why do we and the Pharisees fast often, but your disciples don't fast?”
B040C009V015	40	9	15	Jesus said to them,
B040C009V016	40	9	16	
        
B040C009V017	40	9	17	
        
B040C009V018	40	9	18	While Jesus was telling them these things, an official came up, fell down before him, and said, “My daughter has just died. But come and lay your hand on her, and she will live.”
B040C009V019	40	9	19	So Jesus got up and followed him, along with his disciples.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	Just then a woman who had been suffering from chronic bleeding for twelve years came up behind him and touched the tassel of his garment.
B040C009V021	40	9	21	For she had been saying to herself, “If I just touch his robe, I will get well.”
B040C009V022	40	9	22	When Jesus turned and saw her, he said,
B040C009V023	40	9	23	When Jesus came to the official's house and saw the flute players and the crowd making a commotion,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	he said,
B040C009V025	40	9	25	But when the crowd had been driven outside, he went in and took the girl by the hand, and she got up.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	The news of this spread throughout that land.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	As Jesus was traveling on from there, two blind men followed him, shouting, “Have mercy on us, Son of David!”
B040C009V028	40	9	28	When he had gone into the house, the blind men came to him.Jesus asked them,
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then he touched their eyes and said,
