B041C015V014	41	15	14	Pilate asked them, “Why? What has he done wrong?”But they shouted even louder, “Crucify him!”
B041C015V015	41	15	15	So Pilate, wanting to satisfy the crowd, released Barabbas for them, but he had Jesus whipped and handed over to be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	The soldiers led Jesus into the courtyard of the palace (that is, the governor's headquarters) and called out the whole guard.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	They dressed him in a purple robe, twisted some thorns into a victor's crown, and placed it on his head.
B041C015V018	41	15	18	They began to greet him, “Long live the king of the Jews!”
B041C015V019	41	15	19	They kept hitting him on the head with a stick, spitting on him, kneeling in front of him, and worshiping him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	When they had finished making fun of him, they stripped him of the purple robe, put his own clothes back on him, and led him away to crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	They forced a certain passer-by who was coming in from the country to carry Jesus’ cross. He was Simon of Cyrene, the father of Alexander and Rufus.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	They took Jesus to a place called Golgotha, which means Skull Place.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	They tried to give him wine mixed with myrrh, but he wouldn't take it.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	Then they crucified him. They divided his clothes among themselves by throwing dice to see what each one would get.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	It was nine in the morning when they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	The written notice of the charge against him read, “The king of the Jews.”
B041C015V027	41	15	27	They crucified two bandits with him, one on his right and the other on his left.
B041C015V029	41	15	29	Those who passed by kept insulting him, shaking their heads, and saying, “Ha! You who were going to destroy the sanctuary and rebuild it in three days—
B041C015V030	41	15	30	save yourself and come down from the cross!”
B041C015V031	41	15	31	In the same way the high priests, along with the scribes, were also making fun of him among themselves. They kept saying, “He saved others but can't save himself!
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let the Christ, the king of Israel, come down from the cross now so that we may see it and believe.” Even the men who were crucified with him kept insulting him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	At twelve noon, darkness came over the whole land until three in the afternoon.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	At three o'clock Jesus cried out with a loud voice,
B041C015V035	41	15	35	When some of the people standing there heard this, they said, “Listen! He's calling for Elijah!”
B041C015V036	41	15	36	So someone ran and soaked a sponge in some sour wine. Then he put it on a stick and offered Jesus a drink, saying, “Wait! Let's see if Elijah comes to take him down!”
B041C015V037	41	15	37	Then Jesus gave a loud cry and breathed his last.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	The curtain in the sanctuary was torn in two from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	When the centurion who stood facing Jesus saw how he had cried out and breathed his last, he said, “This man certainly was the Son of God!”
B041C015V040	41	15	40	Now there were women watching from a distance. Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of young James and Joseph, and Salome.
B041C015V041	41	15	41	They used to accompany him and care for him while he was in Galilee. Many other women who had come up to Jerusalem with him were there, too.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	It was the Day of Preparation, that is, the day before the Sabbath. Since it was already evening,
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathea, a highly respected member of the Council, who was waiting for the kingdom of God, went boldly to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	Pilate wondered if Jesus had already died, so he summoned the centurion to ask him if he was in fact dead.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	When he learned from the centurion that he was dead, he let Joseph have the corpse.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	Joseph bought some linen cloth, took the body down, and wrapped it in the cloth. Then he laid it in a tomb that had been cut out of the rock and rolled a stone against the door of the tomb.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	Now Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joseph saw where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	When the Sabbath was over, Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James, and Salome bought spices to go and anoint Jesus.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	Very early on the first day of the week, when the sun had just come up, they were going to the tomb.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	They kept saying to one another, “Who will roll away the stone for us from the entrance to the tomb?”
B041C016V004	41	16	4	Then they looked up and saw that the stone had been rolled away. (For it was a very large stone.)
B041C016V005	41	16	5	As they went into the tomb, they saw a young man dressed in a white robe sitting on the right side, and they were utterly astonished.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, “Stop being astonished! You are looking for Jesus of Nazareth, who was crucified. He has been raised. He is not here. Look at the place where they laid him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go and tell his disciples, especially Peter, that he is going ahead of you into Galilee. There you will see him, just as he told you.”
B041C016V008	41	16	8	So they left the tomb and ran away, for shock and astonishment had overwhelmed them. They didn't say a thing to anyone, because they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	After Jesus rose early on the first day of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, from whom he had driven out seven demons.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	She went and told those who had been with him and who now were grieving and crying.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	When they heard that he was alive and that he had been seen by her, they refused to believe it.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	After this, he appeared in a different form to two disciples as they were walking into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	They went back and told the others, who didn't believe them either.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	Finally he appeared to the eleven disciples while they were eating. He rebuked them for their unbelief and stubbornness, because they had not believed those who had seen him after he had risen.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	Then he said to them,
B041C016V016	41	16	16	
        
B041C016V017	41	16	17	
        
B041C016V018	41	16	18	
        
B041C016V019	41	16	19	So the Lord Jesus, after talking with them, was taken up to heaven and sat down at the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	The disciples went out and preached everywhere, while the Lord kept working with them and confirming the message by the signs that accompanied it.
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Since many people have attempted to write an orderly account of the events that have been fulfilled among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as they were passed down to us by those who had been eyewitnesses and servants of the word from the beginning,
B042C001V003	42	1	3	I, too, have carefully investigated everything from the beginning and have decided to write an orderly account for you, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	so that you may know the certainty of the things you have been taught.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	In the days of King Herod of Judea, there was a priest named Zechariah, who belonged to the priestly order of Abijah. His wife was a descendant of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	Both of them were righteous in the sight of God, and they lived blamelessly according to all of the commandments and regulations of the Lord.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	They had no children because Elizabeth was barren and because both of them were getting on in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	When Zechariah was serving with his division of priests in God's presence,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	he was chosen by lot to go into the sanctuary of the Lord and burn incense, according to the custom of the priests.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And the entire congregation of people was praying outside at the time when the incense was burned.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	An angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing at the right side of the incense altar.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	When Zechariah saw him, he was shaken, and fear overwhelmed him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, “Stop being afraid, Zechariah, because your prayer has been heard. Your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and you are to name him John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	You will have joy and gladness, and many people will rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he will be great in the sight of the Lord. He will never drink wine or any strong drink, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit even before he is born.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	He will bring many of Israel's descendants back to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	He is the one who will go before the Lord with the spirit and power of Elijah to turn the hearts of parents to their children and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, and to prepare the people to be ready for the Lord.”
B042C001V018	42	1	18	Then Zechariah said to the angel, “How can I know this is so? For I am an old man, and my wife is getting on in years.”
B042C001V019	42	1	19	The angel answered him, “I am Gabriel! I stand in the very presence of God. I have been sent to speak to you and to tell you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	But because you did not believe my words, which will be fulfilled at the proper time, you will become silent and unable to speak until the day this happens.”
B042C001V021	42	1	21	Meanwhile, the people kept waiting for Zechariah and wondering why he stayed in the sanctuary so long.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	But when he did come out, he was unable to speak to them. Then they realized that he had seen a vision in the sanctuary. He kept motioning to them but remained unable to speak.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	When the days of his service were over, he went home.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	After this, his wife Elizabeth became pregnant and remained in seclusion for five months. She said,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	“This is what the Lord did for me when he looked favorably on me and took away my public disgrace.”
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Now in the sixth month of her pregnancy, the angel Gabriel was sent by God to a city in Galilee called Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a virgin engaged to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. The virgin's name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	The angel came to her and said, “Greetings, you who are highly favored! The Lord is with you!”
B042C001V029	42	1	29	She was startled by his statement and tried to figure out what his greeting meant.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	Then the angel told her, “Stop being afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	Listen! You will become pregnant and give birth to a son, and you are to name him Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He will be great and will be called the Son of the Most High, and the Lord God will give him the throne of his forefather David.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	He will rule over the house of Jacob forever, and his kingdom will never end.”
B042C001V034	42	1	34	Mary asked the angel, “How can this be, since I have not had relations with a man?”
B042C001V035	42	1	35	The angel answered her, “The Holy Spirit will come over you, and the power of the Most High will cover you. Therefore, the child will be holy and will be called the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And listen! Elizabeth, your relative, has herself conceived a son in her old age. This is the sixth month for the woman who was said to be barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For nothing is impossible for God.”
B042C001V038	42	1	38	Then Mary said, “Truly I am the Lord's servant. Let everything you have said happen to me.” Then the angel left her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	At this time Mary set out hurriedly for a Judean city in the hill country.
B042C001V040	42	1	40	She went into Zechariah's home and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	When Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting, the baby jumped in her womb. Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and exclaimed with a loud cry, “How blessed are you among women, and how blessed is the fruit of your womb!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	Why should this happen to me, to have the mother of my Lord visit me!
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For as soon as the sound of your greeting reached my ears, the baby in my womb jumped for joy.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	How blessed is this woman for believing that what was spoken to her by the Lord would be fulfilled!”
B042C001V046	42	1	46	Then Mary said,	“My soul praises the greatness of the Lord!
B042C001V047	42	1	47	My spirit exults in God, my Savior,
B042C001V048	42	1	48	for he has looked favorably on his humble servant.	From now on, all generations will call me blessed,
B042C001V049	42	1	49	because the Almighty has done great things for me.His name is holy.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	His mercy lasts from generation to generationfor those who fear him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He displayed his mighty power with his arm.	He scattered people who were proud in mind and heart.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He pulled powerful rulers from their thronesand lifted up humble people.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	He filled hungry people with good thingsand sent rich people away with nothing.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He helped his servant Israel,remembering to be merciful,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	according to the promise he made to our ancestors—to Abraham and his descendants forever.”
B042C001V056	42	1	56	Now Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months and then went back home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	When the time came for Elizabeth to have her child, she gave birth to a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	Her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had shown his great mercy to her, and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	On the eighth day they went to circumcise the child. They were going to name him Zechariah after his father,
B042C001V060	42	1	60	but his mother said, “Absolutely not! He must be named John.”
B042C001V061	42	1	61	Their friends said to her, “None of your relatives has that name.”
B042C001V062	42	1	62	So they motioned to the baby's father to see what he wanted to name him.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	He asked for a writing tablet and wrote, “His name is John.” And everyone was amazed.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	Suddenly, Zechariah's mouth was opened, his tongue was set free, and he began to speak and to praise God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	Fear came over all their neighbors, and throughout the hill country of Judea all these things were being discussed.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	All who heard about it debated in their minds what had happened and said, “What will this child become?” For it was obvious that the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	Then his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied:
B042C001V068	42	1	68	“Blessed be the Lord God of Israel!He has taken care of his people and has set them free.
B042C001V069	42	1	69	He has raised up a mighty Savior for usfrom the family of his servant David,
B042C001V070	42	1	70	just as he promised long ago		through the mouth of his holy prophets
B042C001V071	42	1	71	that he would save us from our enemiesand from the grip of all who hate us.
B042C001V072	42	1	72	He has shown mercy to our ancestorsand remembered his holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	the oath that he swore to our ancestor Abraham.	He granted us
B042C001V074	42	1	74	deliverance from our enemies' gripso that we could serve him without fear
B042C001V075	42	1	75	and be holy and righteous before him all of our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, will be called a prophet of the Most High.	For you will go ahead of the Lord to prepare his ways
B042C001V077	42	1	77	and to give his people the knowledge of salvationthrough the forgiveness of their sins.
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Because of the tender mercy of our God,the dawn from on high has broken upon us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	to shine on those who sit in darkness and in death's shadow,and to guide our feet into the way of peace.”
B042C001V080	42	1	80	Now the child continued to grow and to become strong in spirit. He lived in the wilderness until the day he appeared in Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	Now in those days a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that the whole world should be registered.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	This was the first registration taken while Quirinius was governor of Syria.
B042C002V003	42	2	3	So all the people went to their hometowns to be registered.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	Joseph, too, went up from the city of Nazareth in Galilee to Judea, to the city of David called Bethlehem, because he was a descendant of the household and family of David.
B042C002V005	42	2	5	He went there to be registered with Mary, who had been promised to him in marriage and was pregnant.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	While they were there, the time came for her to have her baby,
B042C002V007	42	2	7	and she gave birth to her first child, a son. She wrapped him in strips of cloth and laid him in a manger, because there was not any room for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	In that region there were shepherds living in the fields, watching their flock during the night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	An angel of the Lord appeared to them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were terrified.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	Then the angel said to them, “Stop being afraid! Listen! I am bringing you good news of great joy for all the people.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	Today your Savior, Christ the Lord, was born in the city of David.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this will be a sign for you: You will find a baby wrapped in strips of cloth and lying in a manger.”
B042C002V013	42	2	13	Suddenly a multitude of the Heavenly Army appeared with the angel, praising God and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	“Glory to God in the highest, and peace on earth to people who enjoy his favor!”
B042C002V015	42	2	15	When the angels had left them and gone back to heaven, the shepherds said to one another, “Let's go to Bethlehem and see what has taken place that the Lord has told us about.”
B042C002V016	42	2	16	So they went quickly and found Mary and Joseph with the baby, who was lying in the manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	When they saw this, they repeated what they had been told about this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	All who heard it were amazed at what the shepherds told them,
B042C002V019	42	2	19	but Mary continued to treasure in her heart all these things and to ponder them.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	Then the shepherds returned to their flock, glorifying and praising God for everything they had heard and seen, just as it had been told to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	After eight days had passed, the child was circumcised and named Jesus, the name given him by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	When the time came for their purification according to the law of Moses, Joseph and Mary took Jesus up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord,
B042C002V023	42	2	23	as it is written in the law of the Lord, “Every firstborn son is to be designated as holy to the Lord.”
B042C002V024	42	2	24	They also offered a sacrifice according to what is specified in the law of the Lord: “a pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons.”
B042C002V025	42	2	25	Now a man named Simeon was in Jerusalem. This man was righteous and devout. He was waiting for the one who would comfort Israel, and the Holy Spirit rested on him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he would not die until he had seen the Lord's Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	Moved by the Spirit, he went into the temple. When the parents brought the child Jesus to do for him what was customary under the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	Simeon took the child in his arms and praised God, saying,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	“Master, now you are allowing your servant to leave in peaceaccording to your word.
B042C002V030	42	2	30	For my eyes have seen your salvation,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	which you prepared for all people to see—
B042C002V032	42	2	32	a light that will reveal salvation to the Gentiles		and bring glory to your people Israel.”
B042C002V033	42	2	33	Jesus’ father and mother kept wondering at the things being said about him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	Then Simeon blessed them and said to Mary, his mother, “This child is destined to cause many in Israel to fall or rise. He will be a sign that will be disputed,
B042C002V035	42	2	35	so that the inner thoughts of many people might be revealed. Indeed, a sword will pierce your own soul, too.”
B042C002V036	42	2	36	Now Anna, a prophetess, was also there. She was a descendant of Phanuel from the tribe of Asher. She was very old, having lived with her husband for seven years after her marriage,
B042C002V037	42	2	37	and then as a widow for eighty-four years. She never left the temple, but continued to worship there night and day with times of fasting and prayer.
B042C002V038	42	2	38	Just then she came forward and began to thank God and to speak about the child to all who were waiting for the redemption of Jerusalem.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	After doing everything required by the law of the Lord, Joseph and Mary returned to their hometown of Nazareth in Galilee.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	Meanwhile, the child continued to grow and to become strong. He was filled with wisdom, and God's favor was with him.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	Every year Jesus’ parents would go to Jerusalem for the Passover Festival.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	When he was twelve years old, they went up to the festival as usual.
B042C002V043	42	2	43	When the days of the festival were over, they left for home. The young man Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem, but his parents did not know it.
B042C002V044	42	2	44	They thought that he was in the group of travelers. After traveling for a day, they started looking for him among their relatives and friends.
B042C002V045	42	2	45	When they did not find him, they returned to Jerusalem, searching desperately for him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	Three days later they found him in the temple sitting among the teachers, listening to them, and asking them questions.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	All who heard him were amazed at his intelligence and his answers.
B042C002V048	42	2	48	When his parents saw him, they were shocked. His mother asked him, “Son, why have you treated us like this? Your father and I have been worried sick looking for you!”
B042C002V049	42	2	49	He said to them,
B042C002V050	42	2	50	But they did not understand what he said to them.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	Then he went down with them and returned to Nazareth; and he remained in submission to them. His mother continued to treasure all these things in her heart.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	Meanwhile, Jesus kept on growing in wisdom and maturity, and in favor with God and his fellow man.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Caesar Tiberius, when Pontius Pilate was governor of Judea, Herod tetrarch of Galilee, his brother Philip tetrarch of the region of Ituraea and Trachonitis, Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	and Annas and Caiaphas high priests, the word of God came to John, the son of Zechariah, in the wilderness.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	John went into all the region around the Jordan, proclaiming a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins,
B042C003V004	42	3	4	as it is written in the book of the words of the prophet Isaiah,	“He is a voice calling out in the wilderness:‘Prepare the way for the Lord! Make his paths straight!
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Every valley will be filled,and every mountain and hill will be leveled.	The crooked ways will be made straight,and the rough roads will be made smooth.
B042C003V006	42	3	6	Everyone will see the salvationthat God has provided.’”
B042C003V007	42	3	7	John would say to the crowds that were coming out to be baptized by him, “You children of serpents! Who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Produce fruit that is consistent with repentance! Don't begin to say to yourselves, ‘We have Abraham for our forefather.’ For I tell you that God can raise up descendants for Abraham from these stones!
B042C003V009	42	3	9	The ax already lies against the roots of the trees. So every tree not producing good fruit will be cut down and thrown into a fire.”
B042C003V010	42	3	10	The crowds kept asking him, “What, then, should we do?”
B042C003V011	42	3	11	He answered them, “The person who has two coats must share with the one who doesn't have any, and the person who has food must do the same.”
B042C003V012	42	3	12	Even some tax collectors came to be baptized. They asked him, “Teacher, what should we do?”
B042C003V013	42	3	13	He told them, “Stop collecting more money than the amount you are told to collect.”
B042C003V014	42	3	14	Even some soldiers were asking him, “And what should we do?”He told them, “Never extort money from anyone by threats or blackmail, and be satisfied with your pay.”
B042C003V015	42	3	15	Now the people were filled with expectation, and all of them were wondering if John was perhaps the Christ.
B042C003V016	42	3	16	John replied to all of them, “I am baptizing you with water, but the one who is stronger than I am is coming, and I am not worthy to untie his sandal straps. It is he who will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.
B042C003V017	42	3	17	His winnowing fork is in his hand to clean up his threshing floor. He will gather the grain into his barn, but he will burn the chaff with inextinguishable fire.”
B042C003V018	42	3	18	With many other exhortations John continued to proclaim the good news to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	Now Herod the tetrarch had been rebuked by John because he had married his brother's wife Herodias and because of all the evil things Herod had done.
B042C003V020	42	3	20	Added to all this, Herod locked John up in prison.
B042C003V021	42	3	21	When all the people had been baptized, Jesus, too, was baptized. While he was praying, heaven opened,
