B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning, the Word existed. The Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	He existed in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	Through him all things were made, and apart from him nothing was made that has been made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and that life brought light to humanity.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shines on in the darkness, and the darkness has never put it out.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	He came as a witness to testify about the light, so that all might believe through him.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the light, but he came to testify about the light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	This was the true light that enlightens every person by his coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world was made through him. Yet the world did not recognize him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own creation, yet his own people did not receive him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	However, to all who received him, to those believing in his name, he gave authority to become God's children,
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who were born, not merely in a physical sense, or from a fleshly impulse, or from man's desire, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	The Word became flesh and tabernacled among us. We gazed on his glory, the kind of glory that belongs to the Father's unique Son, full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John told the truth about him when he cried out, “This is the person about whom I said, ‘The one who comes after me ranks ahead of me, because he existed before me.’”
B043C001V016	43	1	16	From his fullness we have all received one gracious gift after another.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For while the law was given through Moses, grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one has ever seen God. The unique God, who is close to the Father's side, has revealed him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	This was John's testimony when the Jews sent priests and Levites to him from Jerusalem to ask him, “Who are you?”
B043C001V020	43	1	20	He spoke openly and did not deny it, but confessed, “I am not the Christ.”
B043C001V021	43	1	21	So they asked him, “Well then, are you Elijah?”He said, “I am not.”“Are you the Prophet?”He answered, “No.”
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then they said to him, “Who are you? We must give an answer to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?”
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He replied,	“I am the voice of one crying out in the wilderness,‘Make the way of the Lord straight,’”as the prophet Isaiah said.
