B043C018V001	43	18	1	After Jesus had said this, he went with his disciples across the Kidron valley to a place where there was a garden, which he and his disciples entered.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	Now Judas, who betrayed him, also knew the place because Jesus often met there with his disciples.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	So Judas took a detachment of soldiers and some officers from the high priests and the Pharisees and went there with lanterns, torches, and weapons.
