B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus answered him,
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Then Annas sent him, with his hands tied, to Caiaphas the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	Meanwhile, Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. They said to him, “You aren't one of his disciples, too, are you?”He denied it by saying, “I am not!”
B043C018V026	43	18	26	Then one of the high priest's servants, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, said, “I saw you in the garden with him, didn't I?”
B043C018V027	43	18	27	Peter again denied it, and immediately a rooster crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	Then they led Jesus from Caiaphas to the governor's headquarters. It was early in the morning, and the Jews did not go into the headquarters for fear that they might become unclean and be unable to eat the Passover meal.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	So Pilate came out to them and said, “What accusation are you bringing against this man?”
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered him, “If he weren't a criminal, we wouldn't have handed him over to you.”
B043C018V031	43	18	31	Pilate told them, “You take him and try him according to your law.”The Jews said to him, “It is not legal for us to put anyone to death.”
B043C018V032	43	18	32	This was to fulfill what Jesus had said when he indicated the kind of death he was to die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	So Pilate went back into the governor's headquarters, summoned Jesus, and said to him, “Are you the king of the Jews?”
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus replied,
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilate replied, “I am not a Jew, am I? It is your own nation and high priests who have handed you over to me. What have you done?”
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus answered,
B043C018V037	43	18	37	Pilate said to him, “So you are a king?”Jesus answered,
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to him, “What is ‘truth’?” After he said this, he went out to the Jews again and told them, “I find no basis for a charge against him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	But you have a custom that I release one person for you at Passover. Do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?”
B043C018V040	43	18	40	At this, they shouted out again, “Not this fellow, but Barabbas!” Now Barabbas was a revolutionary.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	Then Pilate had Jesus taken away and whipped.
B043C019V002	43	19	2	The soldiers twisted some thorns into a victor's crown, put it on his head, and threw a purple robe on him.
B043C019V003	43	19	3	They kept coming up to him and saying, “Long live the king of the Jews!” Then they began to slap him on the face.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	Pilate went outside again and told the Jews, “Look, I am bringing him out to you to let you know that I find no basis for a charge against him.”
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Then Jesus came outside, wearing the victor's crown of thorns and the purple robe.Pilate said to them, “Here is the man!”
B043C019V006	43	19	6	When the high priests and the officials saw him, they shouted, “Crucify him! Crucify him!”Pilate told them, “You take him and crucify him. I find no basis for a charge against him.”
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jews answered Pilate, “We have a law, and according to that law he must die because he made himself out to be the Son of God.”
B043C019V008	43	19	8	When Pilate heard this, he became even more afraid.
B043C019V009	43	19	9	Returning to his headquarters, he said to Jesus, “Where are you from?” But Jesus gave him no reply.
B043C019V010	43	19	10	So Pilate said to him, “Aren't you going to speak to me? You realize, don't you, that I have the authority to release you and the authority to crucify you?”
B043C019V011	43	19	11	Jesus answered him,
B043C019V012	43	19	12	From then on, Pilate tried to release him, but the Jews kept shouting, “If you release this fellow, you're not a friend of Caesar! Anyone who claims to be a king is defying Caesar!”
B043C019V013	43	19	13	When Pilate heard these words, he brought Jesus outside and sat down on the judgment seat in a place called The Pavement, which in Hebrew is called Gabbatha.
B043C019V014	43	19	14	Now it was the Preparation Day for the Passover, about twelve noon. He said to the Jews, “Here is your king!”
B043C019V015	43	19	15	Then they shouted, “Take him away! Take him away! Crucify him!”Pilate said to them, “Should I crucify your king?”The high priests responded, “We have no king but Caesar!”
B043C019V016	43	19	16	Then Pilate handed him over to be crucified, and they took Jesus away.
B043C019V017	43	19	17	Carrying the cross all by himself, he went out to what is called The Place of a Skull, which in Hebrew is called Golgotha.
B043C019V018	43	19	18	There they crucified him, along with two others, one on each side of him with Jesus in the middle.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	Pilate wrote an inscription and put it on the cross. It read, “Jesus from Nazareth, the King of the Jews.”
B043C019V020	43	19	20	Many Jews read this inscription, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city. It was written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	Then the Jewish high priests told Pilate, “Don't write, ‘The King of the Jews,’ but that this fellow said,
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilate replied, “What I have written I have written.”
B043C019V023	43	19	23	When the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they took his clothes and divided them into four parts, one for each soldier, and took his cloak as well. The cloak was seamless, woven in one piece from the top down.
B043C019V024	43	19	24	So they said to each other, “Let's not tear it. Instead, let's throw dice to see who gets it.” This was to fulfill the Scripture that says,	“They divided my clothes among themselves,and for my clothing they threw dice.”So that is what the soldiers did.
B043C019V025	43	19	25	Meanwhile, standing near Jesus’ cross were his mother, his mother's sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	When Jesus saw his mother and the disciple whom he kept loving standing there, he said to his mother,
B043C019V027	43	19	27	Then he said to the disciple,
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After this, when Jesus realized that everything was now completed, he said (in order to fulfill the Scripture),
B043C019V029	43	19	29	A jar of sour wine was standing there, so they put a sponge full of the wine on a branch of hyssop and held it to his mouth.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	After Jesus had taken the wine, he said,
B043C019V031	43	19	31	Since it was the Preparation Day, the Jews did not want to leave the bodies on the crosses during the Sabbath, for that was a particularly important Sabbath. So they asked Pilate to have the men's legs broken and the bodies removed.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	So the soldiers went and broke the legs of the first man and then of the other man who had been crucified with him.
B043C019V033	43	19	33	But when they came to Jesus and saw that he was already dead, they did not break his legs.
B043C019V034	43	19	34	Instead, one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and blood and water immediately came out.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	The one who saw this has testified, and his testimony is true. He knows he is telling the truth so that you, too, may believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For these things happened so that the Scripture might be fulfilled: 	“None of his bones will be broken.”
B043C019V037	43	19	37	In addition, another passage of Scripture says, 	“They will look on the one whom they pierced.”
B043C019V038	43	19	38	Later on, Joseph of Arimathea, who was a disciple of Jesus (though a secret one because he was afraid of the Jews), asked Pilate to let him remove the body of Jesus. Pilate gave him permission, and he came and removed his body.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	Nicodemus, the man who had first come to Jesus at night, also arrived, bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes weighing about a hundred pounds.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	They took the body of Jesus and wrapped it in linen cloths along with spices, according to the burial custom of the Jews.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	A garden was located in the place where he was crucified, and in that garden was a new tomb in which no one had yet been placed.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	Because it was the Jewish Preparation Day, and because the tomb was nearby, they put Jesus there.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	On the first day of the week, early in the morning and while it was still dark, Mary Magdalene went to the tomb and noticed that the stone had been removed from the tomb.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	So she ran off and went to Simon Peter and the other disciple, whom Jesus kept loving. She told them, “They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we don't know where they have put him!”
B043C020V003	43	20	3	So Peter and the other disciple set out to go to the tomb.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	The two of them were running together, but the other disciple ran faster than Peter and came to the tomb first.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	Bending over to look inside, he noticed the linen cloths lying there but didn't go in.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	At this point Simon Peter arrived, following him, and went straight into the tomb. He observed that the linen cloths were lying there,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	and that the handkerchief that had been on Jesus’ head was not lying with the linen cloths but was rolled up in a separate place.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	Then the other disciple, who arrived at the tomb first, went inside, looked, and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	For they did not yet understand the Scripture that said that he had to rise from the dead.
B043C020V010	43	20	10	So the disciples went back to their homes.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	Meanwhile, Mary stood crying outside the tomb. As she cried, she bent over and looked into the tomb.
B043C020V012	43	20	12	She saw two angels in white clothes who were sitting down, one at the head and the other at the foot of the place where Jesus’ body had been lying.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	They said to her, “Woman, why are you crying?”She told them, “Because they have taken away my Lord, and I don't know where they have put him.”
B043C020V014	43	20	14	After she had said this, she turned around and noticed Jesus standing there, without realizing that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her,
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jesus said to her,
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jesus told her,
B043C020V018	43	20	18	So Mary Magdalene went and announced to the disciples, “I have seen the Lord!” She also told them what he had said to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	It was the evening of the first day of the week, and the doors of the house where the disciples had met were locked because they were afraid of the Jews. Jesus came and stood among them. He said to them,
