B043C020V026	43	20	26	A week later his disciples were again inside, and Thomas was with them. Even though the doors were shut, Jesus came, stood among them, and said,
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then he said to Thomas,
B043C020V028	43	20	28	Thomas answered him, saying “My Lord and my God!”
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jesus said to him,
B043C020V030	43	20	30	Jesus performed many other signs in the presence of his disciples that are not recorded in this book.
B043C020V031	43	20	31	But these have been recorded so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and so that through believing you may have life in his name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	Later on, Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples at the Sea of Tiberias, and he revealed himself in this way.
B043C021V002	43	21	2	Simon Peter, Thomas (called the Twin), Nathaniel from Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, and two of his other disciples were together.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, “I'm going fishing.”They told him, “We'll go with you, too.” So they went out and got into the boat but didn't catch a thing that night.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	Just as dawn was breaking, Jesus stood on the shore. The disciples didn't realize it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	Jesus said to them,
B043C021V006	43	21	6	He told them,
