B043C021V008	43	21	8	But the other disciples came in the boat, dragging the net full of fish. They were only about a hundred yards away from the shore.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	When they arrived at the shore, they saw a charcoal fire with fish lying on it, and some bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	Jesus told them,
B043C021V011	43	21	11	So Simon Peter went aboard and dragged the net ashore. It was full of large fish—153 of them. And although there were so many of them, the net was not torn.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	Then Jesus said to them,
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Jesus went and took the bread and gave it to them, and did the same with the fish.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This was now the third time that Jesus revealed himself to the disciples after he had been raised from the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	When they had finished breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter,
B043C021V016	43	21	16	Then he said to him a second time,
B043C021V017	43	21	17	He said to him a third time,
B043C021V018	43	21	18	
        
