B043C021V020	43	21	20	Peter turned around and noticed the disciple whom Jesus kept loving following them. He was the one who had put his head on Jesus’ chest at the supper and had said, “Lord, who is the one who is going to betray you?”
B043C021V021	43	21	21	When Peter saw him, he said, “Lord, what about him?”
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said to him,
B043C021V023	43	21	23	So the rumor spread among the brothers that this disciple wasn't going to die. Yet Jesus didn't say to him that he wasn't going to die, but,
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who is testifying to these things and has written them down. We know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	Of course, Jesus also did many other things, and I suppose that if every one of them were written down the world couldn't contain the books that would be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	In my first book, Theophilus, I wrote about everything Jesus did and taught from the beginning,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	up to the day when he was taken up to heaven after giving orders by the Holy Spirit to the apostles he had chosen.
B044C001V003	44	1	3	After he had suffered, he had shown himself alive to them by many convincing proofs, appearing to them through a period of forty days and telling them about the kingdom of God.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	While he was meeting with them, he ordered them,
B044C001V005	44	1	5	
        
B044C001V006	44	1	6	Now those who had come together began to ask him, “Lord, is this the time when you will restore the kingdom to Israel?”
B044C001V007	44	1	7	He answered them,
B044C001V008	44	1	8	
        
B044C001V009	44	1	9	After saying this, he was taken up while they were watching, and a cloud took him out of their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	While he was going and they were gazing up toward heaven, two men in white robes were standing right beside them.
B044C001V011	44	1	11	They asked, “Men of Galilee, why do you stand looking up toward heaven? This same Jesus, who has been taken up from you into heaven, will come back in the same way you saw him go up into heaven.”
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the Mount of Olives, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day's journey away.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	When they came into the city, they went to the upstairs room where they had been staying. They were Peter and John; James and Andrew; Philip and Thomas; Bartholomew and Matthew; James the son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot; and Judas the son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	With one mind all of them kept devoting themselves to prayer, along with the women, including Mary the mother of Jesus, and his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	At that time Peter got up among the brothers (there were about 120 people present) and said,
B044C001V016	44	1	16	“Brothers, the Scripture had to be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke long ago through the voice of David about Judas, who was the guide to those who arrested Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he was one of our number and was chosen to share in this ministry.”
B044C001V018	44	1	18	(Now this man bought a field with the money he got for his crime. Falling on his face, he burst open in the middle, and all his intestines gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	This became known to all the residents of Jerusalem, so that this field is called in their language Hakeldama, that is, “The Field of Blood”.)
B044C001V020	44	1	20	“For in the Book of Psalms it is written,	‘Let his estate be desolate, and let no one live on it,’and	‘Let someone else take over his office.’
B044C001V021	44	1	21	Therefore, one of the men who has associated with us all the time the Lord Jesus came and went among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	beginning with the baptism of John until the day he was taken up from us, must become a witness with us to his resurrection.”
B044C001V023	44	1	23	So they nominated two men—Joseph called Barsabbas, who also was called Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	Then they prayed, “Lord, you know the hearts of all people. Show us which one of these two men you have chosen
B044C001V025	44	1	25	to serve in this office of apostle, from which Judas fell away to go to his own place.”
B044C001V026	44	1	26	So they drew lots for them, and when the lot fell on Matthias, he was added to the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	When the day of Pentecost came, all of them were together in one place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	Suddenly, a sound like the roaring of a mighty windstorm came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	They saw tongues like flames of fire that separated, and one rested on each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	All of them were filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues as the Spirit gave them that ability.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	Now devout Jews from every nation under heaven were living in Jerusalem.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	When that sound came, the crowd rushed together and was startled because each one heard the disciples speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	Stunned and amazed, they asked, “All of these people who are speaking are Galileans, aren't they?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	So how is it that each one of us hears them speaking in his own native language?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	We are Parthians, Medes, Elamites, people from Mesopotamia, Judea, Cappadocia, Pontus, Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia, Pamphylia, Egypt, the district of Libya near Cyrene, and visitors from Rome.
B044C002V011	44	2	11	We are Jews, proselytes, Cretans, and Arabs. Yet we hear them telling in our own tongues the great deeds of God!”
B044C002V012	44	2	12	All of them continued to be stunned and puzzled, and they kept asking one another, “What can this mean?”
B044C002V013	44	2	13	But others kept saying in derision, “They're full of sweet wine!”
B044C002V014	44	2	14	Then Peter stood up with the eleven, raised his voice, and addressed them, “Men of Judea and everyone living in Jerusalem! You must understand something, so pay close attention to my words.
B044C002V015	44	2	15	These men are not drunk as you suppose, for it's only nine o'clock in the morning.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	Rather, this is what was spoken through the prophet Joel:
B044C002V017	44	2	17	‘In the last days, God says,I will pour out my Spirit on everyone.	Your sons and your daughters will prophesy,your young men will see visions,and your old men will dream dreams.
B044C002V018	44	2	18	In those days I will even pour out my Spiriton my slaves, men and women alike,and they will prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	I will work wonders in the sky aboveand signs on the earth below:blood, fire, and clouds of smoke.
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun will turn to darkness,and the moon to blood,before the coming of the great and glorious Day of the Lord.
B044C002V021	44	2	21	Then whoever calls on the name of the Lordwill be saved.’
B044C002V022	44	2	22	“Fellow Israelites, listen to these words! Jesus from Nazareth was a man accredited to you by God through miracles, wonders, and signs that God performed through him among you, as you yourselves know.
B044C002V023	44	2	23	This very man, after he was arrested according to the predetermined plan and foreknowledge of God, you crucified and killed by the hands of lawless men.
B044C002V024	44	2	24	But God raised him up and destroyed the pains of death, since it was impossible for him to be held in its power.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David says about him,	‘I always see the Lord in front of me,for he is at my right handso that I cannot be shaken.
B044C002V026	44	2	26	That is why my heart is gladand my tongue rejoices,yes, even my body still rests securely in hope.
B044C002V027	44	2	27	For you will not abandon my soul to Hadesor allow your Holy One to experience decay.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	You have made the ways of life known to me,and you will fill me with gladness in your presence.’
B044C002V029	44	2	29	“Brothers, I can tell you confidently that the patriarch David died and was buried, and that his tomb is among us to this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	Therefore, since he was a prophet and knew that God had promised him with an oath to put one of his descendants on his throne,
B044C002V031	44	2	31	he looked ahead and spoke about the resurrection of the Christ:	‘He was not abandoned to Hades,and his flesh did not experience decay.’
B044C002V032	44	2	32	It was this very Jesus whom God raised, and of that we are all witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	He has been exalted to the right hand of God, has received from the Father the promised Holy Spirit, and has poured out what you are seeing and hearing.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David did not go up to heaven, but he said,	‘The Lord said to my Lord,“Sit at my right hand,
B044C002V035	44	2	35	until I make your enemies your footstool.”’
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Therefore, let the entire house of Israel understand beyond a doubt that God made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord and Christ!”
B044C002V037	44	2	37	When they heard this, they were pierced to the heart. They asked Peter and the other apostles, “Brothers, what should we do?”
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Peter answered them, “Repent and be baptized, every one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins. Then you will receive the Holy Spirit as a gift.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For this promise belongs to you and your children, as well as to all those who are far away, whom the Lord our God may call to himself.”
B044C002V040	44	2	40	With many more words he continued to testify and to plead with them, saying, “Be saved from this corrupt generation!”
B044C002V041	44	2	41	So those who welcomed his message were baptized, and that day about 3,000 persons were added to them.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	They continually devoted themselves to the teaching of the apostles, to fellowship, to the breaking of bread, and to times of prayer.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	A sense of fear came over everyone, and many wonders and signs were being done by the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	All the believers were together, and they shared everything with one another.
B044C002V045	44	2	45	They made it their practice to sell their possessions and goods and to distribute the proceeds to anyone who was in need.
