B044C003V001	44	3	1	Peter and John were going up to the temple for the hour of prayer at three in the afternoon.
B044C003V002	44	3	2	Now a man who had been crippled from birth was being carried in. Every day people would lay him at what was called the Beautiful Gate so that he could beg from those who were going into the temple.
B044C003V003	44	3	3	When he saw that Peter and John were about to go into the temple, he asked them to give him something.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	Peter, along with John, looked him straight in the eye and said, “Look at us!”
B044C003V005	44	3	5	So the man watched them closely, expecting to get something from them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	However, Peter said, “I don't have any silver or gold, but I'll give you what I do have. In the name of Jesus Christ from Nazareth, walk!”
B044C003V007	44	3	7	Then Peter took hold of his right hand and began to help him up. Immediately his feet and ankles became strong,
B044C003V008	44	3	8	and he sprung to his feet, stood up, and began to walk. Then he went with them into the temple, walking, jumping, and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	When all the people saw him walking and praising God,
B044C003V010	44	3	10	they knew that he was the man who used to sit and beg at the Beautiful Gate of the temple, and they were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	While he was holding on to Peter and John, all the people came running together to them in what was called Solomon's Colonnade. They were dumbfounded.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	When Peter saw this, he said to the people: “Fellow Israelites, why are you wondering about this, and why are you staring at us as if by our own power or godliness we made him walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob—the God of our ancestors—has glorified his servant Jesus, whom you betrayed and rejected in the presence of Pilate, even though he had decided to let him go.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	You rejected the Holy and Righteous One and asked to have a murderer given to you,
B044C003V015	44	3	15	and you killed the source of life, whom God raised from the dead. We are witnesses to that.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	It is his name, that is, by the faith of his name, that has healed this man whom you see and know. Yes, the faith that comes through him has given him this perfect health in the presence of all of you.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	“And now, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance like your leaders.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	This is how God fulfilled what he had predicted through the voice of all the prophets—that his Christ would suffer.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Therefore, repent and turn to him to have your sins blotted out,
B044C003V020	44	3	20	so that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord and so that he may send you Jesus, the Christ whom he appointed long ago.
B044C003V021	44	3	21	Heaven must receive him until the time of universal restoration that God announced long ago through the voice of his holy prophets.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	In fact, Moses said,‘The Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among your brothers. You must listen to everything he tells you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	Any person who will not listen to that prophet will be utterly destroyed from among the people.’
B044C003V024	44	3	24	“Indeed, all the prophets who have spoken, from Samuel and those who followed him, also predicted these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the descendants of the prophets and the heirs of the covenant that God made with your ancestors when he said to Abraham, ‘Through your descendant all the families of the earth will be blessed.’
B044C003V026	44	3	26	When God raised up his servant, he sent him first to you to bless you by turning every one of you from your evil ways.”
B044C004V001	44	4	1	While they were speaking to the people, the priests, the commander of the temple guards, and the Sadducees came to them.
