B044C004V023	44	4	23	After they were released, they went to their own people and told them everything the high priests and the elders had said.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	When they heard this, they all raised their voices to God and said, “Master, you made heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them.
B044C004V025	44	4	25	You said by the Holy Spirit through the voice of our ancestor, your servant David,	‘Why do the Gentiles rage,and the people devise useless plots?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings of the earth take their stand,and rulers meet together against the Lordand against his Christ.’
B044C004V027	44	4	27	“For in this city both Herod and Pontius Pilate actually met together with the Gentiles and the people of Israel against your holy servant Jesus, whom you anointed,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	to do all that your hand and your will had predetermined to take place.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	Lord, pay attention to their threats now, and allow your servants to speak your word with all boldness
B044C004V030	44	4	30	as you stretch out your hand to heal and to perform signs and wonders through the name of your holy servant Jesus.”
B044C004V031	44	4	31	When they had prayed, the place where they were meeting was shaken, and all of them were filled with the Holy Spirit and continued to speak the word of God with boldness.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	Now the whole group of believers was one in heart and soul, and nobody called any of his possessions his own. Instead, they shared everything they owned.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	With great power the apostles continued to testify to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and abundant grace was on them all.
