B044C007V001	44	7	1	Then the high priest asked, “Is this true?”
B044C007V002	44	7	2	Stephen replied, “Listen, brothers and fathers! The glorious God appeared to our ancestor Abraham while he was in Mesopotamia before he settled in Haran.
B044C007V003	44	7	3	He said to him, ‘Leave your country and your relatives and go to the land I will show you.’
B044C007V004	44	7	4	So he left the country of the Chaldeans and settled in Haran. Then after the death of his father, God had him move to this country where you now live.
B044C007V005	44	7	5	He gave him no property in it, not even a foot of land, yet he promised to give it to him and his descendants after him as a permanent possession, even though he had no child.
B044C007V006	44	7	6	This is what God promised: His descendants would be strangers in a foreign country, and its people would enslave them and oppress them for 400 years.
B044C007V007	44	7	7	‘But I will punish the nation they serve,’ said God, ‘and afterwards they will leave and worship me in this place.’
