B044C007V010	44	7	10	and rescued him from all his troubles. He allowed him to win favor and show wisdom before Pharaoh, king of Egypt, who appointed him ruler of Egypt and of his whole household.
B044C007V011	44	7	11	“But a famine spread throughout Egypt and Canaan, and with it great suffering, and our ancestors couldn't find any food.
B044C007V012	44	7	12	But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent our ancestors on their first visit.
B044C007V013	44	7	13	On their second visit Joseph made himself known to his brothers, and Joseph's family became known to Pharaoh.
B044C007V014	44	7	14	Then Joseph sent word and invited his father Jacob and all his relatives to come to him—seventy-five persons in all.
B044C007V015	44	7	15	So Jacob went down to Egypt. Then he and our ancestors died.
