B044C007V017	44	7	17	“Now as the time approached for the fulfillment of the promise that God had made to Abraham, the people multiplied and grew more numerous in Egypt,
B044C007V018	44	7	18	until another king, who had not known Joseph, became ruler of Egypt.
B044C007V019	44	7	19	By shrewdly scheming against our people, he oppressed our ancestors and forced them to expose their infants so that they wouldn't live.
B044C007V020	44	7	20	“At this time Moses was born. He was beautiful in the sight of God, and for three months he was cared for in his father's house.
B044C007V021	44	7	21	When he was placed outside, Pharaoh's daughter adopted him and brought him up as her own son.
B044C007V022	44	7	22	So Moses was educated in all the wisdom of the Egyptians and became a great man in speech and action.
B044C007V023	44	7	23	“When he was forty years old, his heart was moved to visit his brothers, the descendants of Israel.
B044C007V024	44	7	24	Because he saw one of them being mistreated, he defended and avenged the man who was being mistreated by striking down the Egyptian.
B044C007V025	44	7	25	He supposed that his brothers would understand that God was using him to rescue them, but they didn't understand.
