B044C007V027	44	7	27	But the man who was harming his neighbor pushed Moses away and said, ‘Who made you ruler and judge over us?
B044C007V028	44	7	28	You don't want to kill me like you killed the Egyptian yesterday, do you?’
B044C007V029	44	7	29	At this statement Moses fled and lived as a foreigner in the land of Midian. There he had two sons.
B044C007V030	44	7	30	“When forty years had passed, an angel appeared to him in the flames of a burning bush in the desert near Mount Sinai.
B044C007V031	44	7	31	When Moses saw it, he was amazed at the sight, and when he approached to look at it, the voice of the Lord said,
B044C007V032	44	7	32	‘I am the God of your ancestors—the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.’ Moses became terrified and didn't dare to look.
