B044C007V049	44	7	49	“‘Heaven is my throne,and the earth is my footstool.	What kind of house can you build for me,’ declares the Lord, “or what place is there in which I can rest?
B044C007V050	44	7	50	It was my hand that made all these things, wasn't it?’”
B044C007V051	44	7	51	“You stubborn people with uncircumcised hearts and ears! You are always opposing the Holy Spirit, just as your ancestors used to do.
B044C007V052	44	7	52	Which of the prophets did your ancestors fail to persecute? They killed those who predicted the coming of the Righteous One, and now you have become his betrayers and murderers.
B044C007V053	44	7	53	You received the law as ordained by angels, and yet you didn't obey it!”
B044C007V054	44	7	54	While they were listening to these things, they became more and more furious and began to grind their teeth at him.
B044C007V055	44	7	55	But Stephen, filled with the Holy Spirit, looked straight into heaven and saw the glory of God and Jesus standing at the right hand of God.
B044C007V056	44	7	56	He said, “Look! I see the heavens opened and the Son of Man standing at the right hand of God!”
B044C007V057	44	7	57	But they raised a loud shout, held their ears shut, and together they all rushed at him.
