B044C012V005	44	12	5	So Peter was being kept in prison, but earnest prayer to God for him was being offered by the church.
B044C012V006	44	12	6	That very night, before Herod was going to bring him out, Peter, bound with two chains, was sleeping between two soldiers, and guards in front of the door were watching the prisoners.
B044C012V007	44	12	7	Suddenly an angel of the Lord appeared and a light shone in the cell. He tapped Peter on his side, woke him up, and said, “Get up quickly!” His chains fell from his wrists.
