B044C012V010	44	12	10	They passed the first guard, then the second, and came to the iron gate that led into the city. It opened by itself for them, and they went outside and proceeded one block when the angel suddenly left him.
B044C012V011	44	12	11	Then Peter came to himself and said, “Now I'm sure that the Lord has sent his angel and rescued me from the hands of Herod and from everything the Jewish people were expecting!”
B044C012V012	44	12	12	When he realized what had happened, he went to the house of Mary, the mother of John who was also called Mark, where a large number of people had gathered and were praying.
B044C012V013	44	12	13	When he knocked at the outer gate, a servant-girl named Rhoda came to answer it.
B044C012V014	44	12	14	On recognizing Peter's voice, she was so overjoyed that she didn't open the gate but ran in and announced that Peter was standing at the gate.
B044C012V015	44	12	15	They said to her, “You're out of your mind!” But she kept insisting that it was so. Then they said, “It's his angel.”
B044C012V016	44	12	16	Meanwhile, Peter kept on knocking and knocking. When they opened the gate, they saw him and were amazed.
B044C012V017	44	12	17	He motioned to them with his hand to be quiet, and then he told them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. He added, “Tell this to James and the brothers.” Then he left and went somewhere else.
