B044C012V019	44	12	19	Herod searched for him but didn't find him, so he questioned the guards and ordered them to be executed. Then he left Judea, went down to Caesarea, and stayed there for a while.
B044C012V020	44	12	20	Now Herod had a violent quarrel with the people of Tyre and Sidon. So they came to him as a group. After they had won over Blastus, who took care of the king's bedroom, they asked for peace because their country depended on the king's country for food.
B044C012V021	44	12	21	Therefore, on a day that was set, Herod put on his royal robes, sat down on the royal seat, and made a speech to them.
B044C012V022	44	12	22	The people kept shouting, “This is the voice of a god, not of a man!”
B044C012V023	44	12	23	Immediately the angel of the Lord struck him down because he did not give glory to God, and he was eaten by worms and died.
B044C012V024	44	12	24	But the word of God continued to grow and spread.
B044C012V025	44	12	25	When Barnabas and Saul had fulfilled their mission, they returned to Jerusalem, bringing with them John who was also called Mark.
B044C013V001	44	13	1	Now Barnabas, Simeon called Niger, Lucius from Cyrene, Manaen who had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul were prophets and teachers in the church at Antioch.
B044C013V002	44	13	2	While they were worshiping the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit said, “Set Barnabas and Saul apart for me to do the work for which I called them.”
B044C013V003	44	13	3	Then they fasted and prayed, laid their hands on them, and let them go.
B044C013V004	44	13	4	Being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went to Seleucia and from there sailed to Cyprus.
