B044C023V012	44	23	12	In the morning, the Jews formed a conspiracy and took an oath not to eat or drink anything before they had killed Paul.
B044C023V013	44	23	13	More than forty men formed this conspiracy.
B044C023V014	44	23	14	They went to the high priests and elders and said, “We have taken a solemn oath not to taste any food before we have killed Paul.
B044C023V015	44	23	15	Now then, you and the Council must notify the tribune to bring him down to you on the pretext that you want to look into his case more carefully, but before he arrives we'll be ready to kill him.”
B044C023V016	44	23	16	But the son of Paul's sister heard about the ambush, so he came and got into the barracks and told Paul.
B044C023V017	44	23	17	Then Paul called one of the centurions and said, “Take this young man to the tribune, because he has something to tell him.”
B044C023V018	44	23	18	So he took him, brought him to the tribune, and said, “The prisoner Paul called me and asked me to bring this young man to you. He has something to tell you.”
B044C023V019	44	23	19	The tribune took him by the hand, stepped aside to be alone with him, and asked, “What have you got to tell me?”
B044C023V020	44	23	20	He answered, “The Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul down to the Council tomorrow as though they were going to examine his case more carefully.
B044C023V021	44	23	21	Don't believe them, because more than forty of them are planning to ambush him. They have taken an oath not to eat or drink before they have killed him. They are ready now, just waiting for your consent.”
B044C023V022	44	23	22	The tribune dismissed the young man and ordered him not to tell anyone that he had notified him.
B044C023V023	44	23	23	Then he summoned two of the centurions and said, “Get 200 soldiers ready to leave for Caesarea at nine o'clock tonight, along with seventy mounted soldiers and 200 soldiers with spears.
B044C023V024	44	23	24	Provide an animal for Paul to ride, and take him safely to Governor Felix.”
B044C023V025	44	23	25	He wrote a letter with this message:
B044C023V026	44	23	26	“From Claudius Lysias to Your Excellency, Governor Felix. Greetings.
B044C023V027	44	23	27	This man had been seized by the Jews and was about to be killed by them when I went with the guard and rescued him, having learned that he was a Roman citizen.
B044C023V028	44	23	28	I wanted to know the exact charge they were making against him, so I had him brought before their Council.
B044C023V029	44	23	29	I found that, although he was charged with questions about their law, there was no charge against him deserving death or imprisonment.
B044C023V030	44	23	30	Since a plot against the man has been reported to me, I am at once sending him to you and have also ordered his accusers to present their charges against him before you.”
B044C023V031	44	23	31	So the soldiers, in keeping with their orders, took Paul and brought him by night to Antipatris.
B044C023V032	44	23	32	The next day they let the horsemen ride on with him while they returned to their barracks.
B044C023V033	44	23	33	When these came to Caesarea, they delivered the letter to the governor and handed Paul over to him.
B044C023V034	44	23	34	After reading the letter, he asked which province he was from. On learning that he was from Cilicia,
B044C023V035	44	23	35	he said, “I will hear your case when your accusers arrive.” Then he ordered him to be kept in custody in Herod's palace.
B044C024V001	44	24	1	Five days later, the high priest Ananias arrived with some elders and Tertullius, an attorney, and they presented their case against Paul before the governor.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	When Paul had been summoned, Tertullius opened the prosecution by saying:“Your Excellency Felix, since we are enjoying lasting peace through you, and since reforms for this nation are being brought about through your foresight,
B044C024V003	44	24	3	we always and everywhere acknowledge it with profound gratitude.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	But so as not to detain you any further, I beg you to hear us briefly with your customary graciousness.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	For we have found this man a perfect pest and an agitator among all Jews throughout the world. He is a ringleader in the sect of the Nazarenes
B044C024V006	44	24	6	and even tried to profane the temple, but we arrested him.
B044C024V008	44	24	8	By examining him for yourself, you will be able to find out from him everything of which we accuse him.”
B044C024V009	44	24	9	The Jews supported his accusations by asserting that these things were true.
B044C024V010	44	24	10	When the governor motioned for Paul to speak, he replied: “Since I know that you have been a judge over this nation for many years, I am pleased to present my defense.
B044C024V011	44	24	11	You can verify for yourself that I went up to worship in Jerusalem no more than twelve days ago.
B044C024V012	44	24	12	They never found me debating with anyone in the temple or stirring up a crowd in the synagogues or throughout the city,
B044C024V013	44	24	13	and they cannot prove to you the charges they are now bringing against me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	However, I admit to you that in accordance with the Way, which they call a heresy, I worship the God of our ancestors and believe in everything written in the Law and the Prophets.
B044C024V015	44	24	15	I have the same hope in God that they themselves cherish—that there is to be a resurrection of the righteous and the wicked.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	Therefore, I always do my best to have a clear conscience in the sight of God and people.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	After many years I have come back to my people to bring gifts for the poor and to offer sacrifices.
B044C024V018	44	24	18	They found me in the temple doing these things just as I had completed the purification ceremony. No crowd or noisy mob was present.
B044C024V019	44	24	19	But some Jews from Asia were there, and they should be here before you to accuse me if they have anything against me.
B044C024V020	44	24	20	Otherwise, these men themselves should tell what wrong they found when I stood before the Council—
B044C024V021	44	24	21	unless it is for the one thing I shouted as I stood among them: ‘It is for the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial before you today.’”
B044C024V022	44	24	22	Felix was rather well informed about the Way, and so he adjourned the trial with the comment, “When Tribune Lysias arrives, I will decide your case.”
B044C024V023	44	24	23	He ordered the centurion to guard Paul but to let him have some freedom and not to keep any of his friends from caring for his needs.
B044C024V024	44	24	24	Some days later, Felix arrived with his wife Drusilla, who was Jewish. He sent for Paul and listened to him talk about faith in Christ Jesus.
B044C024V025	44	24	25	As Paul talked about righteousness, self-control, and the coming judgment, Felix became afraid and said, “For the present you may go. When I get a chance, I will send for you again.”
B044C024V026	44	24	26	At the same time he was hoping to get money from Paul, and so he would send for him frequently to talk with him.
B044C024V027	44	24	27	After two years had passed, Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus. Since Felix wanted to do the Jews a favor, he left Paul in prison.
B044C025V001	44	25	1	Three days after Festus had arrived in the province, he went up from Caesarea to Jerusalem.
B044C025V002	44	25	2	The high priests and Jewish leaders informed him of their charges against Paul, urging
B044C025V003	44	25	3	and begging him as a favor to have Paul brought to Jerusalem. They were laying an ambush to kill him on the way.
B044C025V004	44	25	4	Festus replied that Paul was being kept in custody at Caesarea and that he himself would be going there soon.
B044C025V005	44	25	5	“Therefore,” he said, “have your authorities come down with me and present their charges against him, if there is anything wrong with the man.”
B044C025V006	44	25	6	Festus stayed with them no more than eight or ten days and then went down to Caesarea. The next day he sat on the judge's seat and ordered Paul brought in.
B044C025V007	44	25	7	When he arrived, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem surrounded him and began bringing a number of serious charges against him that they couldn't prove.
B044C025V008	44	25	8	Paul said in his defense, “I have in no way sinned against the law of the Jews or the temple or the emperor.”
B044C025V009	44	25	9	Then Festus, wanting to do the Jews a favor, asked Paul, “Are you willing to go up to Jerusalem to be tried there before me on these charges?”
B044C025V010	44	25	10	But Paul said, “I am standing before the emperor's judgment seat where I ought to be tried. I haven't done anything wrong to the Jews, as you know very well.
B044C025V011	44	25	11	If I am guilty and have done something that deserves death, I don't refuse to die. But if there is nothing to their charges against me, no one can hand me over to them as a favor. I appeal to the emperor!”
B044C025V012	44	25	12	Festus talked it over with the council and then answered, “To the emperor you have appealed; to the emperor you will go!”
B044C025V013	44	25	13	After several days had passed, King Agrippa and Bernice came to Caesarea to welcome Festus.
B044C025V014	44	25	14	Since they were staying there for several days, Festus laid Paul's case before the king. He said, “There is a man here who was left in prison by Felix.
B044C025V015	44	25	15	When I went to Jerusalem, the high priests and the Jewish elders informed me about him and asked me to condemn him.
B044C025V016	44	25	16	I answered them that it was not the Roman custom to hand over a man for punishment until the accused met his accusers face to face and had an opportunity to defend himself against the charge.
B044C025V017	44	25	17	“So they came here with me, and the next day without any delay I sat down in the judge's seat and ordered the man to be brought in.
B044C025V018	44	25	18	When his accusers stood up, they didn't accuse him of any of the crimes I was expecting.
B044C025V019	44	25	19	Instead, they had several arguments with him about their own religion and about a certain Jesus who had died but whom Paul kept claiming was alive.
B044C025V020	44	25	20	I was puzzled how I should investigate such matters and asked if he would like to go to Jerusalem and be tried there in regard to these things.
B044C025V021	44	25	21	But Paul appealed his case and asked to be held in prison until the decision of his Majesty. So I ordered him to be held in custody until I could send him to the emperor.”
B044C025V022	44	25	22	Agrippa told Festus, “I would like to hear the man.”“Tomorrow,” he said, “you will hear him.”
B044C025V023	44	25	23	The next day Agrippa and Bernice arrived with much fanfare and went into the auditorium along with the tribunes and the leading men of the city. At the command of Festus, Paul was brought in.
B044C025V024	44	25	24	Then Festus said, “King Agrippa and all you men who are present with us! You see this man about whom the whole Jewish nation petitioned me, both in Jerusalem and here, shouting that he ought not to live any longer.
B044C025V025	44	25	25	I find that he has not done anything deserving of death. But since he has appealed to his Majesty, I have decided to send him.
B044C025V026	44	25	26	I have nothing reliable to write our Sovereign about him, so I have brought him to all of you, and especially to you, King Agrippa, so that I will have something to write after he is cross-examined.
B044C025V027	44	25	27	For it seems to me absurd to send a prisoner without specifying the charges against him.”
B044C026V001	44	26	1	Then Agrippa said to Paul, “You have permission to speak for yourself.” So Paul stretched out his hand and began his defense.
B044C026V002	44	26	2	“I consider myself fortunate that it is before you, King Agrippa, that I can defend myself today against all the accusations of the Jews,
B044C026V003	44	26	3	since you are especially familiar with all the Jewish customs and controversies. I beg you, therefore, to listen patiently to me.
B044C026V004	44	26	4	All the Jews know how I lived from the earliest days of my youth with my own people and in Jerusalem.
B044C026V005	44	26	5	They have known for a long time, if they would but testify to it, that I lived as a Pharisee by the standard of the strictest sect of our religion.
B044C026V006	44	26	6	“And now it is for the hope of the promise made by God to our ancestors that I stand here on trial.
B044C026V007	44	26	7	Our twelve tribes, worshiping day and night with intense devotion, hope to attain it. It is for this hope, O King, that I am accused by the Jews.
B044C026V008	44	26	8	Why is it thought incredible by all of you that God should raise the dead?
B044C026V009	44	26	9	Indeed, I myself thought it my duty to take extreme measures against the name of Jesus from Nazareth.
B044C026V010	44	26	10	That is what I did in Jerusalem. I received authority from the high priests and locked many of the saints in prison. And when they were put to death, I cast my vote against them.
B044C026V011	44	26	11	I would even punish them frequently in every synagogue and try to make them blaspheme. Raging furiously against them, I would hunt them down even to distant cities.
B044C026V012	44	26	12	“That is how I happened to be traveling to Damascus with authority based on a commission from the high priests.
B044C026V013	44	26	13	On the road at noon, O King, I saw from heaven a light that was brighter than the sun flash around me and those who were traveling with me.
B044C026V014	44	26	14	All of us fell to the ground, and I heard a voice asking me in the Hebrew language,
B044C026V015	44	26	15	I asked, ‘Who are you, Lord?’ The Lord answered,
B044C026V016	44	26	16	
        
B044C026V017	44	26	17	
        
B044C026V018	44	26	18	
        
B044C026V019	44	26	19	“And so, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision.
B044C026V020	44	26	20	Instead, I first told the people in Damascus and Jerusalem, then the whole countryside of Judea, and then the Gentiles to repent, turn to God, and practice works that are consistent with such repentance.
B044C026V021	44	26	21	For this reason the Jews grabbed me in the temple and kept trying to kill me.
B044C026V022	44	26	22	I have had help from God to this day, and so I stand here to testify to high and low alike, stating only what the prophets and Moses said would happen—
B044C026V023	44	26	23	that the Christ would suffer and be the first to rise from the dead and would announce light to our people and the Gentiles.”
B044C026V024	44	26	24	As he continued to make his defense, Festus shouted, “You're out of your mind, Paul! Too much education is driving you crazy!”
B044C026V025	44	26	25	But Paul said, “I'm not out of my mind, Your Excellency Festus. I'm uttering words of sober truth.
B044C026V026	44	26	26	Indeed, the king knows about these things, and I can speak to him freely. For I am certain that none of these things has escaped his notice, since this wasn't done in a corner.
B044C026V027	44	26	27	King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know you believe them!”
B044C026V028	44	26	28	Agrippa said to Paul, “Can you so quickly persuade me to become a Christian?”
B044C026V029	44	26	29	Paul replied, “Whether quickly or not, I wish to God that not only you but everyone listening to me today would become what I am—except for these chains!”
B044C026V030	44	26	30	Then the king, the governor, Bernice, and those who were sitting with him got up.
B044C026V031	44	26	31	As they were leaving, they began to say to each other, “This man isn't doing anything to deserve death or imprisonment.”
B044C026V032	44	26	32	Agrippa told Festus, “This man could have been set free if he hadn't appealed to the emperor.”
B044C027V001	44	27	1	When it was decided that we should sail to Italy, they transferred Paul and some other prisoners to a centurion named Julius, who belonged to the emperor's division.
B044C027V002	44	27	2	Boarding a ship from Adramyttium that was about to sail to the ports on the coast of Asia, we put out to sea. Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica, went with us.
B044C027V003	44	27	3	The next day we arrived at Sidon, and Julius treated Paul kindly and allowed him to visit his friends and receive any care he needed.
B044C027V004	44	27	4	After putting out from there, we sailed on the sheltered side of Cyprus because the winds were against us.
B044C027V005	44	27	5	We sailed along the sea off Cilicia and Pamphylia and reached Myra in Lycia.
B044C027V006	44	27	6	There the centurion found an Alexandrian ship bound for Italy and put us on it.
B044C027V007	44	27	7	We sailed slowly for a number of days and with difficulty arrived off Cnidus. Then, because the wind was against us, we sailed on the sheltered side of Crete off Cape Salome.
B044C027V008	44	27	8	Sailing past it with difficulty, we came to a place called Fair Havens, near the town of Lasea.
B044C027V009	44	27	9	Much time had been lost, and because navigation had become dangerous and the day of fasting had already past, Paul began to warn them
B044C027V010	44	27	10	by saying, “Men, I see that in this voyage there will be hardship and a heavy loss not only of the cargo and ship but also of our lives.”
B044C027V011	44	27	11	But the centurion was persuaded by the pilot and the owner of the ship and not by what Paul said.
B044C027V012	44	27	12	Since the harbor was not a good place to spend the winter, most of the men favored putting out to sea from there on the chance that somehow they could reach Phoenix and spend the winter there. It is a harbor of Crete facing southwest and northwest.
B044C027V013	44	27	13	When a gentle breeze began to blow from the south, they thought they could achieve their purpose. So they raised the anchor and began to sail close to the shore of Crete.
B044C027V014	44	27	14	But it was not long before a violent wind (called a northeaster) swept down from the island.
B044C027V015	44	27	15	The ship was caught so that it couldn't face the wind, and we gave up and were swept along.
B044C027V016	44	27	16	As we drifted to the sheltered side of a small island called Cauda, we barely managed to secure the ship's lifeboat.
B044C027V017	44	27	17	They pulled it up on deck and used ropes to brace the ship. Fearing that they would hit the large sandbank near Lybia, they lowered the sail and drifted along.
B044C027V018	44	27	18	The next day, because we were being tossed so violently by the storm, they began to throw the cargo overboard.
B044C027V019	44	27	19	On the third day they threw the ship's equipment overboard with their own hands.
B044C027V020	44	27	20	For a number of days neither the sun nor the stars were to be seen, and the storm continued to rage until at last all hope of our being saved vanished.
B044C027V021	44	27	21	After they had gone a long time without food, Paul stood among them and said, “Men, you should have listened to me and not have sailed from Crete. You would have avoided this hardship and damage.
B044C027V022	44	27	22	But now I urge you to have courage because there will be no loss of life among you, but only of the ship.
B044C027V023	44	27	23	For just last night an angel of God, to whom I belong and whom I serve, stood by me
B044C027V024	44	27	24	and said, ‘Stop being afraid, Paul! You must stand before the emperor. Indeed, God has given you all who are sailing with you.’
B044C027V025	44	27	25	So have courage, men, for I trust God that it will turn out just as he told me.
B044C027V026	44	27	26	However, we will have to run aground on some island.”
B044C027V027	44	27	27	It was the fourteenth night, and we were drifting through the Adriatic Sea when about midnight the sailors suspected that land was near.
B044C027V028	44	27	28	On taking soundings, they found a depth of twenty fathoms. A little later they took soundings again and found it was fifteen fathoms.
B044C027V029	44	27	29	Fearing that we might run aground on the rocks, they dropped four anchors from the stern and began praying for daylight to come.
B044C027V030	44	27	30	Now the sailors were trying to escape from the ship. They had lowered the lifeboat into the sea and pretended that they were going to lay out the anchors from the bow.
B044C027V031	44	27	31	Paul told the centurion and the soldiers, “Unless these men remain in the ship, you cannot be saved.”
B044C027V032	44	27	32	Then the soldiers cut the ropes that held the lifeboat and set it adrift.
B044C027V033	44	27	33	Right up to daybreak Paul kept urging all of them to eat something, saying, “Today is the fourteenth day that you have been waiting and going without food, having eaten nothing.
B044C027V034	44	27	34	So I urge you to eat something, for it will help you survive, since none of you will lose a hair from his head.”
B044C027V035	44	27	35	After he said this, he took some bread, thanked God in front of everyone, broke it, and began to eat.
B044C027V036	44	27	36	All of them were encouraged and had something to eat.
B044C027V037	44	27	37	There were 276 of us on the ship.
B044C027V038	44	27	38	After they had eaten all they wanted, they began to lighten the ship by dumping the wheat into the sea.
B044C027V039	44	27	39	When day came, they couldn't recognize the land, but they could see a bay with a beach on which they planned to run the ship ashore if possible.
B044C027V040	44	27	40	So they cut the anchors free and left them in the sea. At the same time they untied the ropes that held the steering oars, raised the foresail to the wind, and headed for the beach.
B044C027V041	44	27	41	But they struck a sandbar and ran the ship aground. The bow stuck and couldn't be moved, while the stern was broken to pieces by the force of the waves.
B044C027V042	44	27	42	The soldiers’ plan was to kill the prisoners to keep them from swimming ashore and escaping,
B044C027V043	44	27	43	but the centurion wanted to save Paul and prevented them from carrying out their plan. He ordered those who could swim to jump overboard first and get to land.
B044C027V044	44	27	44	The rest were to follow, some on planks and others on various pieces of the ship. In this way all of them got to shore safely.
B044C028V001	44	28	1	When we were safely on shore, we learned that the island was called Malta.
B044C028V002	44	28	2	The people who lived there were unusually kind to us. It had started to rain and was cold, and so they made a fire and welcomed all of us around it.
B044C028V003	44	28	3	Paul gathered a bundle of sticks and put it on the fire. A poisonous snake was forced out by the heat and attached itself to Paul's hand.
B044C028V004	44	28	4	When the people who lived there saw the snake hanging from his hand, they said to one another, “This man must be a murderer! He may have escaped from the sea, but Justice won't let him live.”
B044C028V005	44	28	5	But he shook the snake into the fire and wasn't harmed.
B044C028V006	44	28	6	They were expecting him to swell up or suddenly drop dead, but after waiting a long time and seeing nothing unusual happen to him, they changed their minds and said he was a god.
B044C028V007	44	28	7	The governor of the island, whose name was Publius, owned estates in that part of the island, and he welcomed us and entertained us with great hospitality for three days.
B044C028V008	44	28	8	The father of Publius happened to be sick in bed with fever and dysentery. Paul went to him, prayed, and healed him by placing his hands on him.
B044C028V009	44	28	9	After that had happened, the rest of the sick people on the island went to him and were healed.
B044C028V010	44	28	10	They honored us in many ways, and when we were going to sail, they supplied us with everything we needed.
B044C028V011	44	28	11	Three months later, we sailed on an Alexandrian ship that had spent the winter at the island. It had the Twin Brothers as its figurehead.
B044C028V012	44	28	12	We stopped at Syracuse and stayed there for three days.
B044C028V013	44	28	13	Then we weighed anchor and came to Rhegium. A day later a south wind began to blow, and on the second day we came to Puteoli.
B044C028V014	44	28	14	There we found some brothers and were invited to stay with them for seven days. And so we came to Rome.
B044C028V015	44	28	15	The brothers there heard about us and came as far as the Forum of Appius and the Three Taverns to meet us. When Paul saw them, he thanked God and felt encouraged.
B044C028V016	44	28	16	When we came into Rome, Paul was allowed to live by himself with the soldier who was guarding him.
B044C028V017	44	28	17	Three days later, he called the leaders of the Jews together. When they assembled, he said to them, “Brothers, although I haven't done anything against our people or the customs of our ancestors, I was arrested in Jerusalem and handed over to the Romans.
B044C028V018	44	28	18	They examined me and wanted to let me go because there was no reason for the death penalty in my case.
B044C028V019	44	28	19	But the Jews objected and forced me to appeal to the emperor, even though I have no countercharge to bring against my own people.
B044C028V020	44	28	20	That's why I asked to see you and speak with you, since it is for the hope of Israel that I'm wearing this chain.”
B044C028V021	44	28	21	They told him, “We haven't received any letters from Judea about you, and none of the brothers coming here has reported or mentioned anything bad about you.
B044C028V022	44	28	22	However, we would like to hear from you what you think, because everywhere people are talking against this sect.”
B044C028V023	44	28	23	So they set a day to meet with him and came in large numbers to see him where he was staying. From morning until evening he continued to explain the kingdom of God to them, trying to convince them about Jesus from the law of Moses and the Prophets.
B044C028V024	44	28	24	Some of them were convinced by what he said, but others wouldn't believe.
B044C028V025	44	28	25	They disagreed with one another as they were leaving, and Paul added a statement: “How well did the Holy Spirit speak to your ancestors through the prophet Isaiah!
B044C028V026	44	28	26	He said,	‘Go to this people and say,“You will listen and listenbut never understand,and you will look and lookbut never see!
B044C028V027	44	28	27	For this people's heart has become dull,and their ears are hard of hearing,	and they have shut their eyesso that they may never see with their eyes,	and listen with their ears,and understand with their heart	and turn and let me heal them.”’
B044C028V028	44	28	28	“You must understand that this salvation of God has been sent to the Gentiles, and they will listen.”
B044C028V030	44	28	30	For two whole years he lived in his own rented place and welcomed everyone who came to him.
B044C028V031	44	28	31	He continued to preach the kingdom of God and to teach about the Lord Jesus Christ with perfect boldness and freedom.
B045C001V001	45	1	1	From Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called to be an apostle and set apart for the gospel of God,
B045C001V002	45	1	2	which he promised beforehand through his prophets in the Holy Scriptures
B045C001V003	45	1	3	regarding his Son, who according to the flesh was a descendant of David,
B045C001V004	45	1	4	and who according to the spirit of holiness was declared to be the Son of God with power by the resurrection from the dead—Jesus Christ our Lord.
B045C001V005	45	1	5	Through him we received grace and a commission as an apostle to bring about the obedience of faith among all the Gentiles for the sake of his name.
B045C001V006	45	1	6	You, too, are among those who have been called to belong to Jesus Christ.
B045C001V007	45	1	7	To all in Rome who are loved by God and called to be holy. May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B045C001V008	45	1	8	First of all, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because the news about your faith is being reported throughout the world.
B045C001V009	45	1	9	For God, whom I serve in my spirit by preaching the gospel of his Son, is my witness how constantly I mention you
B045C001V010	45	1	10	in my prayers at all times, asking that somehow by God's will I may at last succeed in coming to you.
B045C001V011	45	1	11	For I am longing to see you so that I may impart to you some spiritual gift to make you strong,
B045C001V012	45	1	12	that is, that we may be mutually encouraged by each other's faith, both yours and mine.
B045C001V013	45	1	13	I do not want you to be unaware, brothers, that I often planned to come to you (but have been prevented from doing so until now), so that I might reap a harvest among you, just as I have among the rest of the Gentiles.
B045C001V014	45	1	14	Both to Greeks and to barbarians, both to wise and to foolish people, I am a debtor.
B045C001V015	45	1	15	That is why I am so eager to proclaim the gospel to you who live in Rome, too.
B045C001V016	45	1	16	For I am not ashamed of the gospel, because it is God's power for the salvation of everyone who believes, of the Jew first and of the Greek as well.
B045C001V017	45	1	17	For in it God's righteousness is being revealed from faith to faith, as it is written, “The righteous will live by faith.”
B045C001V018	45	1	18	For God's wrath is being revealed from heaven against all the ungodliness and wickedness of those who in their wickedness suppress the truth.
B045C001V019	45	1	19	For what can be known about God is plain to them, because God himself has made it plain to them.
B045C001V020	45	1	20	For since the creation of the world his invisible attributes—his eternal power and divine nature—have been understood and observed by what he made, so that people are without excuse.
B045C001V021	45	1	21	For although they knew God, they neither glorified him as God nor gave thanks to him. Instead, their thoughts turned to worthless things, and their ignorant hearts were darkened.
B045C001V022	45	1	22	Though claiming to be wise, they became fools
B045C001V023	45	1	23	and exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images that looked like mortal human beings, birds, four-footed animals, and reptiles.
B045C001V024	45	1	24	For this reason, God gave them over to impurity to follow the lusts of their hearts and to dishonor their bodies with one another.
B045C001V025	45	1	25	They exchanged God's truth for a lie and worshipped and served the creation rather than the Creator, who is blessed forever. Amen.
B045C001V026	45	1	26	For this reason, God gave them over to degrading passions. Even their females exchanged their natural sexual function for one that is unnatural.
B045C001V027	45	1	27	In the same way, their males also abandoned the natural sexual function of females and burned with lust for one another. Males committed indecent acts with males, and received in themselves the appropriate penalty for their perversion.
B045C001V028	45	1	28	Furthermore, because they did not think it worthwhile to retain the full knowledge of God, God gave them over to degraded minds to perform acts that should not be done.
B045C001V029	45	1	29	They have become filled with every kind of wickedness, evil, greed, and depravity. They are full of envy, murder, quarreling, deceit, and viciousness. They are gossips,
B045C001V030	45	1	30	slanderers, God-haters, haughty, arrogant, boastful, inventors of evil, disobedient to their parents,
B045C001V031	45	1	31	foolish, faithless, heartless, ruthless.
B045C001V032	45	1	32	Although they know God's just requirement—that those who practice such things deserve to die—they not only do these things but even applaud others who practice them.
B045C002V001	45	2	1	Therefore, you have no excuse—every one of you who judges. For when you pass judgment on another person, you condemn yourself, since you, the judge, practice the very same things.
B045C002V002	45	2	2	Now we know that God's judgment against those who practice such is based on truth.
B045C002V003	45	2	3	So when you, a mere man, pass judgment on those who practice these things and then do them yourself, do you think you will escape God's judgment?
B045C002V004	45	2	4	Or do you think so little of the riches of his kindness, forbearance, and patience, not realizing that it is God's kindness that is leading you to repentance?
B045C002V005	45	2	5	But because of your stubborn and unrepentant heart you are storing up wrath for yourself on the day of wrath, when God's righteous judgment will be revealed.
B045C002V006	45	2	6	For he will repay everyone according to what that person has done:
B045C002V007	45	2	7	eternal life to those who strive for glory, honor, and immortality by patiently doing good;
B045C002V008	45	2	8	but wrath and fury for those who in their selfish pride refuse to believe the truth and practice wickedness instead.
B045C002V009	45	2	9	There will be suffering and anguish for every human being who practices doing evil, for Jews first and for Greeks as well.
B045C002V010	45	2	10	But there will be glory, honor, and peace for everyone who practices doing good, for Jews first and for Greeks as well.
B045C002V011	45	2	11	For God does not show partiality.
B045C002V012	45	2	12	For all who have sinned apart from the law will also perish apart from the law, and all who have sinned under the law will be judged by the law.
B045C002V013	45	2	13	For it is not merely those who hear the law who are righteous in God's sight. No, it is those who do the law, who will be justified.
B045C002V014	45	2	14	For whenever Gentiles, who do not possess the law, do instinctively what the law requires, they are a law to themselves, even though they do not have the law.
B045C002V015	45	2	15	They show that what the law requires is written in their hearts, a fact to which their own consciences testify, and their thoughts will either accuse or excuse them
B045C002V016	45	2	16	on that day when God, through Jesus Christ, will judge people's secrets according to my gospel.
B045C002V017	45	2	17	Now if you call yourself a Jew, and rely on the law, and boast about God,
B045C002V018	45	2	18	and know his will, and approve of what is best because you have been instructed in the law;
B045C002V019	45	2	19	and if you are convinced that you are a guide for the blind, a light to those in darkness,
B045C002V020	45	2	20	an instructor of ignorant people, and a teacher of infants because you have the full content of knowledge and truth in the law—
B045C002V021	45	2	21	as you teach others, do you fail to teach yourself? As you preach against stealing, do you steal?
B045C002V022	45	2	22	As you forbid adultery, do you commit adultery? As you abhor idols, do you rob temples?
B045C002V023	45	2	23	As you boast about the law, do you dishonor God by breaking the law?
B045C002V024	45	2	24	As it is written, “God's name is being blasphemed among the Gentiles because of you.”
B045C002V025	45	2	25	For circumcision is valuable if you observe the law, but if you break the law, your circumcision has become uncircumcision.
B045C002V026	45	2	26	So if a man who is uncircumcised keeps the requirements of the law, his uncircumcision will be regarded as circumcision, won't it?
B045C002V027	45	2	27	The man who is uncircumcised physically but who keeps the law will condemn you who break the law, even though you have the written law and circumcision.
B045C002V028	45	2	28	For a person is not a Jew because of his appearance, nor is circumcision something external and physical.
B045C002V029	45	2	29	No, a person is a Jew inwardly, and circumcision is a matter of the heart, by the Spirit, not by a written law. That person's praise will come from God, not from people.
B045C003V001	45	3	1	What advantage, then, does the Jew have, or what value is there in circumcision?
B045C003V002	45	3	2	There are all kinds of advantages! First of all, the Jews have been entrusted with the utterances of God.
B045C003V003	45	3	3	What if some of them were unfaithful? Their unfaithfulness cannot cancel God's faithfulness, can it?
B045C003V004	45	3	4	Of course not! God is true, even if everyone else is a liar. As it is written,	“You are right when you speak,and win your case when you go into court.”
B045C003V005	45	3	5	But if our unrighteousness serves to confirm God's righteousness, what can we say? God is not unrighteous when he vents his wrath on us, is he? (I am talking in human terms.)
B045C003V006	45	3	6	Of course not! Otherwise, how could God judge the world?
B045C003V007	45	3	7	For if through my falsehood God's truthfulness increases to his glory, why am I still being condemned as a sinner?
B045C003V008	45	3	8	Or can we say—as some people slander us by claiming that we say—“Let us do evil that good may result”? Their condemnation is deserved!
B045C003V009	45	3	9	What, then, does this mean? Are we Jews any better off? Not at all! For we have already accused everyone, both Jews and Greeks, of being under the power of sin.
B045C003V010	45	3	10	As it is written,	“Not even one person is righteous.
B045C003V011	45	3	11	No one understands.No one searches for God.
B045C003V012	45	3	12	All have turned away.Together they have become worthless.No one shows kindness, not even one person!
B045C003V013	45	3	13	Their throats are open graves.With their tongues they practice deception.The venom of poisonous snakes is under their lips.
B045C003V014	45	3	14	Their mouths are full of cursing and bitterness.
B045C003V015	45	3	15	Their feet are swift to shed blood.
B045C003V016	45	3	16	Ruin and misery mark their ways.
B045C003V017	45	3	17	They have not learned the path to peace.
B045C003V018	45	3	18	There is no fear of God before their eyes.”
B045C003V019	45	3	19	Now we know that whatever the law says applies to those who are under the law, so that every mouth may be silenced and the whole world held accountable to God.
B045C003V020	45	3	20	Therefore, no human being will be justified in God's sight by means of the works prescribed by the law, for through the law comes the full knowledge of sin.
B045C003V021	45	3	21	But now, apart from the law, God's righteousness is revealed and is attested by the Law and the Prophets—
B045C003V022	45	3	22	God's righteousness through the faithfulness of Jesus Christ for all who believe. For there is no distinction,
B045C003V023	45	3	23	since all have sinned and continue to fall short of God's glory.
B045C003V024	45	3	24	By his grace they are justified freely through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus,
B045C003V025	45	3	25	whom God offered as a place where atonement by Christ's blood could occur through faith. He did this to demonstrate his righteousness, because he had waited patiently to deal with sins committed in the past.
B045C003V026	45	3	26	He wanted to demonstrate at the present time that he himself is righteous and that he justifies the person who has the faithfulness of Jesus.
B045C003V027	45	3	27	What, then, is there to boast about? That has been eliminated. On what principle? On that of works? No, but on the principle of faith.
B045C003V028	45	3	28	For we maintain that a person is justified by faith apart from the works prescribed by the law.
B045C003V029	45	3	29	Is God the God of the Jews only? Is he not the God of the Gentiles, too? Yes, of the Gentiles, too,
B045C003V030	45	3	30	since there is only one God who will justify the circumcised on the basis of faith and the uncircumcised by that same faith.
B045C003V031	45	3	31	Do we, then, abolish the law by this faith? Of course not! Instead, we uphold the law.
B045C004V001	45	4	1	What, then, are we to say about Abraham, our ancestor according to the flesh?
B045C004V002	45	4	2	For if Abraham was justified by works, he would have had something to boast about—though not before God.
B045C004V003	45	4	3	For what does the Scripture say? “Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.”
B045C004V004	45	4	4	Now to someone who works, wages are not considered a gift but an obligation.
B045C004V005	45	4	5	However, to someone who does not work, but simply believes in the one who justifies the ungodly, his faith is credited as righteousness.
B045C004V006	45	4	6	Likewise, David also speaks of the blessedness of the person whom God regards as righteous apart from works:
B045C004V007	45	4	7	“How blessed are those whose iniquities are forgivenand whose sins are covered!
B045C004V008	45	4	8	How blessed is the person whose sinsthe Lord will never charge against him!”
B045C004V009	45	4	9	Now does this blessedness come to the circumcised alone, or also to the uncircumcised? For we say, “Abraham's faith was credited to him as righteousness.”
B045C004V010	45	4	10	Under what circumstances was it credited? Was he circumcised or uncircumcised? He had not been circumcised, but was uncircumcised.
B045C004V011	45	4	11	Afterward he received the mark of circumcision as a seal of the righteousness that he had by faith while he was still uncircumcised. Therefore, he is the ancestor of all who believe while uncircumcised, in order that righteousness may be credited to them.
B045C004V012	45	4	12	He is also the ancestor of the circumcised—those who are not only circumcised, but who also walk in the footsteps of the faith that our father Abraham had before he was circumcised.
B045C004V013	45	4	13	For the promise that he would inherit the world did not come to Abraham or to his descendants through the law, but through the righteousness produced by faith.
B045C004V014	45	4	14	For if those who were given the law are the heirs, then faith is useless and the promise is worthless,
B045C004V015	45	4	15	for the law brings about wrath. Now where there is no law, neither can there be any violation of it.
B045C004V016	45	4	16	Therefore, the promise is based on faith, so that it may be a matter of grace and may be guaranteed for all his descendants—not only for those who were given the law, but also for those who share Abraham's faith, who is the father of us all.
B045C004V017	45	4	17	As it is written, “I have made you the father of many nations.” Abraham acted in faith when he stood in God's presence, who gives life to the dead and calls into existence things that don't even exist.
B045C004V018	45	4	18	Hoping in spite of hopeless circumstances, he believed that he would become “the father of many nations,” just as he had been told: “This is how many descendants you will have.”
B045C004V019	45	4	19	He did not weaken in faith when he thought about his own body (which was already as good as dead now that he was about a hundred years old) or about Sarah's inability to have children,
B045C004V020	45	4	20	nor did he doubt God's promise out of a lack of faith. Instead, he became strong in faith and gave glory to God,
B045C004V021	45	4	21	being absolutely convinced that God would do what he had promised.
B045C004V022	45	4	22	This is why “it was credited to him as righteousness.”
B045C004V023	45	4	23	Now the words “it was credited to him” were written not only for him
B045C004V024	45	4	24	but also for us. Our faith will be regarded in the same way, if we believe in the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead.
B045C004V025	45	4	25	He was handed over to death because of our sins and was raised to life because of our justification.
B045C005V001	45	5	1	Therefore, since we have been justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C005V002	45	5	2	Through him we have also obtained access by faith into this grace in which we stand, and we boast in our hope of sharing God's glory.
B045C005V003	45	5	3	Not only that, but we also boast in our sufferings, knowing that suffering produces endurance,
B045C005V004	45	5	4	endurance produces character, and character produces hope.
B045C005V005	45	5	5	Now this hope does not disappoint us, because God's love has been poured out into our hearts by the Holy Spirit, who has been given to us.
B045C005V006	45	5	6	For at just the right time, while we were still powerless, Christ died for the ungodly.
B045C005V007	45	5	7	For it is rare for anyone to die for a righteous person, though somebody might be brave enough to die for a good person.
B045C005V008	45	5	8	But God demonstrates his love for us by the fact that Christ died for us while we were still sinners.
B045C005V009	45	5	9	Now that we have been justified by his blood, how much more will we be saved from wrath through him!
B045C005V010	45	5	10	For if, while we were enemies, we were reconciled to God through the death of his Son, how much more, having been reconciled, will we be saved by his life!
B045C005V011	45	5	11	Not only that, but we also continue to boast in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have now received our reconciliation.
B045C005V012	45	5	12	Therefore, just as sin entered the world through one man, and death through sin, so death spread to everyone, because all have sinned.
B045C005V013	45	5	13	Certainly sin was in the world before the law was given, but no record of sin is kept when there is no law.
B045C005V014	45	5	14	Nevertheless, death ruled from the time of Adam to Moses, even over those who did not sin in the same way Adam did when he disobeyed. He is a type of the one who would come.
B045C005V015	45	5	15	But God's free gift is not like Adam's offense. For if many people died as the result of one man's offense, how much more have God's grace and the free gift given through the kindness of one man, Jesus Christ, been showered on many people!
B045C005V016	45	5	16	Nor can the free gift be compared to what came through the man who sinned. For the sentence that followed one man's offense brought condemnation, but the free gift brought justification, even after many offenses.
B045C005V017	45	5	17	For if, through one man, death ruled because of that man's offense, how much more will those who receive such overflowing grace and the gift of righteousness rule in life because of one man, Jesus Christ!
B045C005V018	45	5	18	Consequently, just as one offense resulted in condemnation for everyone, so one act of righteousness results in justification and life for everyone.
B045C005V019	45	5	19	For just as through one man's disobedience many people were made sinners, so also through one man's obedience many people will be made righteous.
B045C005V020	45	5	20	Now the law crept in so that the offense would increase. But where sin increased, grace increased even more,
B045C005V021	45	5	21	so that, just as sin ruled by bringing death, so also grace might rule by bringing justification that results in eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
B045C006V001	45	6	1	What should we say, then? Should we go on sinning so that grace may increase?
B045C006V002	45	6	2	Of course not! How can we who died as far as sin is concerned go on living in it?
B045C006V003	45	6	3	Or don't you know that all of us who were baptized into union with Christ Jesus were baptized into his death?
B045C006V004	45	6	4	Therefore, through baptism we were buried with him into his death so that, just as Christ was raised from the dead by the Father's glory, we too may live an entirely new life.
B045C006V005	45	6	5	For if we have become united with him in a death like his, we will certainly also be united with him in a resurrection like his.
B045C006V006	45	6	6	We know that our old selves were crucified with him so that our sinful bodies might be rendered powerless and we might no longer be slaves to sin.
B045C006V007	45	6	7	For the person who has died has been freed from sin.
B045C006V008	45	6	8	Now if we have died with Christ, we believe that we will also live with him,
B045C006V009	45	6	9	for we know that Christ, who was raised from the dead, will never die again; death no longer has mastery over him.
B045C006V010	45	6	10	For when he died, he died once and for all as far as sin is concerned. But now that he is alive, he lives for God.
B045C006V011	45	6	11	In the same way, you too must continually consider yourselves dead as far as sin is concerned, but alive to God in Christ Jesus.
B045C006V012	45	6	12	Therefore, do not let sin rule your mortal bodies so that you obey their desires.
B045C006V013	45	6	13	Stop offering the parts of your body to sin as instruments of unrighteousness. Instead, offer yourselves to God as people who have been brought from death to life and the parts of your body as instruments of righteousness to God.
B045C006V014	45	6	14	For sin will not have mastery over you, because you are not under law but under grace.
B045C006V015	45	6	15	What, then, does this mean? Should we go on sinning because we are not under law but under grace? Of course not!
B045C006V016	45	6	16	Don't you know that when you offer yourselves to someone as obedient slaves, you are slaves of the one you obey—either of sin, which leads to death, or of obedience, which leads to righteousness?
B045C006V017	45	6	17	But thank God that, though you were once slaves of sin, you became obedient from your hearts to that form of teaching with which you were entrusted!
B045C006V018	45	6	18	And since you have been freed from sin, you have become slaves of righteousness.
B045C006V019	45	6	19	I am speaking in human terms because of the frailty of your flesh. Just as you once offered the parts of your body as slaves to impurity and to greater and greater disobedience, so now, in the same way, you must offer the parts of your body as slaves to righteousness that leads to sanctification.
B045C006V020	45	6	20	For when you were slaves of sin, you were free as far as righteousness was concerned.
B045C006V021	45	6	21	What benefit did you get from doing those things you are now ashamed of? For those things resulted in death.
B045C006V022	45	6	22	But now that you have been freed from sin and have become God's slaves, the benefit you reap is sanctification, and the result is eternal life.
B045C006V023	45	6	23	For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life in union with Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C007V001	45	7	1	Don't you realize, brothers—for I am speaking to people who know the law—that the law can press its claims over a person only as long as he is alive?
B045C007V002	45	7	2	For a married woman is bound by the law to her husband while he is living, but if her husband dies, she is released from the law concerning her husband.
B045C007V003	45	7	3	So while her husband is living, she will be called an adulterer even if she lives with another man. But if her husband dies, she is free from this law, so that she is not an adulterer if she marries another man.
B045C007V004	45	7	4	In the same way, my brothers, through Christ's body you also died as far as the law is concerned, so that you may belong to another person, the one who was raised from the dead, and may bear fruit for God.
B045C007V005	45	7	5	For while we were living in the flesh, sinful passions aroused by the law were at work in our bodies to bear fruit for death.
B045C007V006	45	7	6	But now we have been released from the law by dying to what enslaved us, so that we may serve in the new life of the Spirit, not under the old written code.
B045C007V007	45	7	7	What should we say, then? Is the law sinful? Of course not! In fact, I wouldn't have known sin if it had not been for the law. For I wouldn't have known what it means to covet if the law had not said, “You must not covet.”
B045C007V008	45	7	8	But sin seized the opportunity provided by this commandment and produced in me all kinds of sinful desires. For apart from the law, sin is dead.
B045C007V009	45	7	9	At one time I was alive without any connection to the law. But when the commandment came, sin sprang to life,
B045C007V010	45	7	10	and I died. I found that the very commandment that was intended to bring life actually brought death.
B045C007V011	45	7	11	For sin, seizing the opportunity provided by the commandment, deceived me and used it to kill me.
B045C007V012	45	7	12	So then, the law itself is holy, and the commandment is holy, just, and good.
B045C007V013	45	7	13	Now, did something good bring me death? Of course not! But in order that sin might be recognized as sin, it used something good to cause my death, so that through the commandment sin might become more sinful than ever.
B045C007V014	45	7	14	For we know that the law is spiritual, but I am mere flesh, sold as a slave to sin.
B045C007V015	45	7	15	I don't understand what I am doing. For I don't do what I want to do, but instead do what I hate.
B045C007V016	45	7	16	Now if I do what I don't want to do, I agree that the law is good.
B045C007V017	45	7	17	As it is, I am no longer the one who is doing it, but it is the sin that lives in me.
B045C007V018	45	7	18	For I know that nothing good lives in me, that is, in my flesh. For I have the desire to do what is right, but I cannot carry it out.
B045C007V019	45	7	19	For I don't do the good I want to do, but instead do the evil that I don't want to do.
B045C007V020	45	7	20	But if I do what I don't want to do, I am no longer the one who is doing it, but it is the sin that lives in me.
B045C007V021	45	7	21	So I find this to be a law: when I want to do what is good, evil is right there with me.
B045C007V022	45	7	22	For I delight in the law of God in my inner being,
B045C007V023	45	7	23	but I see in my body a different law waging war with the law in my mind and making me a prisoner of the law of sin that exists in my body.
B045C007V024	45	7	24	What a wretched man I am! Who will rescue me from this body of death?
B045C007V025	45	7	25	Thank God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, with my mind I myself serve the law of God, but with my flesh I serve the law of sin.
B045C008V001	45	8	1	Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in union with Christ Jesus.
B045C008V002	45	8	2	For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus has set me free from the law of sin and death.
B045C008V003	45	8	3	For what the law was powerless to do in that it was weakened by the flesh, God did by sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh to deal with sin. He condemned sin in the flesh
B045C008V004	45	8	4	so that the righteous requirement of the law might be fulfilled in us, who do not live according to the flesh but according to the Spirit.
B045C008V005	45	8	5	For those who live according to the flesh set their minds on the things of the flesh, but those who live according to the Spirit set their minds on the things of the Spirit.
B045C008V006	45	8	6	To set our minds on the flesh leads to death, but to set our minds on the Spirit leads to life and peace.
B045C008V007	45	8	7	That is why the mind that is set on the flesh is hostile toward God. For it refuses to submit to the authority of God's law because it is powerless to do so.
B045C008V008	45	8	8	Indeed, those who are under the control of the flesh cannot please God.
B045C008V009	45	8	9	You, however, are not of the flesh but under the control of the Spirit, since God's Spirit lives in you. And if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, he does not belong to him.
B045C008V010	45	8	10	But if Christ is in you, your bodies are dead because of sin, but the Spirit is life because of righteousness.
B045C008V011	45	8	11	And if the Spirit of the one who raised Jesus from the dead is living in you, then the one who raised Christ from the dead will also make your mortal bodies alive by his Spirit who lives in you.
B045C008V012	45	8	12	Consequently, brothers, we have an obligation—but it is not to the flesh, to live according to the flesh.
B045C008V013	45	8	13	For if you live according to the flesh, you are going to die, but if by the Spirit you continually put to death the activities of the body, you will live.
B045C008V014	45	8	14	For all who are led by God's Spirit are God's children.
B045C008V015	45	8	15	For you have not received a spirit of slavery that leads you into fear again. Instead, you have received the Spirit of adoption by whom we cry out, “Abba! Father!”
B045C008V016	45	8	16	The Spirit himself testifies with our spirit that we are God's children.
B045C008V017	45	8	17	Now if we are children, we are heirs—heirs of God and co-heirs with Christ, if, in fact, we share in his sufferings in order that we may also share in his glory.
B045C008V018	45	8	18	For I consider that the sufferings of this present time are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed to us.
B045C008V019	45	8	19	For the creation is eagerly waiting for God to reveal his children,
B045C008V020	45	8	20	because the creation was subjected to frustration, though not by its own choice. The one who subjected it did so in the hope
B045C008V021	45	8	21	that the creation itself would also be set free from slavery to decay in order to share the glorious freedom of God's children.
B045C008V022	45	8	22	For we know that all creation has been groaning with the pains of childbirth right up to the present time.
B045C008V023	45	8	23	However, not only creation groans, but we who have the first fruits of the Spirit also groan inwardly as we eagerly wait for our adoption, the redemption of our bodies.
B045C008V024	45	8	24	For we were saved with this hope in mind. Now hope that is seen is not really hope, for who hopes for what can be seen?
B045C008V025	45	8	25	But if we hope for what we do not see, we eagerly wait for it with patience.
B045C008V026	45	8	26	In the same way, the Spirit also helps us in our weakness, for we do not know how to pray as we should. But the Spirit himself intercedes with groans too deep for words,
B045C008V027	45	8	27	and the one who searches our hearts knows the mind of the Spirit, for the Spirit intercedes for the saints according to God's will.
B045C008V028	45	8	28	And we know that he works all things together for the good of those who love God, who are called according to his purpose.
B045C008V029	45	8	29	For those whom he foreknew he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his Son, in order that he might be the firstborn among many brothers.
B045C008V030	45	8	30	And those whom he predestined, he also called; and those whom he called, he also justified; and those whom he justified he also glorified.
B045C008V031	45	8	31	What, then, can we say about all of this? If God is for us, who can be against us?
B045C008V032	45	8	32	The one who did not spare his own Son but gave him up for all of us—surely he will give us all things along with him, won't he?
B045C008V033	45	8	33	Who can bring an accusation against God's chosen people? It is God who justifies them!
B045C008V034	45	8	34	Who can condemn them? Christ Jesus, who died—and more importantly, who has been raised and is seated at the right hand of God—is the one who is also interceding for us!
B045C008V035	45	8	35	Who can separate us from Christ's love? Can trouble, distress, persecution, hunger, nakedness, danger, or a sword?
B045C008V036	45	8	36	As it is written,	“For your sake we are being killed all day long.We are thought of as sheep to be slaughtered.”
B045C008V037	45	8	37	No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through the one who loved us.
B045C008V038	45	8	38	For I am convinced that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor rulers, nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,
B045C008V039	45	8	39	nor anything above, nor anything below, nor anything else in all creation can separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C009V001	45	9	1	I am telling the truth in union with Christ—I am not lying, for my conscience, confirms it in the Holy Spirit.
B045C009V002	45	9	2	I have deep sorrow and unceasing anguish in my heart,
B045C009V003	45	9	3	for I could wish that I myself were condemned and cut off from Christ for the sake of my brothers, my relatives according to the flesh.
B045C009V004	45	9	4	They are Israelites. To them belong the adoption, the glory, the covenants, the giving of the law, the worship, and the promises.
B045C009V005	45	9	5	To them belong the patriarchs, and from them, according to the flesh, Christ descended, who is God over all, blessed forever. Amen.
B045C009V006	45	9	6	Now it is not as though the word of God has failed. For not all Israelites truly belong to Israel,
B045C009V007	45	9	7	and not all of Abraham's descendants are his true descendants. On the contrary, “It is through Isaac that descendants will be named for you.”
B045C009V008	45	9	8	That is, it is not the children of natural descent who are God's children, but it is the children of the promise who are regarded as descendants.
B045C009V009	45	9	9	For this is the language of promise: “At this time I will return, and Sarah will have a son.”
B045C009V010	45	9	10	Not only that, but Rebecca became pregnant by our ancestor Isaac.
B045C009V011	45	9	11	Yet before their children had been born or had done anything good or bad (so that God's plan of election might continue to operate
B045C009V012	45	9	12	according to his calling and not by works), Rebecca was told, “The older child will serve the younger one.”
B045C009V013	45	9	13	As it is written, “Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated.”
B045C009V014	45	9	14	What can we say, then? God is not unrighteous, is he? Of course not!
B045C009V015	45	9	15	For he says to Moses, “I will be merciful to the person I want to be merciful to, and I will be kind to the person I want to be kind to.”
B045C009V016	45	9	16	Therefore, God's choice does not depend on a person's will or effort, but on God himself, who shows mercy.
B045C009V017	45	9	17	For the Scripture says to Pharaoh,	“I have raised you up for this very purpose,to demonstrate my power in you	and that my name might be proclaimedin all the earth.”
B045C009V018	45	9	18	Therefore, God has mercy on whomever he chooses, and he hardens the heart of whomever he chooses.
B045C009V019	45	9	19	You may ask me, “Then why does God still find fault with anybody? For who can resist his will?”
B045C009V020	45	9	20	On the contrary, who are you—mere man that you are—to talk back to God? Can an object that was molded say to the one who molded it, “Why did you make me like this?”
B045C009V021	45	9	21	A potter has the right to do what he wants to with his clay, doesn't he? He can make something for a special occasion or something for ordinary use from the same lump.
B045C009V022	45	9	22	Now if God wants to demonstrate his wrath and reveal his power, can't he be extremely patient with the objects of his wrath that are made for destruction?
B045C009V023	45	9	23	Can't he also reveal his glorious riches to the objects of his mercy that he has prepared ahead of time for glory—
B045C009V024	45	9	24	including us, whom he also called, not only from the Jews but from the Gentiles as well?
B045C009V025	45	9	25	As he says in Hosea,	“Those who are not my peopleI will call my people,	and the one who was not lovedI will call my loved one.
B045C009V026	45	9	26	In the very place where it was said to them,‘You are not my people,’they will be called children of the living God.”
B045C009V027	45	9	27	Isaiah also calls out concerning Israel,	“Although the descendants of Israelare as numerous as the grains of sand on the seashore,only a few will be saved.
B045C009V028	45	9	28	For the Lord will carry out his planand shorten it in righteousness,because he will carry out his plan on the earth decisively.”
B045C009V029	45	9	29	It is just as Isaiah predicted:	“If the Lord of the Heavenly Armieshad not left us some descendants,we would have become like Sodomand would have been compared to Gomorrah.”
B045C009V030	45	9	30	What can we say, then? Gentiles, who were not pursuing righteousness, have attained righteousness, a righteousness that comes through faith.
B045C009V031	45	9	31	But Israel, who did pursue the righteousness that is based on the law, did not arrive at that law.
B045C009V032	45	9	32	Why not? Because they did not pursue it on the basis of faith, but as if it were based on works. They stumbled over the stone that causes people to stumble.
B045C009V033	45	9	33	As it is written,	“Look! I am placing a stone in Zionthat people will stumble over	and a large rock that will make them fall,and the one who believes in him will never be ashamed.”
B045C010V001	45	10	1	Brothers, my heart's desire and prayer to God on behalf of the Jews is that they would be saved.
B045C010V002	45	10	2	For I can testify on their behalf that they have a zeal for God, but it is not in keeping with full knowledge.
B045C010V003	45	10	3	For they are ignorant of the righteousness that comes from God while they try to establish their own, and they have not submitted to God's righteousness.
B045C010V004	45	10	4	For Christ is the culmination of the law as far as righteousness is concerned for everyone who believes.
B045C010V005	45	10	5	For Moses writes about the righteousness that comes from the law as follows: “The person who obeys these things will find life in them.”
B045C010V006	45	10	6	But the righteousness that comes from faith says, “Do not say in your heart, ‘Who will go up to heaven?’ (that is, to bring Christ down),
B045C010V007	45	10	7	or ‘Who will go down into the depths?’ (that is, to bring Christ back from the dead).”
B045C010V008	45	10	8	But what does it say? “The message is near you. It is in your mouth and in your heart.” This is the message of faith that we proclaim:
B045C010V009	45	10	9	If you declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord, and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.
B045C010V010	45	10	10	For a person believes with his heart and is justified, and a person declares with his mouth and is saved.
B045C010V011	45	10	11	For the Scripture says, “Everyone who believes in him will not be ashamed.”
B045C010V012	45	10	12	For there is no difference between Jew and Greek, because they all have the same Lord, who gives richly to all who call on him.
B045C010V013	45	10	13	For “everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.”
B045C010V014	45	10	14	How, then, can people call on someone they have not believed? And how can they believe in someone they have not heard about? And how can they hear without someone preaching?
B045C010V015	45	10	15	And how can they preach unless they are sent? As it is written,	“How beautiful are the feet of thosewho bring the good news!”
B045C010V016	45	10	16	But not everyone has obeyed the gospel. For Isaiah asks,	“Lord, who has believed our message?”
B045C010V017	45	10	17	Consequently, faith comes from listening, and listening comes through the word of Christ.
B045C010V018	45	10	18	But I ask, “Didn't they hear?” Certainly they did! In fact,	“Their voice has gone out into the whole world,and their words to the ends of the earth.”
B045C010V019	45	10	19	Again I ask, “Did Israel not understand?” Moses was the first to say,	“I will make you jealousby those who are not a nation;	I will make you angryby a nation that doesn't understand.”
B045C010V020	45	10	20	And Isaiah boldly says,	“I was found by those who were not looking for me;I was revealed to those who were not asking for me.”
B045C010V021	45	10	21	But about Israel he says,	“All day long I have held out my handsto a disobedient and rebellious people.”
B045C011V001	45	11	1	So I ask, “God has not rejected his people, has he?” Of course not! I am an Israelite myself, a descendant of Abraham from the tribe of Benjamin.
B045C011V002	45	11	2	God has not rejected his people whom he chose long ago. Don't you know what the Scripture says in the story about Elijah, when he pleads with God against Israel?
B045C011V003	45	11	3	“Lord, they have killed your prophets and demolished your altars. I am the only one left, and they are trying to take my life.”
B045C011V004	45	11	4	But what was the divine reply to him? “I have reserved for myself 7,000 people who have not knelt to worship Baal.”
B045C011V005	45	11	5	So it is at the present time: there is a remnant, chosen by grace.
B045C011V006	45	11	6	But if this is by grace, then it is no longer on the basis of works. Otherwise, grace would no longer be grace.
B045C011V007	45	11	7	What, then, does this mean? It means that Israel failed to obtain what it was striving for, but those who were chosen obtained it. However, the rest were hardened.
B045C011V008	45	11	8	As it is written,	“To this day God has given them a spirit of deep sleep.Their eyes do not see, and their ears do not hear.”
B045C011V009	45	11	9	And David says,	“Let their table become a snare and a trap,a stumbling block and a punishment for them.
B045C011V010	45	11	10	Let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see,and keep their backs forever bent.”
B045C011V011	45	11	11	And so I ask, “They have not stumbled so as to fall, have they?” Of course not! On the contrary, because of their stumbling, salvation has come to the Gentiles to make the Jews jealous.
B045C011V012	45	11	12	Now if their stumbling means riches for the world, and if their fall means riches for the Gentiles, how much more will their full inclusion mean!
B045C011V013	45	11	13	I am speaking to you Gentiles. Because I am an apostle to the Gentiles, I am glorifying my ministry
B045C011V014	45	11	14	in the hope that I can make my people jealous and save some of them.
B045C011V015	45	11	15	For if their rejection means the reconciliation of the world, what will their acceptance mean but life from the dead?
B045C011V016	45	11	16	If the first part of the dough is holy, so is the whole batch. If the root is holy, so are the branches.
B045C011V017	45	11	17	Now if some of the branches have been broken off, and you, a wild olive branch, have been grafted in their place to share the rich root of the olive tree,
B045C011V018	45	11	18	do not boast about being better than the other branches. If you boast, remember that you do not support the root, but the root supports you.
B045C011V019	45	11	19	Then you will say, “Branches were cut off so that I could be grafted in.”
B045C011V020	45	11	20	That's right! They were broken off because of their unbelief, but you remain only because of faith. Do not be arrogant, but be afraid!
B045C011V021	45	11	21	For if God did not spare the natural branches, he certainly will not spare you either.
B045C011V022	45	11	22	Consider, then, the kindness and severity of God: his severity toward those who fell, but God's kindness toward you—if you continue in his kindness. Otherwise, you too will be cut off.
B045C011V023	45	11	23	If the Jews do not persist in their unbelief, they will be grafted in again, because God is able to graft them in.
B045C011V024	45	11	24	After all, if you were cut off from what is naturally a wild olive tree, and contrary to nature were grafted into a cultivated olive tree, how much easier it will be for these natural branches to be grafted back into their own olive tree!
B045C011V025	45	11	25	For I do not want you to be ignorant of this secret, brothers, so that you will not claim to be wiser than you are. A partial hardening has come on Israel until the full number of the Gentiles has come in.
B045C011V026	45	11	26	In this way, all Israel will be saved. As it is written,	“The Deliverer will come from Zion;he will remove ungodliness from Jacob.
B045C011V027	45	11	27	This is my covenant with themwhen I take away their sins.”
B045C011V028	45	11	28	As far as the gospel is concerned, they are enemies for your sake, but as far as election is concerned, they are loved because of their ancestors.
B045C011V029	45	11	29	For God's gifts and calling never change.
B045C011V030	45	11	30	For just as you disobeyed God in the past but now have received his mercy because of their disobedience,
B045C011V031	45	11	31	in order they too have disobeyed in the present so that they may receive mercy because of the mercy shown to you.
B045C011V032	45	11	32	For God has locked all people in the prison of their own disobedience so that he may have mercy on them all.
B045C011V033	45	11	33	O how deep are God's riches, wisdom, and knowledge! How impossible to explain his judgments or to understand his ways!
B045C011V034	45	11	34	“Who has known the mind of the Lord?Or who has become his adviser?
B045C011V035	45	11	35	Who has given him somethingonly to have him pay it back?”
B045C011V036	45	11	36	For all things are from him, by him, and for him. Glory belongs to him forever! Amen.
B045C012V001	45	12	1	I therefore urge you, brothers, in view of God's mercies, to offer your bodies as living sacrifices that are holy and pleasing to God, for this is the reasonable way for you to worship.
B045C012V002	45	12	2	Do not be conformed to this world, but continually be transformed by the renewing of your minds so that you may be able to determine what God's will is—what is proper, pleasing, and perfect.
B045C012V003	45	12	3	For by the grace given to me I ask every one of you not to think of yourself more highly than you should think, rather to think of yourself with sober judgment on the measure of faith that God has assigned each of you.
B045C012V004	45	12	4	For we have many parts in one body, but these parts do not all have the same function.
B045C012V005	45	12	5	In the same way, even though we are many people, we are one body in Christ and individual parts connected to each other.
B045C012V006	45	12	6	We have different gifts based on the grace that was given to us. So if your gift is prophecy, use your gift in proportion to your faith.
B045C012V007	45	12	7	If your gift is serving, devote yourself to serving others. If it is teaching, devote yourself to teaching others.
B045C012V008	45	12	8	If it is encouraging, devote yourself to encouraging others. If it is sharing, share generously. If it is leading, lead enthusiastically. If it is helping, help cheerfully.
B045C012V009	45	12	9	Your love must be without hypocrisy. Abhor what is evil; cling to what is good.
B045C012V010	45	12	10	Be devoted to each other with mutual affection. Excel in showing respect for each other.
B045C012V011	45	12	11	Never be lazy in showing such devotion. Be on fire with the Spirit. Serve the Lord.
B045C012V012	45	12	12	Be joyful in hope, patient in trouble, and persistent in prayer.
B045C012V013	45	12	13	Supply the needs of the saints. Extend hospitality to strangers.
B045C012V014	45	12	14	Bless those who persecute you. Keep on blessing them, and never curse them.
B045C012V015	45	12	15	Rejoice with those who are rejoicing. Cry with those who are crying.
B045C012V016	45	12	16	Live in harmony with each other. Do not be arrogant, but associate with humble people. Do not think that you are wiser than you really are.
B045C012V017	45	12	17	Do not pay anyone back evil for evil, but focus your thoughts on what is right in the sight of all people.
B045C012V018	45	12	18	If possible, so far as it depends on you, live in peace with all people.
B045C012V019	45	12	19	Do not take revenge, dear fiends, but leave room for God's wrath. For it is written, “Vengeance belongs to me. I will pay them back, declares the Lord.”
B045C012V020	45	12	20	But “if your enemy is hungry, feed him. For if he is thirsty, give him a drink. If you do this, you will pile burning coals on his head.”
B045C012V021	45	12	21	Do not be conquered by evil, but conquer evil with good.
B045C013V001	45	13	1	Every person must be subject to the governing authorities, for no authority exists except by God's permission. The existing authorities have been established by God,
B045C013V002	45	13	2	so that whoever resists the authorities opposes what God has established, and those who resist will bring judgment on themselves.
B045C013V003	45	13	3	For the authorities are not a terror to good conduct, but to bad. Would you like to live without being afraid of the authorities? Then do what is right, and you will receive their approval.
B045C013V004	45	13	4	For they are God's servants working for your good. But if you do what is wrong, you should be afraid, for it is not without reason that they bear the sword. Indeed, they are God's servants to execute wrath on anyone who does wrong.
B045C013V005	45	13	5	Therefore, it is necessary for you to be subject, not only because of God's wrath but also because of your own conscience.
B045C013V006	45	13	6	This is also why you pay taxes. For rulers are God's servants faithfully devoting themselves to their work.
B045C013V007	45	13	7	Pay everyone whatever you owe them—taxes to whom taxes are due, tolls to whom tolls are due, fear to whom fear is due, honor to whom honor is due.
B045C013V008	45	13	8	Do not owe anyone anything—except to love one another. For the one who loves another has fulfilled the law.
B045C013V009	45	13	9	For the commandments, “You must not commit adultery; you must not murder; you must not steal; you must not covet,” and every other commandment are summed up in this statement: “You must love your neighbor as yourself.”
B045C013V010	45	13	10	Love never does anything that is harmful to its neighbor. Therefore, love is the fulfillment of the law.
B045C013V011	45	13	11	This is necessary because you know the times—that it's time for you to wake up from sleep. For our salvation is nearer now than when we became believers.
B045C013V012	45	13	12	The night is almost over, and the day is near. Let us therefore put aside the works of darkness and put on the armor of light.
B045C013V013	45	13	13	Let us behave decently, as people who live in the light of day. No wild parties, drunkenness, sexual immorality, promiscuity, rivalry, or jealousy!
B045C013V014	45	13	14	Instead, clothe yourselves with the Lord Jesus Christ, and do not obey your flesh and its desires.
B045C014V001	45	14	1	Accept the person who is weak in faith, but not for the purpose of arguing over differences of opinion.
B045C014V002	45	14	2	One person believes that he can eat anything, while the weak person eats only vegetables.
B045C014V003	45	14	3	The person who eats must not despise the person who does not eat, and the person who does not eat must not criticize the person who eats, for God has accepted him.
B045C014V004	45	14	4	Who are you to criticize someone else's servant? His own Lord will determine whether he stands or falls. And stand he will, because God is able to make him stand.
B045C014V005	45	14	5	One person decides that one day is better than another, while another person decides that all days are the same. Each one must be fully convinced in his own mind.
B045C014V006	45	14	6	The one who observes a special day, observes it to honor the Lord. The one who eats, eats to honor the Lord, since he gives thanks to God. And the one who does not eat, refrains from eating to honor the Lord; yet he, too, gives thanks to God.
B045C014V007	45	14	7	For none of us lives to himself, and no one dies to himself.
B045C014V008	45	14	8	If we live, we live to honor the Lord; and if we die, we die to honor the Lord. So whether we live or die, we belong to the Lord.
B045C014V009	45	14	9	For this reason Christ died and returned to life, so that he might become the Lord of both the dead and the living.
B045C014V010	45	14	10	Why, then, do you criticize your brother? Or why do you despise your brother? For all of us will stand before the judgment seat of God.
B045C014V011	45	14	11	For it is written,	“As certainly as I live, declares the Lord,every knee will bow to me,and every tongue will praise God.”
B045C014V012	45	14	12	Consequently, each of us will give an account of himself to God.
B045C014V013	45	14	13	Therefore, let us no longer criticize each other. Instead, make up your mind not to put a stumbling block or hindrance in the way of a brother.
B045C014V014	45	14	14	I know and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus that nothing is unclean in and of itself. But it is unclean to a person who thinks it is unclean.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	For if your brother is being hurt by what you eat, you are no longer acting in love. Do not destroy the person for whom Christ died by what you eat.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Do not allow your good to be spoken of as evil.
B045C014V017	45	14	17	For God's kingdom does not consist of food and drink, but of righteousness, peace, and joy produced by the Holy Spirit.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For the person who serves Christ in this way is pleasing to God and approved by people.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	Therefore, let us keep on pursuing those things that bring peace and that lead to building one another up.
B045C014V020	45	14	20	Do not destroy God's work for the sake of food. Everything is clean, but it is wrong to make another person fall because of what you eat.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	The right thing to do is to avoid eating meat, drinking wine, or doing anything else that makes your brother stumble or become upset or weak.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	As for the faith you do have, have it as your own conviction before God. How blessed is the person who has no reason to condemn himself because of what he approves!
B045C014V023	45	14	23	But the person who has doubts is condemned if he eats, because he does not act in faith; and anything that is not done in faith is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	Now we who are strong ought to be patient with the weaknesses of those who are not strong and must stop pleasing ourselves.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	Each of us must please our neighbor for the good purpose of building him up.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	For even Christ did not please himself. Instead, as it is written, “The insults of those who insult you have fallen on me.”
B045C015V004	45	15	4	For everything that was written long ago was written for our instruction, so that we might have hope through the endurance and encouragement that the Scriptures give us.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	Now may God, the source of endurance and encouragement, allow you to live in harmony with each other as you follow Christ Jesus,
B045C015V006	45	15	6	so that with one mind and one voice you might glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore, accept one another, just as Christ accepted you, for the glory of God.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	For I tell you that Christ became a servant of the circumcised on behalf of God's truth in order to confirm the promises given to our forefathers,
B045C015V009	45	15	9	so that the Gentiles may glorify God for his mercy. As it is written,	“That is why I will praise you among the Gentiles;I will sing praises to your name.”
B045C015V010	45	15	10	Again he says,	“Rejoice, you Gentiles, with his people!”
B045C015V011	45	15	11	And again,	“Praise the Lord, all you Gentiles!Let all the nations praise him.”
B045C015V012	45	15	12	And again, Isaiah says,	“There will be a Root from Jesse.He will rise up to rule the Gentiles,and the Gentiles will hope in him.”
B045C015V013	45	15	13	Now may God, the source of hope, fill you with all joy and peace as you believe, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V014	45	15	14	I myself am convinced, my brothers, that you yourselves are filled with goodness and full of all the knowledge you need to be able to instruct each other.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	However, on some points I have written to you rather boldly, both as a reminder to you and because of the grace given me by God
B045C015V016	45	15	16	to be a minister of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles in the priestly service of the gospel of God, so that the offering of the Gentiles might be acceptable because it has been sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	Therefore, in Christ Jesus I have the right to boast about my work for God.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I am bold enough to tell you only about what Christ has accomplished through me in the bringing of Gentiles to obedience. By my words and actions,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	by the power of signs and wonders, and by the power of God's Spirit, I have fully proclaimed the gospel of Christ from Jerusalem as far as Illyricum.
B045C015V020	45	15	20	My one ambition is to proclaim the gospel where the name of Christ is not known, lest I build on someone else's foundation.
B045C015V021	45	15	21	Rather, as it is written,	“Those who were never told about him will see,and those who have never heard will understand.”
B045C015V022	45	15	22	This is why I have so often been hindered in coming to you.
B045C015V023	45	15	23	But now, having no further opportunities in these regions, I have the desire to come to you, as I have had for many years.
B045C015V024	45	15	24	Now that I am on my way to Spain, I hope to see you when I come your way and, after I have enjoyed your company for a while, to be sent on by you.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	Right now, however, I am going to Jerusalem to minister to the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For the believers in Macedonia and Achaia have been eager to share their resources with the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	Yes, they were eager to do this, and in fact they are obligated to help them, for if the Gentiles have shared in their spiritual blessings, they are obligated to be of service to them in material things.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	So when I have completed this task and have put my seal on this contribution of theirs, I will visit you on my way to Spain.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	And I know that when I come to you I will come with the full blessing of Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I urge you, brothers, by our Lord Jesus Christ and by the love that the Spirit produces, to join me in my struggle, earnestly praying to God for me
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be rescued from the unbelievers in Judea, that my ministry to Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints,
B045C015V032	45	15	32	and that by the will of God I may come to you with joy and together with you be refreshed.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	Now may the God of peace be with all of you! Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	Now I commend to you our sister Phoebe, a servant in the church at Cenchreae.
B045C016V002	45	16	2	Welcome her in the Lord as is appropriate for saints, and provide her with anything she may need from you, for she has assisted many people, including me.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus,
B045C016V004	45	16	4	who risked their necks for my life. I am thankful to them, and so are all the churches among the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	Greet also the church in their house. Greet my dear friend Epaenetus, who was the first convert to Christ in Asia.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Greet Mary, who has worked very hard for you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Greet Andronicus and Junias, my fellow Jews who are in prison with me and are prominent among the apostles. They were in Christ before I was.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Greet Ampliatus, my dear friend in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Greet Urbanus, our fellow in Christ, and my dear friend Stachys.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Greet Apelles, who has been approved by Christ. Greet those who belong to the family of Aristobulus.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Greet Herodion, my fellow Jew. Greet those in the family of Narcissus, who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Greet Tryphaena and Tryphosa, who have worked hard in the Lord. Greet my dear friend Persis, who has worked very hard in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Greet Rufus, the one chosen by the Lord, and his mother, who has been a mother to me, too.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers who are with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Greet Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	Now I urge you, brothers, to watch out for those who create divisions and sinful enticements in opposition to the teaching you have learned. Stay away from them!
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For such people are not serving Christ our Lord but their own desires. By their smooth talk and flattering words they deceive the hearts of the unsuspecting.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For your obedience has become known to everyone, and I am full of joy for you. But I want you to be wise about what is good, and innocent about what is evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	The God of peace will soon crush Satan under your feet. May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you!
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, greets you, as do Lucius, Jason, and Sosipater, my fellow Jews.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertius, who wrote down this letter, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, who is host to me and the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the city treasurer, and our brother Quartus greet you.
B045C016V025	45	16	25	Now to the one who is able to strengthen you by my gospel and the message that I preach about Jesus Christ, by revealing the secret that was kept in silence in long ages past
B045C016V026	45	16	26	but now has been made known through the prophets to all the Gentiles, in keeping with the decree of the eternal God to bring them to the obedience of faith—
B045C016V027	45	16	27	to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, be glory forever! Amen.
B046C001V001	46	1	1	From Paul, called to be an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and from our brother Sosthenes,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the church of God in Corinth, to those who have been sanctified in Christ Jesus and called to be holy, together with all those everywhere who continually call on the name of our Lord Jesus Christ—their Lord and ours.
B046C001V003	46	1	3	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I always thank my God for you because of the grace of God given you in Christ Jesus.
B046C001V005	46	1	5	For in him you have become rich in every way—in speech and knowledge of every kind.
B046C001V006	46	1	6	In this way, our testimony about Christ has been confirmed among you.
B046C001V007	46	1	7	Therefore, you don't lack any spiritual gift as you eagerly wait for our Lord Jesus Christ to be revealed.
B046C001V008	46	1	8	He will keep you strong until the end, so that you will be blameless on the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	Faithful is the God by whom you were called into fellowship with his Son Jesus Christ our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	Brothers, I urge all of you in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to be in agreement and not to have divisions among you, so that you may be perfectly united in your understanding and opinions.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	My brothers, some members of Chloe's family have made it clear to me that there are quarrels among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	This is what I mean: Each of you is saying, “I belong to Paul,” or “I belong to Apollos,” or “I belong to Cephas,” or “I belong to Christ.”
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Has Christ been divided? Paul wasn't crucified for you, was he? You weren't baptized in Paul's name, were you?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I thank God that I did not baptize any of you except Chrispus and Gaius,
B046C001V015	46	1	15	lest anyone can say that you were baptized in my name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	(Yes, I also baptized the family of Stephanus. Beyond that, I'm not sure whether I baptized anyone else.)
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ did not send me to baptize but to preach the gospel, not with eloquent wisdom, lest the cross of Christ be emptied of its power.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the message about the cross is nonsense to those who are being destroyed, but it is God's power to us who are being saved.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written,	“I will destroy the wisdom of the wise,and the intelligence of the intelligent I will reject.”
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise person? Where is the scholar? Where is the philosopher of this age? God has turned the wisdom of the world into nonsense, hasn't he?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For since in the wisdom of God the world through its wisdom did not know God, God decided through the nonsense of our preaching to save those who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	Jews ask for signs, and Greeks look for wisdom,
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we preach Christ crucified. He is a stumbling block to Jews and nonsense to Gentiles,
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ is God's power and God's wisdom.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	For God's nonsense is wiser than human wisdom, and God's weakness is stronger than human strength.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	Brothers, think about your own calling. Not many of you were wise by human standards, not many were powerful, not many were of noble birth.
B046C001V027	46	1	27	But God chose what is nonsense in the world to make the wise feel ashamed. God chose what is weak in the world to make the strong feel ashamed.
B046C001V028	46	1	28	And God chose what is insignificant in the world, what is despised, what is nothing, in order to destroy what is something,
B046C001V029	46	1	29	so that no human being may boast in God's presence.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	It is because of him that you are in union with Christ Jesus, who for us has become wisdom from God, as well as our righteousness, sanctification, and redemption.
B046C001V031	46	1	31	Therefore, as it is written, “The person who boasts must boast in the Lord.”
B046C002V001	46	2	1	When I came to you, brothers, I didn't come and tell you about God's secret with rhetorical language or wisdom.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For while I was with you I resolved to know nothing except Jesus Christ and him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	It was in weakness, fear, and great trembling that I came to you.
B046C002V004	46	2	4	My message and my preaching were not accompanied by clever words of wisdom, but by a display of the Spirit's power,
B046C002V005	46	2	5	so that your faith would not be based on human wisdom but on God's power.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	However, when we are among mature people, we do speak a message of wisdom, but not the wisdom of this world or of the rulers of this world, who are passing off the scene.
B046C002V007	46	2	7	Instead, we speak about God's secret wisdom that has been hidden, which God destined for our glory before the world began.
B046C002V008	46	2	8	None of the rulers of this world understood it, for if they had, they would not have crucified the Lord of Glory.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written,	“No eye has seen, no ear has heard,and no mind has imagined	the things that God has preparedfor those who love him.”
B046C002V010	46	2	10	But God has revealed those things to us by his Spirit. For the Spirit searches everything, even the deep things of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	Is there anyone who can understand his own thoughts except by his own inner spirit? In the same way, no one can know the thoughts of God except God's Spirit.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	Now, we have not received the spirit of the world but the Spirit who comes from God, so that we can understand the things that were freely given to us by God.
B046C002V013	46	2	13	We don't speak about these things in words taught us by human wisdom, but in words taught by the Spirit, as we explain spiritual things to spiritual people.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	A person who isn't spiritual doesn't accept the things of God's Spirit, for they are nonsense to him. He can't understand them because they are spiritually evaluated.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	The spiritual person evaluates everything but is subject to no one else's evaluation.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	For	“Who has known the mind of the Lordso that he can advise him?”However, we have the mind of Christ.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	Brothers, I couldn't talk to you as spiritual people but as worldly people, as mere infants in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I gave you milk to drink, not solid food, because you weren't ready for it. Why, you're still not ready for it!
B046C003V003	46	3	3	That's because you are still worldly. As long as there is jealousy and quarreling among you, you are worldly and living by human standards, aren't you?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For when one says, “I belong to Paul,” and another, “I belong to Apollos,” you are merely human, aren't you?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	What is Apollos anyhow? Or what is Paul? Mere servants through whom you came to believe, as the Lord gave to each of us his task.
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I did the planting, Apollos did the watering, but God kept everything growing.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is significant, but God, who keeps everything growing, is the one who matters.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	The one who plants and the one who waters have the same goal, and each will receive a reward for his own work.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For we are God's co-workers. You are God's farmland and God's building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	As an expert builder using the grace that God gave me, I laid the foundation, and someone else is building on it. But each person must be careful how he builds on it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	After all, no one can lay any other foundation than the one that is already laid, and that is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	Whether a person builds on this foundation with gold, silver, expensive stones, wood, hay, or straw,
B046C003V013	46	3	13	the workmanship of each person will become evident, for the day will show what it is, because it will be revealed with fire, and the fire will test the quality of each person's work.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If what a person has built on the foundation survives, he will receive a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If his work is burned up, he will suffer loss. However, he himself will be saved, but it will be like going through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	You know that you are God's sanctuary and that God's Spirit lives in you, don't you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If anyone destroys God's sanctuary, God will destroy him, for God's sanctuary is holy. And you are that sanctuary!
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no one deceive himself. If any of you thinks he is wise in the ways of this world, he must become a fool to become really wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is nonsense in God's sight. For it is written,	“He catches the wise with their own trickery,”
B046C003V020	46	3	20	and again,	“The Lord knows that the thoughts of the wise are worthless.”
B046C003V021	46	3	21	So let no one boast about men. For everything belongs to you,
B046C003V022	46	3	22	whether Paul, Apollos, Cephas, the world, life, death, the present, or the future—everything belongs to you,
B046C003V023	46	3	23	but you belong to Christ, and Christ belongs to God.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	A person should think of us as servants of Christ and managers entrusted with God's secrets.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	Now it is required of managers that each one should prove to be trustworthy.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	It is a very small thing to me that I should be examined by you or by any human court. In fact, I don't even examine myself.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For my conscience is clear, but that does not vindicate me. It is the Lord who examines me.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	Therefore, stop judging before the proper time, before the Lord comes, for he will bring to light what is hidden in darkness and reveal the motives of our hearts. Then each person will receive his praise from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	Brothers, I have applied all this to Apollos and myself for your benefit, so that you may learn from us not to go beyond what is written. Then you will stop boasting about one person at the expense of another.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who makes you superior? What do you have that you did not receive? And if you did receive it, why do you boast as though you did not receive it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	You already have all you want! You have already become rich! You have become kings without us! I wish you really were kings so that we could be kings with you!
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For it seems to me that God has put us apostles on display at the end of the procession, like men condemned to death. We have become a spectacle for the world, for angels, and for people to stare at.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are wise in Christ. We are weak, but you are strong. You are honored, but we are dishonored.
B046C004V011	46	4	11	To this very hour we are hungry, thirsty, dressed in rags, brutally treated, and homeless.
B046C004V012	46	4	12	We wear ourselves out from working with our own hands. When insulted, we bless. When persecuted, we endure.
B046C004V013	46	4	13	When slandered, we answer with kind words. Up to this moment we have become the filth of the world, the scum of the universe!
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I'm not writing this to make you feel ashamed, but to warn you as my dear children.
B046C004V015	46	4	15	You may have 10,000 guardians in Christ, but not many fathers. For in Christ Jesus I became your father through the gospel.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	So I urge you to become imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	That's why I sent Timothy to you. He is my dear and dependable child in the Lord and will help you remember my way of life in Christ Jesus as I teach it everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	Some of you have become arrogant, as though I were not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I will come to you soon if it's the Lord's will. Then I'll discover not only what these arrogant people are saying but also what power they have,
B046C004V020	46	4	20	for the kingdom of God isn't just talk but power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	Which do you prefer? Should I come to you with a stick, or in love and with a gentle spirit?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	It is actually reported that sexual immorality exists among you, and of a kind that is not found even among the Gentiles. A man is actually living with his father's wife!
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you are being arrogant instead of being filled with grief and seeing to it that the man who did this is removed from among you.
B046C005V003	46	5	3	Even though I am away from you physically, I am with you in spirit. I have already passed judgment on the man who did this, as though I were present with you.
B046C005V004	46	5	4	When you are gathered together in the name of our Lord Jesus and my spirit and the power of our Lord Jesus are present,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	hand this man over to Satan for the destruction of his flesh, so that his spirit may be saved on the Day of the Lord.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is not good. You know that a little yeast leavens the whole batch of dough, don't you?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Get rid of the old yeast so that you may be a new batch of dough, since you are to be free from yeast. For Christ, our Passover lamb, has been sacrificed.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	So let us keep celebrating the festival, not with the old yeast or with the yeast of vice and wickedness, but with the bread of purity and truth that has no yeast.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in my letter to stop associating with people who are sexually immoral—
B046C005V010	46	5	10	not at all meaning the people of this world who are immoral, or greedy people, robbers, or idolaters. In that case you would have to leave this world.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But now I am writing to you to stop associating with any so-called brother if he is sexually immoral, greedy, an idolater, a slanderer, a drunk, or a robber. With such a person you must even stop eating.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	After all, is it my business to judge outsiders? You are to judge those who are inside, aren't you?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	God will judge outsiders. “Put that wicked man away from you.”
B046C006V001	46	6	1	When one of you has a complaint against another, does he dare to take it before the unrighteous and not before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	You know that the saints will rule the world, don't you? And if the world is going to be ruled by you, can't you handle insignificant cases?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	You know that we will rule angels, not to mention things in this life, don't you?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	So if you have cases dealing with this life, why do you appoint as judges people who have no standing in the church?
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I say this to make you feel ashamed. Has it come to this, that there is not one person among you who is wise enough to settle disagreements between brothers?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	Instead, one brother goes to court against another brother, and before unbelievers at that!
B046C006V007	46	6	7	The very fact that you have lawsuits among yourselves is already a defeat for you. Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be cheated?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	Instead, you yourselves practice doing wrong and cheating others, and brothers at that!
B046C006V009	46	6	9	You know that wicked people will not inherit the kingdom of God, don't you? Stop deceiving yourselves! Sexually immoral people, idolaters, adulterers, male prostitutes, homosexuals,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	thieves, greedy people, drunks, slanderers, and robbers will not inherit the kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	That is what some of you were! But you were washed, you were sanctified, you were justified in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ and in the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	Everything is permissible for me, but not everything is helpful. Everything is permissible for me, but I will not allow anything to control me.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Food is for the stomach, and the stomach is for food, but God will put an end to both of them. The body is not meant for sexual immorality but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	God raised the Lord, and by his power he will also raise us.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	You know that your bodies are parts of Christ, don't you? Should I take the parts of Christ and make them parts of a prostitute? Certainly not!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	You know that the person who unites himself with a prostitute becomes one body with her, don't you? For it is said, “The two will become one flesh.”
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But the person who unites himself with the Lord becomes one spirit with him.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Keep on running away from sexual immorality. Any other sin that a person commits is outside his body, but the person who sins sexually sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	You know that your body is a sanctuary of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have received from God, don't you? You do not belong to yourselves,
B046C006V020	46	6	20	because you were bought for a price. Therefore, glorify God with your bodies.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	Now concerning the things you wrote about: It's good for a man not to touch a woman.
B046C007V002	46	7	2	But because sexual immorality is so rampant, every man should have his own wife, and every woman should have her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	A husband should fulfill his obligation to his wife, and a wife should do the same for her husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	A wife does not have authority over her own body, but her husband does. In the same way, a husband doesn't have authority over his own body, but his wife does.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not withhold yourselves from each other unless you agree to do so for a set time in order to devote yourselves to prayer. Then you should come together again so that Satan does not tempt you through your lack of self-control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But I say this as a concession, not as a command.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	I would like everyone to be like me. However, each person has a special gift from God, one this and another that.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	I say to those who are unmarried, especially to widows: It is good for them to remain like me.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	However, if they cannot control themselves, they should get married, for it is better to marry than to burn with passion.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	To married people I give this command (not really I, but the Lord): A wife must not leave her husband.
B046C007V011	46	7	11	But if she does leave him, she must remain unmarried or else be reconciled to her husband. Likewise, a husband must not abandon his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	I (not the Lord) say to the rest of you: If a brother has a wife who is an unbeliever and she is willing to live with him, he must not abandon her.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And if a woman has a husband who is an unbeliever and he is willing to live with her, she must not abandon him.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband has been sanctified because of his wife, and the unbelieving wife has been sanctified because of her husband. Otherwise, your children would be unclean, but now they are holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if the unbelieving partner leaves, let him go. In such cases the brother or sister is not bound; God has called you to live in peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	Wife, how do you know whether you will save your husband? Husband, how do you know whether you will save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	Nevertheless, everyone should live the life that the Lord gave him and to which God called him. This is my rule in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was anyone circumcised when he was called? He should not try to change that. Was anyone uncircumcised when he was called? He should not get circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but obeying God's commandments is everything.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Everyone should stay in the calling in which he was called.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you a slave when you were called? Do not let that bother you. Of course, if you have a chance to become free, take advantage of the opportunity.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For the slave who has been called in the Lord is the Lord's free person. In the same way, the free person who has been called is Christ's slave.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought for a price. Stop becoming slaves of people.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Brothers, everyone should stay in the calling he was in when called by God.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	Now concerning virgins, although I do not have any command from the Lord, I will give you my opinion as one who by the Lord's mercy is trustworthy.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	In view of the present crisis, I think it is prudent for a man to stay as he is.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Have you been bound to a wife? Stop trying to get free. Have you been freed from a wife? Stop looking for a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But if you do get married, you have not sinned. And if a virgin gets married, she has not sinned. However, these people will experience distress in the flesh, and I want to spare you that.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	This is what I mean, brothers: The time has been shortened. From now on, those who have wives should live as though they had none,
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and those who mourn as though they did not mourn, and those who rejoice as though they were not rejoicing, and those who buy as though they did not own a thing,
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and those who use the things in the world as though they were not dependent on them. For the world in its present form is passing away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	I want you to be free from concerns. An unmarried man is concerned about the affairs of the Lord, that is, about how he can please the Lord.
B046C007V033	46	7	33	But a married man is concerned about the affairs of this world, that is, about how he can please his wife,
B046C007V034	46	7	34	and so his attention is divided. An unmarried woman or virgin is concerned about the affairs of the Lord, so that she may be holy in body and spirit. But a married woman is concerned about the affairs of this world, that is, about how she can please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	I'm saying this for your benefit, not to put a noose around your necks, but to promote good order and unhindered devotion to the Lord.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	If a man thinks he is not behaving properly toward his virgin, and if his passion is too strong and he feels he ought to, let him do what he wants; he isn't sinning. Let them get married.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	However, if a man stands firm in his resolve and feels no necessity but has made up his mind to keep her a virgin, he will be acting appropriately.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So then the man who marries the virgin acts appropriately, but the man who refrains from marriage does even better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	A wife is bound to her husband as long as he lives. But if her husband dies, she is free to marry anyone she wishes, only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	However, in my opinion she will be happier if she stays as she is. And I think that I, too, have God's Spirit.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	Now concerning food offered to idols: We know that we all possess knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	If anyone thinks he knows something, he has not yet learned it as he ought to know it.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	But if anyone loves God, he is known by him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Now concerning eating food offered to idols: We know that no idol is real in the world and that there is only one God.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For even if there are “gods” in heaven and on earth (as indeed there are many so-called “gods” and “lords”),
B046C008V006	46	8	6	yet for us there is only one God, the Father, from whom everything came into being and for whom we live. And there is only one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom everything came into being and through whom we live.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	But not everyone has this knowledge. Some people are so accustomed to idols that they still think they are eating food offered to an idol, and since their conscience is weak, it becomes contaminated.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	However, food will not bring us closer to God. We are no worse off if we do not eat, and no better off if we do.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But you must see to it that this right of yours does not become a stumbling block to the weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if anyone with a weak conscience sees you who have this knowledge eating in an idol's temple, he will be encouraged to eat what has been offered to idols, won't he?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	In that case, the weak brother for whom Christ died is destroyed by your knowledge.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	When you sin against your brothers in this way and wound their weak consciences, you are sinning against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Therefore, if food causes my brother to fall, I will never eat meat again, in order to keep my brother from falling.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	I am free, am I not? I am an apostle, am I not? I have seen Jesus our Lord, haven't I? You are my work in the Lord, aren't you?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If I am not an apostle to other people, surely I am one to you, for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord!
B046C009V003	46	9	3	This is my defense to those who would examine me:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	We have the right to eat and drink, don't we?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	We have the right to take a believing wife with us like the other apostles, the Lord's brothers, and Cephas, don't we?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or is it only Barnabas and I who have no right to refrain from working for a living?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who would ever go to war at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat any of its grapes? Or who takes care of a flock and does not drink any of its milk?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	I am not saying this on human authority, am I? The law says the same thing, doesn't it?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For in the law of Moses it is written, “You must not muzzle an ox while it is treading out the grain.” God is not only concerned about oxen, is he?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	Isn't he really speaking on our behalf? Yes, this was written on our behalf, because the one who plows should plow in hope, and the one who threshes should thresh in hope of sharing in the crop.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we have sown spiritual seed among you, is it too much if we reap material benefits from you?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others enjoy this right over you, don't we have a stronger claim? But we did not use this right. On the contrary, we put up with everything in order not to put an obstacle in the way of the gospel of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	You know that those who work in the temple get their food from the temple and that those who serve at the altar get their share of its offerings, don't you?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	In the same way, the Lord has ordered that those who proclaim the gospel should make their living from the gospel.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I have not used any of these rights, and I'm not writing this so that they may be applied in my case. I would rather die than let anyone deprive me of my reason for boasting.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For if I preach the gospel, I have nothing to boast about, for this obligation has been laid on me. How terrible it would be for me if I didn't preach the gospel!
B046C009V017	46	9	17	For if I do this voluntarily, I get a reward, but if I am unwilling to do it, I am still entrusted with an obligation.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What, then, is my reward? It's to be able to preach the gospel free of charge, and so never resort to using my rights in the gospel.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	Although I am free from all people, I made myself a slave to all of them to win more of them.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	To the Jews I became like a Jew in order to win Jews. To those under the law I became like a man under the law, in order to win those under the law (although I myself am not under the law).
B046C009V021	46	9	21	To those who do not have the law I became like a man who does not have the law, in order to win those who do not have the law (although I am not free from God's law, but am under the law of Christ).
B046C009V022	46	9	22	To the weak I became weak in order to win the weak. I have become all things to all people so that by all possible means I might save some of them.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	I do all this for the sake of the gospel in order to have a share in its blessings.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	You know that in a race all the runners run but only one wins the prize, don't you? You must run in such a way that you may be victorious.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	Everyone who enters an athletic contest practices self-control in everything. They do it to win a wreath that dies, but we to win one that never dies.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	That is the way I run, with a clear goal in mind. That is the way I box, not like someone punching the air.
B046C009V027	46	9	27	No, I keep on beating my body and making it my slave so that, after I have preached to others, I myself will not somehow be disqualified.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	For I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, of the fact that all of our ancestors were under the cloud, and they all went through the sea,
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and they all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea,
B046C010V003	46	10	3	and they all ate the same spiritual food,
B046C010V004	46	10	4	and they all drank the same spiritual drink, for they continually drank from the spiritual Rock that went with them, and that Rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	But God wasn't pleased with most of them, and so they were struck down in the wilderness.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	Now these things became examples for us so that we won't set our hearts on evil as they did.
B046C010V007	46	10	7	Let us stop being idolaters, as some of them were. As it is written, “The people sat down to eat and drink and got up to play.”
B046C010V008	46	10	8	Let us stop sinning sexually, as some of them were doing, and on a single day 23,000 fell dead.
B046C010V009	46	10	9	Let us stop putting the Lord to the test, as some of them were doing, and were destroyed by snakes.
B046C010V010	46	10	10	You must stop complaining, as some of them were doing, and were destroyed by the destroying angel.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	These things happened to them to serve as an example, and they were written down as a warning for us in whom the climax of the ages has been realized.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	Therefore, the person who thinks he is standing securely should watch out that he does not fall.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	No temptation has overtaken you that is unusual for human beings. But God is faithful, and he will not allow you to be tempted beyond your strength. Instead, along with the temptation he will also provide a way out, so that you may be able to endure it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	And so, my dear friends, keep on running away from idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I am talking to sensible people. Decide for yourselves what I am saying.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing that we bless is a sign of our sharing in the blood of Christ, isn't it? The bread that we break is a sign of our sharing in the body of Christ, isn't it?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because there is one loaf, we who are many are one body, because all of us partake of the one loaf.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Look at the Israelites from a human point of view. Those who eat the sacrifices share in what is on the altar, don't they?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	Am I suggesting that an offering made to idols means anything, or that an idol itself means anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	Hardly! What they offer, they offer to demons and not to God, and I do not want you to become partners with demons.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot eat at the table of the Lord and at the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Are we trying to provoke the Lord to jealousy? We are not stronger than he is, are we?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	Everything is permissible, but not everything is helpful. Everything is permissible, but not everything builds up.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	No one should seek his own welfare, but rather his neighbor's.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Eat anything that is sold in the meat market without raising any question about it on the ground of conscience,
B046C010V026	46	10	26	for “the earth and everything in it belong to the Lord.”
B046C010V027	46	10	27	If an unbeliever invites you to his house and you wish to go, eat whatever is set before you, raising no question on the ground of conscience.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	However, if someone says to you, “This was offered in sacrifice,” don't eat it, both out of consideration for the one who told you and because of conscience.
B046C010V029	46	10	29	I mean, of course, his conscience, not yours. For why should my freedom be judged by someone else's conscience?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	If I eat with thankfulness, why should I be denounced because of what I am thankful for?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Therefore, whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do everything to the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Stop being stumbling blocks to Jews or Greeks or to the church of God,
B046C010V033	46	10	33	just as I myself try to please everybody in every way, not looking for my own advantage but for that of many people, so that they might be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Be imitators of me, as I am of Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	I praise you for remembering me in everything and for carefully following the traditions, just as I passed them on to you.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	Now I want you to realize that Christ is the head of every man, and man is the head of the woman, and God is the head of Christ.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man who prays or prophesies with something on his head dishonors his head,
B046C011V005	46	11	5	and every woman who prays or prophesies with her head uncovered dishonors her head, which is the same as having her head shaved.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	So if a woman does not cover her head, she should cut off her hair. If it is a disgrace for a woman to cut off her hair or shave her head, let her cover her own head.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	A man should not cover his own head, because he exists as God's image and glory. But the woman is man's glory.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For man did not come from woman, but woman from man;
B046C011V009	46	11	9	and man was not created for woman, but woman for man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	This is why a woman should have authority over her own head: because of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	In the Lord, however, woman is not independent of man, nor is man of woman.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as woman came from man, so man comes through woman. But everything comes from God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Decide for yourselves: Is it proper for a woman to pray to God with her head uncovered?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Nature itself teaches you neither that it is disgraceful for a man to have long hair
B046C011V015	46	11	15	nor that hair is a woman's glory, for hair is given as a substitute for coverings.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if anyone wants to argue about this, we do not have any custom like this, nor do any of God's churches.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	Now I am not praising you in giving you the following instructions. When you gather, it is not for the better but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For in the first place, I hear that when you gather as a church there are divisions among you, and I partly believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	Of course, there must be factions among you to show which of you are genuine!
B046C011V020	46	11	20	When you gather in the same place, it is not to eat the Lord's Supper.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For as you eat, each of you rushes to eat his own supper, and one person goes hungry while another gets drunk.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	You have homes in which to eat and drink, don't you? Or do you despise God's church and humiliate those who have nothing? What should I say to you? Should I praise you? I will not praise you for this!
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I received from the Lord what I also passed on to you—how the Lord Jesus, on the night he was betrayed, took a loaf of bread,
B046C011V024	46	11	24	gave thanks for it, and broke it in pieces, saying,
B046C011V025	46	11	25	He did the same with the cup after the supper, saying,
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread and drink from this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Therefore, whoever eats the bread or drinks from the cup in an unworthy manner will be held responsible for the Lord's body and blood.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	A person must examine himself and then eat the bread and drink from the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For the one who eats and drinks without recognizing the body eats and drinks judgment on himself.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	That's why so many of you are weak and sick and a considerable number are dying.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	But if we judged ourselves correctly, we would not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	Now, while we are being judged by the Lord, we are being disciplined lest we be condemned along with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	Therefore, my brothers, when you gather to eat, wait for each other.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	If anyone is hungry, he should eat at home, so that when you gather it may not bring judgment on you. And when I come I will give instructions concerning the other matters.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers, I don't want you to be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	You know that when you were Gentiles, you were enticed and led away to idols that couldn't even speak.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore, I want you to know that no one who is speaking by God's Spirit can say, “Jesus is cursed,” and no one can say, “Jesus is Lord,” except by the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now there are varieties of gifts, but the Spirit is the same;
B046C012V005	46	12	5	and there are varieties of ministries, but the Lord is the same;
B046C012V006	46	12	6	and there are varieties of results, but God is the same, and it is he who produces all the results in everyone.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	To each person has been given the ability to display the Spirit for the common good.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	To one has been given a message of wisdom by the Spirit; to another the ability to speak with knowledge according to the same Spirit;
B046C012V009	46	12	9	to another faith by the same Spirit; to another gifts of healing by that one Spirit;
B046C012V010	46	12	10	to another miraculous results; to another prophecy; to another the ability to distinguish between spirits; to another various kinds of tongues; and to another the interpretation of tongues.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But one and the same Spirit produces all these results and gives what he wants to each person.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For just as the body is one and yet has many parts, and all the parts of the body, though many, form one body, so it is with Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For by one Spirit all of us—Jews and Greeks, slaves and free—were baptized into one body and were all privileged to drink from one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body does not consist of only one part, but of many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot says, “Since I'm not a hand, I'm not part of the body,” that does not make it any less a part of the body, does it?
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear says, “Since I'm not an eye, I'm not part of the body,” that does not make it any less a part of the body, does it?
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body were an eye, where would the sense of hearing be? If the whole body were an ear, where would the sense of smell be?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But at this very time God has arranged the parts, every one of them, in the body just as he wanted to.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	Now if they were all one part, where would the body be?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	So there are many parts, but one body.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	The eye cannot say to the hand, “I don't need you,” or the head to the feet, “I don't need you.”
B046C012V022	46	12	22	On the contrary, those parts of the body that seem to be weaker are in fact indispensable,
B046C012V023	46	12	23	and the parts of the body that we think are less honorable are treated with special honor, and we make our less attractive parts more attractive.
B046C012V024	46	12	24	However, our attractive parts don't need this. But God has put the body together and has given special honor to the parts that lack it,
B046C012V025	46	12	25	so that there might be no disharmony in the body, but that its parts should have the same concern for each other.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	If one part suffers, every part suffers with it. If one part is praised, every part rejoices with it.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	Now you are Christ's body and individual parts of it.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	God has appointed in the church first of all apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then those who perform miracles, those who have gifts of healing, those who help others, administrators, and various kinds of tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Not all are apostles, are they? Not all are prophets, are they? Not all are teachers, are they? Not all perform miracles, do they?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Not all have the gift of healing, do they? Not all speak in tongues, do they? Not all interpret, do they?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	Keep on desiring the better gifts. And now I will show you the best way of all.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	If I speak in the tongues of humans and angels but have no love, I have become a reverberating gong or a clashing cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	If I have the gift of prophecy and can understand all secrets and every form of knowledge, and if I have absolute faith so as to move mountains but have no love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	Even if I give away all that I have and surrender my body so that I may boast but have no love, I get nothing out of it.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is always patient,	Love is always kind,	Love is never envious	Or vaunted up with pride.	Nor is she conceited,
B046C013V005	46	13	5	And never is she rude,	Never does she think of self	Or ever get annoyed.	She never is resentful,
B046C013V006	46	13	6	Is never glad with sin,	But always glad to side with truth,	Whene'er the truth should win.
B046C013V007	46	13	7	She bears up under everything,	Believes the best in all,	There is no limit to her hope,	And never will she fall.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never fails. Now if there are prophecies, they will be done away with. If there are tongues, they will cease. If there is knowledge, it will be done away with.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	For what we know is incomplete and what we prophesy is incomplete.
B046C013V010	46	13	10	But when what is complete comes, then what is incomplete will be done away with.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I spoke like a child, thought like a child, and reasoned like a child. When I became a man, I gave up my childish ways.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	Now we see only a blurred reflection in a mirror, but then we will see face to face. Now what I know is incomplete, but then I will know fully, even as I have been fully known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	Right now three things remain: faith, hope, and love. But the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Keep on pursuing love, and keep on desiring spiritual gifts, especially the ability to prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For the person who speaks in a tongue does not speak to people but to God. Indeed, no one understands him, because he is speaking secrets in the Spirit.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But the person who prophesies speaks to people for their upbuilding, encouragement, and comfort.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	The person who speaks in a tongue builds himself up, but the person who prophesies builds the church up.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	Now I wish that all of you could speak in tongues, but especially that you could prophesy. The person who prophesies is more important than the person who speaks in a tongue, unless he interprets it so that the church may be built up.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	Indeed, brothers, if I come to you speaking in tongues, what good will I be to you unless I speak to you in some revelation, knowledge, prophecy, or teaching?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	In the same way, lifeless instruments like the flute or harp produce sounds. But if there's no difference in the notes, how can a person tell what tune is being played?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	For example, if a bugle doesn't sound a clear call, who will get ready for battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	In the same way, unless you speak an intelligible message with your tongue, how will anyone know what is being said? You'll be talking into the air!
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are, I suppose, many different languages in the world, yet none of them is without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	If I don't know the meaning of the language, I will be a foreigner to the speaker and the speaker will be a foreigner to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	In the same way, since you're so desirous of spiritual gifts, you must keep on desiring them for the upbuilding of the church.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore, the person who speaks in a tongue should pray for the ability to interpret it.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays but my mind is not productive.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What does this mean? I will pray with my spirit, but I will also pray with my mind. I will sing psalms with my spirit, but I will also sing psalms with my mind.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	Otherwise, if you say a blessing with your spirit, how can an otherwise uneducated person say “Amen” to your thanksgiving, since he does not know what you're saying?
B046C014V017	46	14	17	It's good for you to give thanks, but it does not build up the other person.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I thank God that I speak in tongues more than all of you.
B046C014V019	46	14	19	But in church I would rather speak five words with my mind to instruct others than 10,000 words in a tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brothers, stop being children in your thinking. In evil be infants, but in thinking be adults.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written,	“Through people of strange tonguesand through the mouths of foreigners	I will speak to this people,but even then they will not listen to me,”declares the Lord.
B046C014V022	46	14	22	Tongues, then, are meant to be a sign, not for believers, but for unbelievers, while prophecy is meant, not for unbelievers, but for believers.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	Now if the whole church gathers in the same place and everyone is speaking in tongues, when uneducated people or unbelievers come in, they will say that you are out of your mind, won't they?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if everyone is prophesying, when an unbeliever or an uneducated person comes in he will be convicted by all and examined by all.
B046C014V025	46	14	25	The secrets in his heart will become known, and so he will bow down to the ground and worship God, declaring, “God is truly among you!”
B046C014V026	46	14	26	What, then, does this mean, brothers? When you gather, everyone has a psalm, teaching, revelation, tongue, or interpretation. Everything must be done for upbuilding.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If anyone speaks in a tongue, only two or three at the most should do so, one at a time, and somebody must interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	If an interpreter is not present, he should remain silent in the church and speak to himself and God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Two or three prophets should speak, and the others should weigh carefully what is said.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	If a revelation is made to another person who is seated, the first person should be silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For everyone can prophesy in turn, so that everyone can be instructed and everyone can be encouraged.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	The spirits of prophets are subject to the prophets,
B046C014V033	46	14	33	for God is not a God of disorder but of peace.As in all the churches of the saints,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	the women must keep silent in the churches. They are not allowed to speak out, but must place themselves in submission, as the law also says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	If they want to learn anything, they should ask their own husbands at home, for it is inappropriate for a woman to speak out in church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	Did God's word originate with you? Are you the only people it has reached?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If anyone thinks he is a prophet or a spiritual person, he must acknowledge that what I am writing to you is the Lord's command.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if anyone ignores this, he should be ignored.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	Therefore, my brothers, desire the ability to prophesy, and do not prevent others from speaking in tongues.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	But everything must be done in a proper and orderly way.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	Now I'm making known to you, brothers, the gospel that I proclaimed to you, which you accepted, on which you have taken your stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	and by which you are also being saved if you hold firmly to the message I proclaimed to you—unless, of course, your faith was worthless.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I passed on to you the most important points of what I received: Christ died for our sins in keeping with the Scriptures,
B046C015V004	46	15	4	he was buried, he was raised on the third day in keeping with the Scriptures—and is still alive!—
B046C015V005	46	15	5	and he was seen by Cephas, and then by the twelve.
B046C015V006	46	15	6	After that, he was seen by more than 500 brothers at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have died.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	Next he was seen by James, then by all the apostles,
B046C015V008	46	15	8	and finally he was seen by me, as though I were born abnormally late.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles and not even fit to be called an apostle because I persecuted God's church.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by God's grace I am what I am, and his grace shown to me was not wasted. Instead, I worked harder than all the others—not I, of course, but God's grace that was with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	So, whether it was I or they, this is what we preach, and this is what you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	Now if we preach that Christ has been raised from the dead, how can some of you keep claiming there is no resurrection of the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	If there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised,
B046C015V014	46	15	14	and if Christ has not been raised, then our message means nothing and your faith means nothing.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	In addition, we are found to be false witnesses about God because we testified on God's behalf that he raised Christ—whom he did not raise if in fact it is true that the dead are not raised.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, then Christ has not been raised,
B046C015V017	46	15	17	and if Christ has not been raised, your faith is worthless and you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	Yes, even those who have died in Christ are lost.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If we have set our hopes on Christ in this life only, we deserve more pity than any other people.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But at this moment Christ stands risen from the dead, the first one offered in the harvest of those who have died.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since death came through a man, the resurrection of the dead also came through a man.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ will all be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	However, this will happen to each person in the proper order: first Christ, then those who belong to Christ when he comes.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	Then the end will come, when he hands over the kingdom to God the Father after he has done away with every ruler and every authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For he must rule until God puts all his enemies under his feet.
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy to be done away with is death,
B046C015V027	46	15	27	for “God has put everything under his feet.” Now when he says, “Everything has been put under him,” this clearly excludes the one who put everything under him.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	But when everything has been put under him, then the Son himself will also become subject to the one who put everything under him, so that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Otherwise, what will those people do who are being baptized for the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why are they being baptized for them?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why in fact are we being endangered every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I face death every day! That is as certain, brothers, as it is that I am proud of you in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If I have fought with wild animals in Ephesus from merely human motives, what do I get out of it? If the dead are not raised,	“Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.”
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Stop being deceived:	“Wicked friends lead to evil ends.”
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Come back to your senses as you should, and stop sinning! For some of you—I say this to your shame—are without a true knowledge of God.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But someone will ask, “How are the dead raised? What kind of body will they have when they come back?”
B046C015V036	46	15	36	You fool! The seed you plant does not come to life unless it dies,
B046C015V037	46	15	37	and what you plant is not the form that it will be, but a bare kernel, whether it is wheat or something else.
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives the plant the form he wants it to have, and to each kind of seed its own form.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	Not all flesh is the same. Humans have one kind of flesh, animals in general have another, birds have another, and fish have still another.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	There are heavenly bodies and earthly bodies, but the splendor of those in heaven is of one kind, and that of those on earth is of another.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	One kind of splendor belongs to the sun, another to the moon, and still another to the stars. In fact, one star differs from another star in splendor.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	This is how it will be at the resurrection of the dead. What is planted is decaying, what is raised cannot decay.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	The body is planted in dishonor but raised in splendor. It is planted in weakness but raised in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is planted a physical body but raised a spiritual body. If there is a physical body, there is also a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	This, indeed, is what is written: “The first man, Adam, became a living being.” The last Adam became a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	The spiritual does not come first, but the physical and then the spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man came from the dust of the earth; the second man came from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	Those who are made of the dust are like the man from the dust, those who are heavenly are like the man who is from heaven.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	Just as we have borne the likeness of the man who was made from dust, we will also bear the likeness of the man from heaven.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	Brothers, this is what I mean: Flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God, and what decays cannot inherit what does not decay.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Let me tell you a secret. Not all of us will die, but all of us will be changed—
B046C015V052	46	15	52	in a moment, in the blinking of an eye, at the sound of the last trumpet. Indeed, that trumpet will sound, and then the dead will be raised never to decay, and we will be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For what is decaying must put on what cannot decay, and what is dying must put on what cannot die.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	Now, when what is decaying puts on what cannot decay, and what is dying puts on what cannot die, then the saying that is written will be fulfilled: “Death has been swallowed up in victory!”
B046C015V055	46	15	55	“Where, O death, is your victory?Where, O death, is your sting?”
B046C015V056	46	15	56	Now the sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!
B046C015V058	46	15	58	Therefore, my dear brothers, be steadfast, unmovable, always excelling in the work of the Lord, because you know that your work isn't wasted in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	Now concerning the collection for the saints, you should follow the directions I gave to the churches in Galatia.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On the first day of the week, each of you should set aside and save some of your money in proportion to what you have, so that no collections will have to be made when I come.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	When I arrive, I will send with letters the men you approve to take your gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	If it is worthwhile for me to go, too, they can go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	I will visit you when I go through Macedonia—for I intend to go through Macedonia—
B046C016V006	46	16	6	and will probably stay with you or even spend the winter. Then you can send me on my way, wherever I decide to go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	I do not want to see you now just in passing, because I hope to spend some time with you if the Lord permits.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	However, I will be staying on in Ephesus until Pentecost,
B046C016V009	46	16	9	because a door has opened wide for me to do effective work, although many people are opposing me.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	If Timothy comes, see to it that he does not have anything to be afraid of while he is with you, for he is doing the Lord's work as I am.
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Therefore, no one should treat him with contempt. Send him on his way in peace so that he may come to me, because I am expecting him along with the brothers.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	Now concerning our brother Apollos, I strongly urged him to visit you with the other brothers, but he was not inclined to go just now. However, he will come when the time is right.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Remain alert. Keep standing firm in your faith. Keep on being courageous and strong.
B046C016V014	46	16	14	Everything you do should be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	Now I urge you, brothers—for you know that the members of the family of Stephanas were the first converts in Achaia, and that they have devoted themselves to serving the saints—
B046C016V016	46	16	16	to submit yourselves to people like these and to anyone else who shares their labor and hard work.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	I am glad that Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus came here, because they have supplied what was lacking from you.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	They refreshed my spirit—and yours, too. Therefore, appreciate men like that.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches in Asia greet you. Aquila and Prisca and the church in their house greet you warmly in the Lord.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.,
B046C016V021	46	16	21	I, Paul, am writing this greeting with my own hand.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If anyone doesn't love the Lord, let him be condemned! May our Lord come!
B046C016V023	46	16	23	May the grace of the Lord Jesus be with you!
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love is with all of you in Christ Jesus.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and Timothy our brother, to the church of God that is in Corinth, with all the holy people throughout Achaia.
B047C001V002	47	1	2	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ! He is the Father of mercies and the God of all comfort,
B047C001V004	47	1	4	who comforts us in all our suffering, so that we may be able to comfort others in all their suffering, since we ourselves are being comforted by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	For just as Christ's sufferings overflow to us, so our comfort overflows through Christ.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	If we suffer, it is for your comfort and salvation. If we are comforted, it is for your comfort when you patiently endure the same sufferings that we are suffering.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	Our hope for you is unshaken, because we know that as you share our sufferings, you also share our comfort.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, about the suffering we experienced in Asia. We were so crushed beyond our ability to endure that we even despaired of living.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	In fact, we felt within ourselves that we had received the sentence of death, so that we would not rely on ourselves but on the God who raises the dead.
B047C001V010	47	1	10	He has rescued us from a terrible death, and he will continue to rescue us. Yes, the one on whom we have set our hope will rescue us again,
B047C001V011	47	1	11	as you also help us by your prayers on our behalf. Then prayers of thanksgiving will be uttered by many people on our behalf because of the favor shown us through the prayers of many.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For this is what we boast about: Our conscience testifies that we have conducted ourselves in the world with pure motives and godly sincerity, without earthly wisdom but with God's grace—and especially towards you.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For what we are writing you is nothing more than what you can read and also understand. I hope you will understand completely,
B047C001V014	47	1	14	just as you have already understood us partially, so that on the day of our Lord Jesus we can be your reason to boast, even as you are ours.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	It was because of this confidence that I planned to come to you first, so that you might receive a double blessing.
B047C001V016	47	1	16	I planned to leave you in order to go to Macedonia, and then come back to you from Macedonia, and let you send me on to Judea.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	When I planned this, I did not do it lightly, did I? Are my plans so fickle that I can say “Yes” and “No” at the same time?
B047C001V018	47	1	18	As certainly as God is faithful, our word to you is not “Yes” and “No.”
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For God's Son, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us—by me, Silvanus, and Timothy—was not “Yes” and “No.” But with him it is always “Yes.”
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For all God's promises are “Yes” in him. And so through him we can say “Amen,” to the glory of God.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	Now the one who makes us—and you as well—secure in union with Christ and has anointed us is God,
B047C001V022	47	1	22	who has placed his seal on us and has given us the Spirit in our hearts as a down payment.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	I call upon God as a witness on my behalf that it was in order to spare you that I did not return to Corinth.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	It is not that we are trying to lord it over your faith. On the contrary, we are workers with you to promote your joy, because you have been standing firm in the faith.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	Now I decided not to pay you another painful visit.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	After all, if I were to grieve you, who should make me happy but the person I am making sad?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	This is the very reason I wrote you, so that when I did come I might not be made sad by those who should have made me happy. For I had confidence in all of you that my gladness would be for all of you.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For I wrote to you out of great sorrow and anguish of heart—along with many tears—not to make you sad but to let you know how much love I have for you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if anyone has caused grief, he didn't cause me any grief. To some extent—I don't want to emphasize this too much—it has affected all of you.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	This punishment by the majority is severe enough for such a man.
B047C002V007	47	2	7	So forgive and comfort him, or else he will drown in his excessive grief.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	That's why I'm urging you to assure him of your love.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	I had also written to you to see if you would stand the test and be obedient in every way.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	When you forgive someone, I do, too. Indeed, what I have forgiven—if there was anything to forgive—I did in the presence of Christ for your benefit,
B047C002V011	47	2	11	so that we may not be outsmarted by Satan. After all, we are not unaware of his intentions.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	When I went to Troas on behalf of the gospel of Christ, a door in fact stood wide open for me in the Lord.
B047C002V013	47	2	13	But my spirit could not find any relief, because I couldn't find Titus, my brother. So I said goodbye to them and went on to Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	But thanks be to God! He always leads us triumphantly in Christ and through us spreads everywhere the fragrance of knowing him.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	To God we are the aroma of Christ among those who are being saved and among those who are being lost.
B047C002V016	47	2	16	To some people we are a deadly fragrance, while to others we are a living fragrance. Who is qualified for this?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	At least we are not commercializing God's word like so many others. Instead, in Christ we speak with sincerity, like people who are sent from God and are accountable to God.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Are we beginning to recommend ourselves again? Unlike some people, we do not need letters of recommendation to you or from you, do we?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, written in our hearts and known and read by everyone.
B047C003V003	47	3	3	You are demonstrating that you are Christ's letter, produced by our service, written not with ink but with the Spirit of the living God, not on tablets of stone but on tablets of human hearts.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	Such is the confidence that we have in God through Christ.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	By ourselves we are not qualified to claim that anything comes from us. Rather, our credentials come from God,
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who has also qualified us to be ministers of a new covenant, which is not written but spiritual, because the written text brings death, but the Spirit gives life.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	Now if the ministry of death that was inscribed in letters of stone came with such glory that the people of Israel could not gaze on Moses’ face (because the glory was fading away from it),
B047C003V008	47	3	8	will not the Spirit's ministry have even more glory?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the ministry of condemnation has glory, then the ministry of justification has an overwhelming glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	In fact, that which once had glory lost its glory, because the other glory surpassed it.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if that which fades away came through glory, how much more does that which is permanent have glory?
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Therefore, since we have such a hope, we speak with great boldness,
B047C003V013	47	3	13	not like Moses, who kept covering his face with a veil to keep the people of Israel from gazing at the end of what was fading away.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	However, their minds were hardened, for to this day the same veil is still there when they read the old covenant. Only in union with Christ is that veil removed.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	Yet even to this day, when Moses is read, a veil covers their hearts.
B047C003V016	47	3	16	But whenever a person turns to the Lord, the veil is removed.
B047C003V017	47	3	17	Now the Lord is the Spirit, and where the Lord's Spirit is, there is freedom.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	As all of us reflect the glory of the Lord with unveiled faces, we are being transformed into the same image with ever-increasing glory by the Lord's Spirit.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	Therefore, since we have this ministry through the mercy shown to us, we do not get discouraged.
B047C004V002	47	4	2	Instead, we have renounced secret and shameful ways. We do not use trickery or pervert God's word. By clear statements of the truth we commend ourselves to everyone's conscience before God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	So if our gospel is veiled, it is veiled to those who are dying.
B047C004V004	47	4	4	In their case, the god of this world has blinded the minds of those who do not believe to keep them from seeing the light of the glorious gospel of Christ, who is the image of God.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we do not preach ourselves but Jesus Christ as Lord, and ourselves as merely your servants for Jesus’ sake.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	For God, who said, “Let light shine out of darkness,” has shone in our hearts to give us the light of the knowledge of God's glory in the face of Jesus Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in clay jars to show that its extraordinary power comes from God and not from us.
B047C004V008	47	4	8	In every way we're troubled but not crushed, frustrated but not in despair,
B047C004V009	47	4	9	persecuted but not abandoned, struck down but not destroyed.
B047C004V010	47	4	10	We are always carrying around the death of Jesus in our bodies, so that the life of Jesus may be clearly shown in our bodies.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	While we are alive, we are constantly being handed over to death for Jesus’ sake, so that the life of Jesus may be clearly shown in our dying bodies.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	And so death is at work in us, but life is at work in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	Now since we have the same spirit of faith in keeping with what is written—“I believed, and so I spoke”—we also believe, and so we speak.
B047C004V014	47	4	14	We know that the one who raised the Lord Jesus will also raise us with Jesus and present us to God together with you.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	All this is for your sake so that, as his grace spreads, it will increase the thanksgiving of more and more people to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	That's why we are not discouraged. No, even if our outer man is wearing out, our inner man is being renewed day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	This light, temporary nature of our suffering is producing for us an eternal weight of glory, far beyond any comparison,
B047C004V018	47	4	18	because we do not look for things that can be seen but for things that cannot be seen. For things that can be seen are temporary, but things that cannot be seen are eternal.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	We know that if the earthly tent we live in is torn down, we have a building in heaven that comes from God, an eternal house not built by human hands.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For in this one we sigh, since we long to put on our heavenly dwelling.
B047C005V003	47	5	3	Of course, if we do put it on, we will not be found without a body.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	So while we are still in this tent, we sigh under our burdens, because we do not want to put it off but to put it on, so that our dying bodies may be swallowed up by life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	God has prepared us for this and has given us his Spirit as a guarantee.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	Therefore, we are always confident, and we know that as long as we are at home in this body we are away from the Lord.
B047C005V007	47	5	7	For we live by faith, not by sight.
B047C005V008	47	5	8	We are confident, then, and would prefer to be away from this body and to live with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	So whether we are at home or away from home, our goal is to be pleasing to him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For all of us must appear before the judgment seat of Christ, so that each of us may receive what he deserves for what he has done in his body, whether good or worthless.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Therefore, since we know the fear of the Lord, we try to persuade people. We ourselves are perfectly known to God. I hope we are also really known to your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	We are not recommending ourselves to you again but are giving you a reason to be proud of us, so that you can answer those who are proud of outward things rather than inward character.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	So if we were crazy, it was for God; if we are sane, it is for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	The love of Christ controls us, for we are convinced of this: that one person died for all people; therefore, all people have died.
B047C005V015	47	5	15	He died for all people, so that those who live should no longer live for themselves but for the one who died and rose for them.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	So then, from now on we do not think of anyone from a human point of view. Even if we did think of Christ from a human point of view, we don't think of him that way any more.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. Old things have disappeared, and—look!—all things have become new!
B047C005V018	47	5	18	All of this comes from God, who has reconciled us to himself through Christ and has given us the ministry of reconciliation.
B047C005V019	47	5	19	For in Christ God was reconciling the world to himself by not counting their sins against them, and he has committed to us the message of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	Therefore, we are Christ's representatives, as though God were pleading through us. We plead on Christ's behalf: “Be reconciled to God!”
B047C005V021	47	5	21	God made the one who did not know sin to be sin for us, so that we might become God's righteousness in him.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	Since, then, we are working with God, we plead with you not to accept God's grace in vain.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	For he says,	“At the right time I heard you,			and on a day of salvation I helped you.”Listen, now is really the “right time”! Now is the “day of salvation”!
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We do not put an obstacle in anyone's way. Otherwise, fault may be found with our ministry.
B047C006V004	47	6	4	Instead, in every way we demonstrate that we are God's servants by tremendous endurance in the midst of difficulties, hardships, and calamities;
B047C006V005	47	6	5	in beatings, imprisonments, and riots; in hard work, sleepless nights, and hunger;
B047C006V006	47	6	6	with purity, knowledge, patience, and kindness; with the Holy Spirit, genuine love,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	truthful speech, and divine power; through the weapons of righteousness in the right and left hands;
B047C006V008	47	6	8	through honor and dishonor; through ill repute and good repute; perceived as deceivers and yet true,
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as unknown and yet well-known, as dying and yet—as you see—very much alive, as punished and yet not killed,
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as sorrowful and yet always rejoicing, as poor and yet enriching many, as having nothing and yet possessing everything.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	We have spoken frankly to you, Corinthians. Our hearts are wide open.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	We have not cut you off, but you have cut off your own feelings toward us.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	Do us a favor—I ask you as my children—and open wide your hearts.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Stop becoming unevenly yoked with unbelievers. What partnership can righteousness have with lawlessness? What fellowship can light have with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	What harmony exists between Christ and Beliar, or what do a believer and an unbeliever have in common?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	What agreement can a temple of God make with idols? For we are the temple of the living God, just as God said:	“I will live and walk among them.I will be their God,and they will be my people.”
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore,	“Get away from themand separate yourselves from them,”declares the Lord,	“and don't touch anything unclean.Then I will welcome you.
B047C006V018	47	6	18	I will be your Father,and you will be my sons and daughters,”declares the Lord Almighty.
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Since we have these promises, dear friends, let us cleanse ourselves from everything that contaminates body and spirit by perfecting holiness in the fear of God.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Make room for us in your hearts! We have not treated anyone unjustly, harmed anyone, or cheated anyone.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I am not saying this to condemn you. I told you before that you are in our hearts to die together and to live together.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	I have great confidence in you. I am very proud of you. I am very much encouraged. I am overjoyed in all our troubles.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For even when we came to Macedonia, our bodies had no rest. We suffered in a number of ways. Outwardly there were conflicts, inwardly there were fears.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	Yet God, who comforts those who feel miserable, comforted us by the arrival of Titus,
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not only by his arrival but also by the comfort he had received from you. He told us about your longing for me, your sorrow, and your eagerness to take my side, and this made me even happier.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	If I made you sad with my letter, I do not regret it, although I did regret it then. I see that the letter caused you sorrow, though only for a while.
B047C007V009	47	7	9	Now I am happy, not because you had such sorrow, but because your sorrow led you to repentance. For you were sorry in a godly way, and so you were not hurt by us in any way.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For having sorrow in a godly way results in repentance that leads to salvation and leaves no regrets. But the sorrow of the world produces death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	See what great earnestness godly sorrow has produced in you! How ready you are to clear yourselves, how indignant, how alarmed, how full of longing and enthusiasm, how eager to seek justice! In every way you have demonstrated that you are innocent in this matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	So, even though I wrote to you, it wasn't because of the man who did the wrong or because of the man who was hurt. Instead, I wrote to you so that your devotion to us might be made perfectly clear to you before God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	This is what comforted us. In addition to our own comfort, we were even more delighted at the joy of Titus, because his spirit had been set at rest by all of you.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	For if I have been doing some boasting about you to him, I have never been ashamed of it. Moreover, since everything we told you was true, our boasting to Titus has also proved to be true.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	His heart goes out to you even more as he remembers how obedient all of you were and how you welcomed him with fear and trembling.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I rejoice that I can have complete confidence in you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	We want you to know, brothers, about God's grace that was given to the churches of Macedonia.
B047C008V002	47	8	2	In spite of a terrible ordeal of suffering, their abundant joy, along with their deep poverty, has resulted in the abundance of their generosity.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	I can testify that by their own free will they have given to the utmost of their ability, yes, even beyond their ability.
B047C008V004	47	8	4	They begged us earnestly for the privilege of participating in this ministry to the saints.
B047C008V005	47	8	5	We did not expect that! They gave themselves to the Lord first and then to us, since this was God's will.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	So we urged Titus to finish this work of kindness among you in the same way that he had started it.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	Indeed, the more your faith, speech, knowledge, enthusiasm, and love for us increase, the more we want you to be rich in this work of kindness.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I am not commanding you but testing the genuineness of your love by the enthusiasm of others.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ. Although he was rich, for your sakes he became poor, so that you, through his poverty, might become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	I am giving you my opinion on this matter because it will be helpful to you. Last year you were not only willing to do something, but had already started to do it.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	Now finish doing it, so that your eagerness to undertake it may be matched by its completion, in keeping with what you have.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if the eagerness is there, the gift is acceptable according to what you have, not according to what you do not have.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	Not that others should have relief while you have hardship. Rather, it is a question of fairness.
B047C008V014	47	8	14	At the present time, your surplus fills their need, so that their surplus may fill your need. In this way things are fair.
B047C008V015	47	8	15	As it is written,	“The person who had much did not have too much,and the person who had little did not have too little.”
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But thanks be to God, who placed in the heart of Titus the same dedication to you that I have.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	He welcomed my request and eagerly went to visit you by his own free will.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	With him we have sent the brother who is praised in all the churches for spreading the gospel.
B047C008V019	47	8	19	More than that, he has also been selected by the churches to travel with us while we are administering this work of kindness for the glory of the Lord and as evidence of our eagerness to help.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	We are trying to avoid any criticism of the way we are administering this great undertaking.
B047C008V021	47	8	21	We intend to do what is right, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of people.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	We have also sent with them our brother whom we have often tested in many ways and found to be dedicated. At present he is more dedicated than ever because he has so much confidence in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker on your behalf. Our brothers, emissaries from the churches, are the glory of Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Therefore, give to the churches a demonstration of your love and a reason for why we boast about you.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	I do not need to write to you any further about the ministry to the saints.
B047C009V002	47	9	2	For I know how willing you are, and I boast about you to the people of Macedonia, saying that Achaia has been ready since last year, and your enthusiasm has stimulated most of them.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	Now I have sent the brothers so that our boasting about you in this matter may not prove to be an idle boast, and so that you may stand ready, just as I said.
B047C009V004	47	9	4	Otherwise, if any Macedonians come with me and find out that you are not ready, we would be humiliated—to say nothing of you—in this undertaking.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	Therefore, I thought it necessary to urge these brothers to visit you ahead of me, to make arrangements in advance for this gift you promised, and to have it ready as something given generously and not forced.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	Remember this: The person who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly, and the person who sows generously will also reap generously.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Each of you must give what you have decided in your heart, not with regret or under compulsion, since God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	Besides, God is able to make every blessing of yours overflow for you, so that in every situation you will always have all you need for any good work.
B047C009V009	47	9	9	As it is written,	“He scatters everywhere and gives to the poor;his righteousness lasts forever.”
B047C009V010	47	9	10	Now he who supplies seed to the sower and bread to eat will also supply you with seed and multiply it and enlarge the harvest of your righteousness.
B047C009V011	47	9	11	In every way you will grow richer and become even more generous, and this will produce thanksgiving to God because of us.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	For this ministry you render is not only fully supplying the needs of the saints, but it is also overflowing with more and more prayers of thanksgiving to God.
B047C009V013	47	9	13	Because of the proof that this service of yours brings, you will glorify God because of your obedience to your confession of the gospel of Christ and because of your generosity in sharing with them and everyone else.
B047C009V014	47	9	14	And so in their prayers for you they will long for you because of God's exceptional grace that was shown to you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Thanks be to God for his indescribable gift!
B047C010V001	47	10	1	Now I myself, Paul, plead with you with the gentleness and kindness of Christ—I who am humble when I am face to face with you but forceful toward you when I am away!
B047C010V002	47	10	2	I beg you that when I come I will not need to be courageous by daring to oppose some people who think that we are living according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	Of course, we are living in the flesh, but we do not fight in a fleshly way.
B047C010V004	47	10	4	For the weapons of our warfare are not those of the flesh. Instead, they have the power of God to demolish fortresses. We tear down arguments
B047C010V005	47	10	5	and every proud obstacle that is raised against the knowledge of God, taking every thought captive in order to obey Christ.
B047C010V006	47	10	6	We are ready to punish every act of disobedience when your obedience is complete.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Look at the plain facts! If anyone is confident that he belongs to Christ, he should remind himself of this: Just as he belongs to Christ, so do we.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	So if I boast a little too much about our authority, which the Lord gave us to build you up and not to tear you down, I will not be ashamed of it.
B047C010V009	47	10	9	I do not want you to think that I am trying to frighten you with my letters.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	For someone is saying, “His letters are impressive and forceful, but his bodily presence is weak and his speech contemptible.”
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Someone like this should take note of the following: What we say by letter when we are absent is what we will do when present!
B047C010V012	47	10	12	We would not dare put ourselves in the same class with or compare ourselves to those who recommend themselves. When they measure themselves by themselves and compare themselves to themselves, they show how foolish they are.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	We will not boast about what cannot be evaluated. Instead, we will stay within the field that God assigned us, so as to reach even you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For it is not as though we were overstepping our limits when we came to you. We were the first to reach you with the gospel of Christ.
B047C010V015	47	10	15	We are not boasting about the work done by others that cannot be evaluated. On the contrary, we cherish the hope that your faith may continue to grow and enlarge our sphere of action among you until it overflows.
B047C010V016	47	10	16	Then we can preach the gospel in the regions far beyond you without boasting about things already accomplished by someone else.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	“The person who boasts must boast in the Lord.”
B047C010V018	47	10	18	It is not the person who commends himself who is approved, but the person whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	I wish you would put up with a little foolishness of mine. Yes, do put up with me!
B047C011V002	47	11	2	I am jealous of you with God's own jealousy, because I promised you in marriage to one husband, to present you as a pure virgin to Christ.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	However, I am afraid that just as the serpent deceived Eve by its tricks, so your minds may somehow be lured away from sincere and pure devotion to Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if someone comes along and preaches another Jesus than the one we preached, or should you receive a different spirit from the one you received or a different gospel from the one you accepted, you are all too willing to listen.
B047C011V005	47	11	5	I do not think I'm inferior in any way to those “super-apostles.”
B047C011V006	47	11	6	Even though I may be untrained as an orator, I am not so in the field of knowledge. We have made this clear to all of you in every possible way.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Did I commit a sin when I humbled myself by proclaiming to you the gospel of God free of charge, so that you could be exalted?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches by accepting support from them in order to serve you.
B047C011V009	47	11	9	When I was with you and needed something, I did not bother any of you, because our brothers who came from Macedonia supplied everything I needed. I kept myself from being a burden to you in any way, and I will continue to do so.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As surely as the truth of Christ is in me, my boasting will not be silenced in the regions of Achaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? Because I do not love you? God knows that I do!
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But I will go on doing what I'm doing in order to deny an opportunity to those people who want an opportunity to be recognized as our equals in the work they are boasting about.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	Such people are false apostles, dishonest workers who are masquerading as apostles of Christ.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder, since Satan himself masquerades as an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	So it is not surprising if his servants also masquerade as servants of righteousness. Their doom will match their deeds!
B047C011V016	47	11	16	I will say it again: No one should think that I am a fool. But if you do, then treat me like a fool so that I can also boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	When I talk as a confident boaster, I am not talking with the Lord's authority but like a fool.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Since many people boast in a fleshly way, I will do it, too.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	You are wise, so you will gladly put up with fools.
B047C011V020	47	11	20	You put up with anyone who makes you his slaves, devours what you have, takes what is yours, orders you around, or slaps your face!
B047C011V021	47	11	21	I am ashamed to admit it, but we have been too weak for that. Whatever anyone else dares to claim—I am talking like a fool—I can claim it, too.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they Abraham's descendants? So am I.
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they Christ's servants? I am insane to talk like this, but I am a far better one! I have been involved in far greater efforts, far more imprisonments, countless beatings, and have faced death more than once.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	Five times I received from the Jews forty lashes minus one.
B047C011V025	47	11	25	Three times I was beaten with a stick, once I was pelted with stones, three times I was shipwrecked, and I drifted on the sea for a day and a night.
B047C011V026	47	11	26	I have been involved in frequent journeys, in dangers from rivers, dangers from robbers, dangers from my own people, dangers from the Gentiles, dangers in the city, dangers in the open country, dangers at sea, dangers from false brothers,
B047C011V027	47	11	27	in toil and hardship, through many a sleepless night, through hunger and thirst, through many periods of fasting, through coldness and nakedness.
B047C011V028	47	11	28	Besides everything else, I have a daily burden because of my anxiety about all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak without me being weak, too? Who is caused to stumble without me becoming indignant?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If I must boast, I will boast about the things that show how weak I am.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of the Lord Jesus, who is blessed forever, knows that I am not lying.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus, the governor under King Aretas put guards around the city of Damascus to catch me,
B047C011V033	47	11	33	but I was let down in a basket through an opening in the wall and escaped from his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	I must boast, although it does not do any good. I will go on to visions and revelations from the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I know a man in Christ. Fourteen years ago—whether in his body or outside of his body, I do not know, but God knows—that man was snatched away to the third heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	I know that this man—whether in his body or outside of his body, I do not know, but God knows—
B047C012V004	47	12	4	was snatched away to Paradise and heard things that cannot be expressed in words, things that no human being has a right even to mention.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	I will boast about this man, but as for myself I will boast only about my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	However, if I did want to boast, I would not be a fool, because I would be telling the truth. But I am not going to do it in order to keep anyone from thinking more of me than what he sees and hears about me.
B047C012V007	47	12	7	To keep me from becoming conceited because of the exceptional nature of these revelations, a thorn was given to me and placed in my body. It was Satan's messenger to keep on tormenting me so that I would not become conceited.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	I pleaded with the Lord three times to take it away from me,
B047C012V009	47	12	9	but he has told me,
B047C012V010	47	12	10	That is why I take such pleasure in weaknesses, insults, hardships, persecutions, and difficulties for Christ's sake, for when I am weak, then I am strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have become a fool. You forced me to be one. Really, I should have been commended by you, for I am not in any way inferior to your “super-apostles,” even if I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	The signs of an apostle were performed among you with utmost patience—signs, wonders, and works of power.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	How were you treated worse than the other churches, except that I did not bother you for help? Forgive me for this wrong!
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Here I am ready to visit you for a third time, and I will not bother you for help. I do not want your things but you. Children should not have to support their parents, but parents their children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	I will be very glad to spend my money and myself for you. Do you love me less because I love you so much?
B047C012V016	47	12	16	Granting that I have not been a burden to you, was I a clever schemer who trapped you by some trick?
B047C012V017	47	12	17	I did not take advantage of you through any of the men I sent you, did I?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I encouraged Titus to visit you, and I sent along with him the brother you know so well. Titus didn't take advantage of you, did he? We conducted ourselves with the same spirit, didn't we? We took the very same steps, didn't we?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	Have you been thinking all along that we are trying to defend ourselves before you? We are speaking before God in Christ, and everything, dear friends, is meant to build you up.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	I am afraid that I may come and somehow find you not as I want to find you, and that you may find me not as you want to find me. Perhaps there will be quarreling, jealousy, angry feelings, selfishness, slander, gossip, arrogance, and disorderly conduct.
B047C012V021	47	12	21	I am afraid that when I come my God may again humble me before you and that I may have to grieve over many who formerly lived in sin and have not repented of their impurity, sexual immorality, and promiscuity that they once practiced.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This will be the third time I am coming to you. “Every accusation must be verified by two or three witnesses.”
B047C013V002	47	13	2	I have already warned those who sinned previously and all the rest. Although I am absent now, I am warning them as I did on my second visit: If I come back, I will not spare you,
B047C013V003	47	13	3	since you want proof that Christ is speaking through me. He is not weak in dealing with you but is making his power felt among you.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	Though he was crucified in weakness, he lives by God's power. We are weak with him, but by God's power we will live for you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Keep examining yourselves to see whether you are continuing in the faith. Test yourselves! You know, do not you, that Jesus Christ lives in you? Could it be that you are failing the test?
B047C013V006	47	13	6	I hope you will realize that we haven't failed our test.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	We pray to God that you will not do anything wrong—not to show that we have not failed the test, but so that you may do what is right, even if we seem to have failed.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we cannot do anything against the truth, but only for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	We are glad when we are weak and you are strong. That is what we are praying for—your maturity.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	For this reason I am writing this while I am away from you: When I come I do not want to be severe in using the authority the Lord gave me to build you up and not to tear you down.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Finally, brothers, goodbye. Keep on growing to maturity. Keep listening to my appeals. Continue agreeing with each other and living in peace. Then the God of love and peace will be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the saints greet you.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	May the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with all of you!
B048C001V001	48	1	1	From Paul—an apostle not sent from men or by a man, but by Jesus Christ and God the Father who raised him from the dead—
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brothers who are with me, to the churches in Galatia.
B048C001V003	48	1	3	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B048C001V004	48	1	4	He gave himself for our sins in order to rescue us from this present evil age according to the will of our God and Father.
B048C001V005	48	1	5	To him be the glory forever and ever! Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I am astonished that you are so quickly deserting the one who called you by the grace of Christ to follow a different gospel,
B048C001V007	48	1	7	which is not really another one. To be sure, there are certain people who are troubling you and want to distort the gospel about Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even if we or an angel from heaven should proclaim to you a gospel contrary to what we proclaimed to you, let that person be condemned!
B048C001V009	48	1	9	What we have told you in the past I am now telling you again: If anyone proclaims to you a gospel contrary to what you received, let that person be condemned!
B048C001V010	48	1	10	Am I now trying to win the approval of people or of God? Or am I trying to please people? If I were still trying to please people, I would not be Christ's servant.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	For I want you to know, brothers, that the gospel that was proclaimed by me is not of human origin.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For I did not receive it from a man, nor was I taught it, but I received it through a revelation of Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard about my earlier life in Judaism—how I kept violently persecuting God's church and was trying to destroy it.
B048C001V014	48	1	14	I advanced in Judaism beyond many of my contemporaries, because I was far more zealous for the traditions of my ancestors.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when God, who set me apart before I was born and who called me by his grace, was pleased
B048C001V016	48	1	16	to reveal his Son to me so that I might proclaim him among the Gentiles, I did not confer with another human being at any time,
B048C001V017	48	1	17	nor did I go up to Jerusalem to see those who were apostles before me. Instead, I went away to Arabia and then came back to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then three years later I went up to Jerusalem to become acquainted with Cephas, and I stayed with him for fifteen days.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But I did not see any other apostle except James, the Lord's brother.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	(I declare before God that what I am writing to you is not a lie.)
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Then I went to the regions of Syria and Cilicia.
B048C001V022	48	1	22	But I was unknown by sight to the churches of Christ in Judea.
B048C001V023	48	1	23	The only thing they kept hearing was this: “The man who used to persecute us is now proclaiming the faith he once tried to destroy!”
B048C001V024	48	1	24	So they kept glorifying God for what had happened to me.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Then fourteen years later I again went up to Jerusalem with Barnabas, taking Titus with me.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	I went in response to a revelation, and in a private meeting with the reputed leaders I set before them the gospel I proclaim among the Gentiles. I did this because I was afraid that I was running or had run for nothing.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But not even Titus, who was with me, was forced to be circumcised, even though he was a Greek.
B048C002V004	48	2	4	However, false brothers were secretly brought in. They slipped in to spy on the freedom we have in Christ Jesus so that they might enslave us.
B048C002V005	48	2	5	But we did not give in to them for a moment, so that the truth of the gospel might always remain with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	Now those who were reputed to be important added nothing to my message. (What sort of people they were makes no difference to me, since God pays no attention to outward appearances.)
B048C002V007	48	2	7	In fact, they saw that I had been entrusted with the gospel for the uncircumcised, just as Peter had been entrusted with the gospel for the circumcised.
B048C002V008	48	2	8	For the one who worked through Peter by making him an apostle to the circumcised also worked through me by sending me to the Gentiles.
B048C002V009	48	2	9	So when James, Cephas, and John (who were reputed to be leaders) recognized the grace that had been given me, they gave Barnabas and me the right hand of fellowship, agreeing that we should go to the Gentiles and they to the circumcised.
B048C002V010	48	2	10	The only thing they asked us to do was to remember the destitute, the very thing I was eager to do.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Cephas came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he was clearly wrong.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For until some men came from James, he was in the habit of eating with the Gentiles, but after they came he drew back and would not associate himself with them, being afraid of the circumcision party.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	The other Jews also joined him in this hypocrisy, to the extent that even Barnabas was caught up in their hypocrisy.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they were not acting consistently with the truth of the gospel, I told Cephas in front of everyone, “Though you are a Jew, you live like a Gentile and not like a Jew. So how can you insist that the Gentiles must live like Jews?”
B048C002V015	48	2	15	We ourselves are Jews by birth, and not Gentile sinners,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	yet we know that a person is not justified by the works of the law but by the faithfulness of Jesus Christ. We, too, have believed in Christ Jesus so that we might be justified by the faith of Christ and not by the works of the law, for no human being will be justified by the works of the law.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	Now if we, while trying to be justified in Christ, have been found to be sinners, does that mean that Christ is a minister of sin? Of course not!
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I rebuild something that I tore down, I demonstrate that I am a wrongdoer.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For through the law I died to the law so that I might live for God. I have been crucified with Christ.
B048C002V020	48	2	20	I no longer live, but Christ lives in me, and the life that I now live in the flesh I live by the faithfulness of the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not set aside the grace of God, for if righteousness comes through the law, then Christ died for nothing.
B048C003V001	48	3	1	You foolish Galatians! Who put you under a spell? Was not Jesus Christ clearly portrayed as crucified before your very eyes?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	I want to learn only one thing from you: Did you receive the Spirit by doing the works of the law or by believing what you heard?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish? Having started out with the Spirit, are you now ending up with the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Did you suffer so much for nothing? (If it really was for nothing!)
B048C003V005	48	3	5	Does God supply you with the Spirit and work miracles among you because you do the works of the law or because you believe what you heard?
B048C003V006	48	3	6	In the same way, Abraham “believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.”
B048C003V007	48	3	7	You see, then, that those who have faith are Abraham's real descendants.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	Because the Scripture saw ahead of time that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, it announced the gospel to Abraham beforehand when it said, “Through you all nations will be blessed.”
B048C003V009	48	3	9	Therefore, those who believe are blessed together with Abraham, the one who believed.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	Certainly all who depend on the works of the law are under a curse. For it is written, “A curse on everyone who does not obey everything that is written in the book of the law!”
B048C003V011	48	3	11	Now it is obvious that no one is justified in the sight of God by the law, because “The righteous will live by faith.”
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the law has nothing to do with faith. Instead, “The person who keeps the commandments will have life in them.”
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ redeemed us from the curse of the law by becoming a curse for us. For it is written, “A curse on everyone who is hung on a tree!”
B048C003V014	48	3	14	This happened in order that the blessing promised to Abraham would come to the Gentiles through Christ Jesus, so that we might receive the promised Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brothers, let me use an example from everyday life. Once a person's will has been ratified, no one can cancel it or add conditions to it.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	Now the promises were spoken to Abraham and to his descendant. It doesn't say “descendants,” referring to many, but “your descendant,” referring to one person, who is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	This is what I mean: The law that came 430 years later did not cancel the covenant previously ratified by God so as to nullify the promise.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance comes by the law, it no longer comes by the promise. But it was by a promise that God so graciously gave it to Abraham.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Why, then, was the law given? It was added because of transgressions until the descendant came to whom the promise was given. It was put into effect through angels by means of an intermediary.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	Now an intermediary involves more than one party, but God has acted on his own.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	So is the law in conflict with the promises of God? Of course not! For if a law had been given that could give us life, then certainly righteousness would come through the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the Scripture has put everything under the power of sin, so that what was promised by the faithfulness of Christ might be given to those who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	Now before this faith came, we were held in custody and carefully guarded under the law in preparation for the faith that was to be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	And so the law was our guardian until Christ came, so that we might be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But now that this faith has come, we are no longer under the control of a guardian.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For all of you are God's children through faith in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	Indeed, all of you who were baptized into Christ have clothed yourselves with Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	A person is no longer a Jew or a Greek, a slave or a free person, a male or a female, because all of you are one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	And if you belong to Christ, then you are Abraham's descendants and heirs according to the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	Now what I am saying is this: As long as an heir is a child, he is no better off than a slave, even though he owns everything.
B048C004V002	48	4	2	Instead, he is placed under the control of guardians and trustees until the time set by the father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	It was the same way with us. While we were children, we were slaves to the basic principles of the world.
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fullness of time had come, God sent his Son, born of a woman, born under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	in order to redeem those who were under the law, so that we might receive adoption as his children.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	Now because you are his children, God has sent the Spirit of his Son into our hearts to cry out, “Abba! Father!”
B048C004V007	48	4	7	So you are no longer a slave but a child, and if you are a child, then you are also an heir through God.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	However, in the past, when you did not know God, you were slaves to things that are not really gods at all.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now that you know God, or rather have been known by God, how can you turn back again to those powerless and bankrupt basic principles? Why do you want to become their slaves all over again?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You are observing days, months, seasons, and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid for you, lest somehow my work for you has been wasted!
B048C004V012	48	4	12	I beg you, brothers, to become like me, since I became like you. You did not do anything wrong to me.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	You know that it was because I was ill that I brought you the gospel the first time.
B048C004V014	48	4	14	Even though my condition put you to the test, you did not despise or reject me. On the contrary, you welcomed me as if I were an angel of God, as Christ Jesus himself.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	What, then, happened to your positive attitude? For I testify that if it had been possible, you would have torn out your eyes and given them to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	So have I now become your enemy for telling you the truth?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	These people are devoted to you, but not in a good way. They want you to avoid me so that you will be devoted to them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	(Now it is always good to be devoted to a good cause, even when I am not with you.)
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My children, I am suffering birth pains for you again until Christ is formed in you.
B048C004V020	48	4	20	Indeed, I wish I were with you right now so that I could change the tone of my voice, because I am completely baffled by you!
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, those of you who want to live under the law: Are you really listening to what the law says?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by a slave woman and the other by a free woman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	Now the son of the slave woman was conceived according to the flesh, but the son of the free woman was conceived through a promise.
B048C004V024	48	4	24	This is being said as an allegory, for these women represent two covenants. The one woman, Hagar, is from Mount Sinai, and her children are born into slavery.
B048C004V025	48	4	25	Now Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia and corresponds to present-day Jerusalem, because she is in slavery along with her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But the heavenly Jerusalem is the free woman, and she is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written,	“Rejoice, you childless woman,who cannot give birth to any children!	Break into song and shout,you who feel no pains of childbirth!	For the children of the deserted womanare more numerous than the childrenof the woman who has a husband.”
B048C004V028	48	4	28	So you, brothers, are children of the promise, like Isaac.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But just as then the son who was conceived according to the flesh persecuted the son who was conceived according to the Spirit, so it is now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	But what does the Scripture say? “Drive out the slave woman and her son, for the son of the slave woman must never share the inheritance with the son of the free woman.”
B048C004V031	48	4	31	So then, brothers, we are not children of the slave woman but of the free woman.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	Christ has set us free so that we may enjoy the benefits of freedom. So keep on standing firm in it, and stop attaching yourselves to the yoke of slavery again.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Listen! I, Paul, am telling you that if you allow yourselves to be circumcised, Christ will be of no benefit to you.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	Again, I insist that everyone who allows himself to be circumcised is obligated to obey the entire law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	Those of you who are trying to be justified by the law have been cut off from Christ. You have fallen away from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For through the Spirit, by faith, we eagerly wait for the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision matters. What matters is faith that is active through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running beautifully! Who cut in on you and stopped you from obeying the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	Such influence does not come from the one who calls you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little yeast spreads through the whole batch of dough.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I am confident in the Lord that you will take no other view of the matter. However, the one who is troubling you will suffer God's judgment, whoever he is.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	As for me, brothers, if I am still preaching the necessity of circumcision, why am I still being persecuted? In that case the offense of the cross has been removed.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	I wish that those who are unsettling you would castrate themselves!
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you, brothers, were called to freedom. Only do not turn your freedom into an opportunity to gratify your flesh, but through love make it your habit to serve one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For the whole law is summarized in a single statement: “You must love your neighbor as yourself.”
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, be careful that you are not destroyed by each other.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	So I say, live by the Spirit, and you will never fulfill the desires of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For what the flesh wants is opposed to the Spirit, and what the Spirit wants is opposed to the flesh. They are opposed to each other, and so you do not do what you want to do.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are being led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the works of the flesh are obvious: sexual immorality, impurity, promiscuity,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, witchcraft, hatred, rivalry, jealously, outbursts of anger, quarrels, conflicts, factions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envy, murder, drunkenness, wild partying, and things like that. I am telling you now, as I have told you in the past, that people who practice such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, and self-control. There is no law against such things.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	Now those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified their flesh with its passions and desires.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, let us also be guided by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us stop being arrogant, provoking one another and envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brothers, if a person is caught doing something wrong, those of you who are spiritual should restore that person in a spirit of gentleness. Watch out for yourself so that you are not tempted as well.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Practice carrying each other's burdens. In this way you will fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if anyone thinks he is something when he is really nothing, he is only fooling himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	Each person must approve his own actions, and then he can boast about his own accomplishments and not those of his neighbor.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For everyone must carry his own load.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	The person who is taught the word should share all his goods with his teacher.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Stop being deceived; God is not to be ridiculed. A person harvests whatever he plants.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For the person who plants in his flesh will harvest decay from the flesh, but the person who plants in the Spirit will harvest eternal life from the Spirit.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	Let us not get tired of doing what is good, for at the right time we will reap a harvest—if we do not give up.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	So then, whenever we have the opportunity, let us practice doing good to everyone, especially to the family of faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	Look at how large these letters are because I am writing with my own hand!
B048C006V012	48	6	12	These people who want to impress others by their flesh are trying to force you to be circumcised, simply to avoid being persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	Why, not even those who are circumcised obey the law! They simply want you to be circumcised so that they can boast about your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But may I never boast about anything except the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world!
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For neither circumcision nor uncircumcision matters. Rather, what matters is being a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	Now may peace be on all those who live by this principle, and may mercy be on the Israel of God.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	From now on let no one make trouble for me, for I carry the scars of Jesus on my own body.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brothers! Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by God's will, to his holy and faithful people in Ephesus who are in union with Christ Jesus.
B049C001V002	49	1	2	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ! He has blessed us in Christ with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly realm,
B049C001V004	49	1	4	just as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world to be holy and blameless in his presence. In love
B049C001V005	49	1	5	he predestined us for adoption to himself through Jesus Christ, according to the pleasure of his will,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	so that we would praise his glorious grace that he gave us in the Beloved One.
B049C001V007	49	1	7	In him we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of our offenses, according to the riches of God's grace
B049C001V008	49	1	8	that he lavished on us, along with all wisdom and understanding,
B049C001V009	49	1	9	when he made known to us the secret of his will. This was according to his plan that he set forth in Christ
B049C001V010	49	1	10	to usher in the fullness of the times and to gather up all things in Christ, both things in heaven and things on earth.
B049C001V011	49	1	11	In Christ we were also chosen when we were predestined according to the purpose of the one who does everything according to the intention of his will,
B049C001V012	49	1	12	so that we who had already fixed our hope on Christ might live for his praise and glory.
B049C001V013	49	1	13	You, too, have heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation. When you believed in him you were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	who is the guarantee of our inheritance until the redemption of God's own possession, to his praise and glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	Therefore, because I have heard about your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	I never stop giving thanks for you as I mention you in my prayers.
B049C001V017	49	1	17	I pray that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father most glorious, would give you a spirit of wisdom and revelation through knowing Christ fully.
B049C001V018	49	1	18	Then, with the eyes of your hearts enlightened, you will know the hope of his calling, the riches of his glorious inheritance among the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and the unlimited greatness of his power for us who believe, according to the working of his mighty strength,
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which he put to work in Christ when he raised him from the dead and seated him at his right hand in the heavenly realm.
B049C001V021	49	1	21	He is far above every ruler, authority, power, dominion, and every name that can be named, not only in the present age but also in the one to come.
B049C001V022	49	1	22	God has put everything under his feet and has made him the head of everything for the good of the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is his body, the fullness of the one who fills everything in every way.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	You used to be dead because of your offenses and sins,
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which you once lived according to the ways of this present world and according to the ruler of the power of the air, the spirit that is now active in those who are disobedient.
B049C002V003	49	2	3	Indeed, all of us once behaved like them in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of our flesh and senses. By nature we deserved wrath, just like everyone else.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, who is rich in mercy, because of his great love for us
B049C002V005	49	2	5	even when we were dead because of our offenses, made us alive together with Christ (by grace you have been saved),
B049C002V006	49	2	6	raised us up with him, and seated us with him in the heavenly realm in Christ Jesus,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	so that in the coming ages he might display the limitless riches of his grace in kindness toward us in Christ Jesus.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by such grace you have been saved through faith. This does not come from you; it is the gift of God
B049C002V009	49	2	9	and not the result of works, lest anyone boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his masterpiece, created in Christ Jesus for good works that God prepared long ago to be our way of life.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	So then, remember that at one time you were Gentiles by birth and were called “the uncircumcision” by what is called “the circumcision” made in the flesh by hands.
B049C002V012	49	2	12	At that time you were without Christ, excluded from citizenship in Israel, and strangers to the covenants of promise. You had no hope and were in the world without God.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now, in Christ Jesus, you who once were far away have been brought near by the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For it is he who is our peace. In his flesh he made both groups one by tearing down the wall of hostility that divided them.
B049C002V015	49	2	15	He rendered the law inoperative, along with its commandments and regulations, so that he might create in himself one new humanity from the two, thus making peace,
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and might reconcile both groups to God in one body through the cross, on which he killed the hostility.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	He came and proclaimed peace for you who were far away and for you who were near.
B049C002V018	49	2	18	For through him, both of us have access to the Father in one Spirit.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	That is why you are no longer strangers and foreigners but fellow citizens with the saints and members of God's household,
B049C002V020	49	2	20	having been built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Christ Jesus himself being the cornerstone.
B049C002V021	49	2	21	In him the whole building is joined together and rises into a holy sanctuary in the Lord.
B049C002V022	49	2	22	You, too, are being built in him along with the others into a dwelling place of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	For this reason I, Paul, am the prisoner of Christ Jesus for the sake of you Gentiles.
B049C003V002	49	3	2	Surely you have heard about the responsibility of administering God's grace that was given to me on your behalf,
B049C003V003	49	3	3	and how this secret was made known to me through a revelation, just as I wrote about briefly in the past.
B049C003V004	49	3	4	By reading this, you will be able to grasp my understanding of the secret about Christ,
B049C003V005	49	3	5	which in previous generations was not made known to human beings as it has now been revealed by the Spirit to God's holy apostles and prophets:
B049C003V006	49	3	6	The Gentiles are fellow heirs, fellow members of the body, and fellow sharers of what was promised in Christ Jesus through the gospel.
B049C003V007	49	3	7	I have become a servant of this gospel according to the gift of God's grace that was given me by the working of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, the very least of all the saints, this grace was given so that I might proclaim to the Gentiles the immeasurable wealth of Christ
B049C003V009	49	3	9	and help everyone see how this secret, which was hidden for ages in God who created all things, has been at work.
B049C003V010	49	3	10	He did this so that now, through the church, the wisdom of God in all its variety might be made known to the rulers and authorities in the heavenly realm
B049C003V011	49	3	11	in keeping with the eternal purpose that God carried out through Christ Jesus our Lord,
B049C003V012	49	3	12	in whom we have boldness and confident access through his faithfulness.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	So then, I ask you not to become discouraged because of my troubles on your behalf, which are your glory.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	This is the reason I bow my knees before the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom every family in heaven and on earth receives its name.
B049C003V016	49	3	16	I pray that he would give you, according to his glorious riches, strength in your inner being and power through his Spirit,
B049C003V017	49	3	17	and that Christ would make his home in your hearts through faith. Then, having been rooted and grounded in love,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	you will be able to understand, along with all the saints, what is wide, long, high, and deep—
B049C003V019	49	3	19	that is, you will know the love of Christ, which goes far beyond knowledge, and will be filled with all the fullness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	Now to the one who can do infinitely more than all we can ask or imagine according to the power that is working among us—
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations, forever and ever! Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	I, therefore, the prisoner of the Lord, urge you to live in a way that is worthy of the calling to which you have been called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	with all humility and gentleness, along with patience, accepting one another in love.
B049C004V003	49	4	3	Do your best to maintain the unity of the Spirit by means of the bond of peace.
B049C004V004	49	4	4	There is one body and one Spirit. In the same way, you were called to the one hope of your calling.
B049C004V005	49	4	5	There is one Lord, one faith, one baptism,
B049C004V006	49	4	6	one God and Father of all, who is above all, through all, and in all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	Now to each one of us grace has been given according to the measure of Christ's gift.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	That is why God says,	“When he went up to the highest placehe led captives into captivityand gave gifts to people.”
B049C004V009	49	4	9	Now what does this “he went up” mean except that he also had gone down into the lower parts of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	The one who went down is the same one who went up above all the heavens so that he might fill everything.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And it is he who gifted some to be apostles, others to be prophets, others to be evangelists, and still others to be pastors and teachers,
B049C004V012	49	4	12	to perfect the saints, to do the work of ministry, and to build up the body of Christ
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until all of us are united in the faith and in the full knowledge of God's Son, and until we attain mature adulthood and the full standard of development in Christ.
B049C004V014	49	4	14	Then we will no longer be little children, tossed like waves and blown about by every wind of doctrine, by people's trickery, or by clever strategies that would lead us astray.
B049C004V015	49	4	15	Instead, by speaking the truth in love, we will grow up completely into the one who is the head, that is, into Christ,
B049C004V016	49	4	16	in whom the whole body is united and held together by every ligament with which it is supplied. As each individual part does its job, the body's growth is promoted so that it builds itself up in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	Therefore, I tell you and insist on in the Lord not to live any longer like the Gentiles live, thinking worthless thoughts.
B049C004V018	49	4	18	They are darkened in their understanding and separated from the life of God because of their ignorance and hardness of heart.
B049C004V019	49	4	19	Since they have lost all sense of shame, they have abandoned themselves to sensuality and practice every kind of sexual perversion without restraint.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	However, that is not the way you came to know Christ.
B049C004V021	49	4	21	Surely you have listened to him and have been taught by him, since truth is in Jesus.
B049C004V022	49	4	22	Regarding your former way of life, you were taught to strip off your old man, which is being ruined by its deceptive desires,
B049C004V023	49	4	23	to be renewed in the spirit of your minds,
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and to clothe yourselves with the new man, which was created according to the likeness of God in righteousness and true holiness.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore, stripping off falsehood, “let each of us speak the truth to his neighbor,” for we are members of one another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	“Be angry, yet do not sin.” Do not let the sun go down on your wrath,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	and do not give the devil an opportunity to work.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	The thief must no longer steal but must work hard and do what is good with his own hands, so that he might have something to give to the needy.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no filthy talk come out of your mouths, but only what is good for building up as the need may be. This way you will give grace to those who hear you.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	Do not grieve the Holy Spirit, by whom you were marked with a seal for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, quarreling, and slander be put away from you, along with all hatred.
B049C004V032	49	4	32	And be kind to one another, compassionate, forgiving one another just as God has forgiven you in Christ.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	So be imitators of God, as his dear children.
B049C005V002	49	5	2	Live in love as Christ also loved us and gave himself for us as an offering and sacrifice, a fragrant aroma to God.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	Do not let sexual sin, impurity of any kind, or greed even be mentioned among you, as is proper for saints.
B049C005V004	49	5	4	Obscene, flippant, or vulgar talk is totally inappropriate. Instead, let there be thanksgiving.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	For you know very well that no immoral or impure person, or anyone who is greedy (that is, an idolater), has an inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Do not let anyone deceive you with meaningless words, for it is because of these things that God's wrath comes on those who are disobedient.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	So do not be partners with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For once you were darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Live as children of light.
B049C005V009	49	5	9	For the fruit of the light consists of every form of goodness, righteousness, and truth.
B049C005V010	49	5	10	Determine what pleases the Lord,
B049C005V011	49	5	11	and have nothing to do with the unfruitful works of darkness. Instead, expose them for what they are.
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For it is shameful even to mention what is done by people in secret.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	But everything that is exposed to the light becomes visible,
B049C005V014	49	5	14	for everything that is visible is light. That is why it says,	“Wake up, O sleeper!Arise from the dead,And Christ will shine on you.’’
B049C005V015	49	5	15	So, then, be careful how you live. Do not be unwise but wise,
B049C005V016	49	5	16	making the best use of time because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Therefore, do not be foolish, but understand what the Lord's will is.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	Stop getting drunk with wine, which leads to wild living, but keep on being filled with the Spirit.
B049C005V019	49	5	19	Then you will recite to one another psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs. You will sing and make music to the Lord with your hearts.
B049C005V020	49	5	20	You will always give thanks to God the Father for everything in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C005V021	49	5	21	And you will submit yourselves to one another out of reverence for Christ.
B049C005V022	49	5	22	Wives, submit yourselves to your husbands as to the Lord.
B049C005V023	49	5	23	For the husband is the head of his wife as Christ is the head of the church. It is he who is the Savior of the body.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	Indeed, just as the church is submissive to Christ, so wives must be submissive to their husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives as Christ loved the church and gave himself for it,
B049C005V026	49	5	26	so that he might make it holy by cleansing it, washing it with water and the word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	and might present the church to himself in all its glory, without a spot or wrinkle or anything of the kind, but holy and without fault.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	In the same way, husbands must love their wives as they love their own bodies. A man who loves his wife loves himself.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no one has ever hated his own body, but he nourishes and tenderly cares for it, as Christ does the church.
B049C005V030	49	5	30	For we are parts of his body—of his flesh and of his bones.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	“That is why a man will leave his father and mother and be united with his wife, and the two will become one flesh.”
B049C005V032	49	5	32	This is a great secret, but I am talking about Christ and the church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	But each individual man among you must love his wife as he loves himself; and may the wife fear her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is the right thing to do.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	“Honor your father and mother.” This is a very important commandment with a promise:
B049C006V003	49	6	3	“So that it may go well for you, and that you may have a long life on the earth.”
B049C006V004	49	6	4	Fathers, do not make your children angry, but bring them up in the training and instruction of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Slaves, obey your earthly masters with fear, with trembling, and along with sincerity, as when you obey Christ.
B049C006V006	49	6	6	Do not do this only while being watched in order to please them, but be like slaves of Christ who do God's will from the heart.
B049C006V007	49	6	7	Serve willingly, as if you were serving the Lord and not merely people.
B049C006V008	49	6	8	For you know that everyone will receive a reward from the Lord for whatever good he has done, whether he is a slave or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	Masters, treat your slaves the same way. Do not threaten them, for you know that both of you have the same Master in heaven, and there is no favoritism with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	Finally, be strong in the Lord and in his mighty strength.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the whole armor of God so that you may be able to stand firm against the devil's strategies.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For our struggle is not against a human opponent, but against rulers, against authorities, against cosmic powers in the darkness around us, against evil spiritual forces in the heavenly realm.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	For this reason, take up the whole armor of God so that you may be able to take a stand in that evil day. And when you have done everything you could, you will be able to stand firm.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand firm, therefore, having fastened the belt of truth around your waist, and having put on the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	and having put shoes on your feet so that you are ready to proclaim the gospel of peace.
B049C006V016	49	6	16	In addition to all of these, having taken up the shield of faith, with which you will be able to put out all the flaming arrows of the evil one,
B049C006V017	49	6	17	also take the helmet of salvation and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.
B049C006V018	49	6	18	Pray in the Spirit at all times with every kind of prayer and request there is. For the same reason be alert with every kind of effort and request for all the saints.
B049C006V019	49	6	19	Pray also for me, so that, when I open my mouth, the right words will be given to me. Then I will boldly make known the secret of the gospel,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for whose sake I am an ambassador in chains, desiring to declare it as boldly as I should.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	So that you may know what has happened to me and how I am doing, Tychicus, our dear brother and a faithful minister in the Lord, will tell you everything.
B049C006V022	49	6	22	I am sending him to you for this very reason, so that you may know how we are doing and that he may encourage your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	May the brothers have peace and love, with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ!
B049C006V024	49	6	24	May grace be with all who love the Lord Jesus Christ with sincerity!
B050C001V001	50	1	1	From Paul and Timothy, servants of Christ Jesus, to all the holy ones in Philippi who are united with Christ Jesus, with their overseers and deacons.
B050C001V002	50	1	2	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I thank my God every time I remember you,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	always praying with joy in every one of my prayers for all of you
B050C001V005	50	1	5	because of your partnership in the gospel from the first day until now.
B050C001V006	50	1	6	I am convinced of this, that the one who began a good work among you will bring it to completion by the day of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V007	50	1	7	For it is only right for me to think this way about all of you, because I have you in my heart. Both in my imprisonment and in the defense and confirmation of the gospel, all of you are partners with me in grace.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness how much I long for all of you with the compassion of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this is my prayer, that your love will keep on growing more and more in full knowledge and perfect insight,
B050C001V010	50	1	10	so that you may be able to determine what is best and may be pure and blameless until the day of Christ,
B050C001V011	50	1	11	having been filled with the fruit of righteousness that comes through Jesus Christ to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	Now I want you to know, brothers, that what has happened to me has actually turned out for the progress of the gospel.
B050C001V013	50	1	13	As a result, it has become clear to the whole imperial guard and to everyone else that I am in prison because of Christ.
B050C001V014	50	1	14	Moreover, because of my imprisonment most of the brothers have been made confident in the Lord to speak God's word more boldly and courageously than ever before.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some are preaching Christ because of their envy and rivalry, while others do so because of their good will.
B050C001V016	50	1	16	The latter are motivated by love, because they know that I have been appointed for the defense of the gospel.
B050C001V017	50	1	17	The former proclaim Christ out of selfish ambition and without sincerity, thinking that they will stir up trouble for me during my imprisonment.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	But what does it matter? Just this, that in every way, whether in pretense or in truth, Christ is being proclaimed, and because of this I rejoice. Yes, I will continue to rejoice,
B050C001V019	50	1	19	because I know that this will result in my deliverance through your prayers and the help that comes from the Spirit of Jesus Christ.
B050C001V020	50	1	20	This is according to my eager expectation and hope that I will have nothing to be ashamed of. Instead, because of my boldness Christ will be exalted in my body, now as always, whether I live or die.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me, to go on living is Christ, and to die is gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	Now if I go on living in this body, that will produce more results, yet I do not know which I would prefer.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	Indeed, I cannot decide between the two. I have the desire to leave this life and be with Christ, for that is far better.
B050C001V024	50	1	24	But for your sake it is better that I remain in this body.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	Since I am convinced of this, I know that I will continue to live and be with all of you for the sake of your progress and joy in the faith.
B050C001V026	50	1	26	Then your boasting in Christ Jesus will increase along with mine through my coming again to you.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	The only thing that matters is that you continue to live as good citizens in a manner worthy of the gospel of Christ. Then, whether I come to see you or whether I stay away, I may hear all about you—that you are standing firm in one spirit, struggling with one mind for the faith of the gospel,
B050C001V028	50	1	28	and that you are not intimidated by your opponents in any way. This is evidence that they will be destroyed and that you will be saved—and all because of God.
B050C001V029	50	1	29	For you have been given the privilege for Christ's sake not only to believe in him but also to suffer for him.
B050C001V030	50	1	30	You have the same struggle that you saw in me and now hear that I am still having.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	Therefore, if there is any encouragement in Christ, if there is any comfort of love, if there is any fellowship in the Spirit, if there is any compassion and sympathy,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	then fill me with joy by having the same attitude, sharing the same love, being united in spirit, and keeping one purpose in mind.
B050C002V003	50	2	3	Do not act out of selfish ambition or conceit, but with humility think of others as being better than yourselves.
B050C002V004	50	2	4	Do not be concerned about your own interests, but also be concerned about the interests of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Have the same attitude among yourselves that was also in Christ Jesus:
B050C002V006	50	2	6	In God's own form existed he,And shared with God equality,Deemed nothing needed grasping.
B050C002V007	50	2	7	Instead, poured out in emptiness,A servant's form did he possess,A mortal man becoming.	In human form he chose to be,
B050C002V008	50	2	8	And lived in all humility,Death on a cross obeying.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Now lifted up by God to heaven,A name above all others given,This matchless name possessing.
B050C002V010	50	2	10	And so, when Jesus’ name is called,The knees of everyone should fallWhere'er they are residing.
B050C002V011	50	2	11	Then every tongue in one accord,Will say that Jesus Christ is Lord,While God the Father praising.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	And so, my dear friends, just as you have always obeyed, not only when I was with you but even more now that I am absent, continue to work out your salvation with fear and trembling.
B050C002V013	50	2	13	For it is God who is producing in you both the desire and the ability to do what pleases him.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do everything without complaining or arguing
B050C002V015	50	2	15	so that you may be blameless and innocent, God's children without any faults among a crooked and perverse generation, among whom you shine like stars in the world
B050C002V016	50	2	16	as you hold out the word of life. Then I can boast in the day of Christ that I did not run in vain or work hard in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	Yet even if I am being poured out like an offering as part of the sacrifice and service I offer for your faith, I rejoice, and I share my joy with all of you.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	In the same way, you also should rejoice and share your joy with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	Now I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon so that I can be encouraged when I learn of your condition.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	I do not have anyone else like him who takes a genuine interest in your welfare.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For all the others look after their own interests, not after those of Jesus Christ.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But you know his proven worth—how like a son with his father he served with me in the gospel.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Therefore, I hope to send him as soon as I see how things are going to turn out for me.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	Indeed, I am confident in the Lord that I will come to visit you soon.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	Meanwhile, I thought it best to send Epaphroditus—my brother, fellow worker, and fellow soldier, but your messenger and minister to my need—back to you.
B050C002V026	50	2	26	For he has been longing for all of you and is troubled because you heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	Indeed, he was sick to the point of death, but God had mercy on him, and not only on him but also on me, so that I would not have one sorrow on top of another.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	Therefore, I am especially eager to send him so that you may have the joy of seeing him again, and so that I may feel relieved.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	So welcome him in the Lord with all joy, and make sure you honor such people highly.
B050C002V030	50	2	30	For he came close to death for the work of Christ, risking his life to complete what was lacking in your service to me.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	So then, my brothers, keep on rejoicing in the Lord. It is no trouble for me to write the same things to you; indeed, it is for your safety.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs! Beware of the evil workers! Beware of the mutilators!
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For it is we who are the circumcision—we who worship in the Spirit of God and boast in Christ Jesus. We have not placed any confidence in the flesh,
B050C003V004	50	3	4	although I could have confidence in the flesh. If anyone thinks he can place confidence in the flesh, I have more reason to think so.
B050C003V005	50	3	5	Having been circumcised on the eighth day, I am of the nation of Israel, from the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews. As far as the law is concerned, I was a Pharisee.
B050C003V006	50	3	6	As far as zeal is concerned, I was a persecutor of the church. As far as the righteousness that is in the law is concerned, I was perfect.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But whatever things were assets to me, these I now consider a loss for the sake of Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	What is more, I continue to consider all these things as a loss for the sake of the surpassing value of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord. It is because of him that I have experienced the loss of all those things. Indeed, I consider them rubbish in order to gain Christ
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and be found in him, not having a righteousness of my own that comes from the law, but one that comes through the faithfulness of Christ, the righteousness that comes from God and that depends on faith.
B050C003V010	50	3	10	I want to know Christ—what his resurrection power is like and what it means to share in his sufferings by becoming like him in his death,
B050C003V011	50	3	11	though I hope to experience the resurrection from the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	It's not that I have already reached this goal or have already become perfect. But I keep pursuing it, hoping somehow to embrace it just as I have been embraced by Christ Jesus.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brothers, I do not consider myself to have embraced it. But this one thing I do: Forgetting what lies behind and straining forward to what lies ahead,
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I keep pursuing the goal to win the prize of God's heavenly call in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Therefore, those of us who are mature should think this way. And if you think differently about anything, God will show you how to think.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	However, we should live up to what we have achieved so far.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Join together in imitating me, brothers, and pay close attention to those who live by the example we have given you.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For I have often told you, and now tell you even with tears, that many live as enemies of the cross of Christ.
B050C003V019	50	3	19	Their destiny is destruction, their god is their belly, and their glory is in their shame. Their minds are set on worldly things.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	Our citizenship, however, is in heaven, and it is from there that we eagerly wait for a Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C003V021	50	3	21	He will change our humble bodies and make them like his glorious body through the power that enables him to bring everything under his authority.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	Therefore, my dear brothers whom I long for, my joy and my victor's crown, stand firm in the Lord in this way, dear friends.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I urge Euodia and I urge Syntyche to have the same attitude in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Yes, I also ask you, my true partner, to help these women. They have struggled with me in the gospel along with Clement and the rest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the Book of Life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Keep on rejoicing in the Lord at all times. I will say it again: Keep on rejoicing!
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your forbearing spirit be known to all people.The Lord is near:
B050C004V006	50	4	6	Never worry about anything, but in every situation let your petitions be made known to God in prayers and requests, with thanksgiving.
B050C004V007	50	4	7	Then God's peace, which goes far beyond anything we can imagine, will guard your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	Finally, brothers, whatever is true, whatever is honorable, whatever is fair, whatever is pure, whatever is acceptable, whatever is commendable, if there is anything of excellence and if there is anything praiseworthy—keep thinking about these things.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	Likewise, keep practicing these things: what you have learned, received, heard, and seen in me. Then the God of peace will be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	Now I rejoice in the Lord greatly, because once again you have shown your concern for me. Of course, you were concerned for me but you did not have an opportunity to show it.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	I am not saying this because I am in any need, for I have learned to be content in whatever situation I am in.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how to be humble, and I know how to prosper. In each and every situation I have learned the secret of being full and of going hungry, of having too much and of having too little.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I can do all things through him who strengthens me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Nevertheless, it was kind of you to share my troubles.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	You Philippians also know that in the early days of the gospel, when I left Macedonia, no church participated with me in the matter of giving and receiving except for you.
B050C004V016	50	4	16	Even while I was in Thessalonica, you provided for my needs not once, but twice.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	It is not that I am looking for a gift. No, I am looking for the profit that accumulates to your account.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	I have been paid in full and have more than enough. I am fully supplied, now that I have received from Epaphroditus what you sent—a fragrant aroma, a sacrifice acceptable and pleasing to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	And my God will fully supply your every need according to his glorious riches in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	Glory belongs to our God and Father forever and ever! Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every saint in Christ Jesus. The brothers who are with me send their greetings to you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints, especially those of the emperor's household, greet you.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	May the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit! Amen.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	to the holy and faithful brothers in Colossae who are in union with Christ.May grace and peace from God our Father be yours!
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying always for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	because we have heard about your faith in Christ Jesus and the love that you have for all the saints,
B051C001V005	51	1	5	based on the hope laid up for you in heaven. Some time ago you heard about this hope in the word of truth, the gospel
B051C001V006	51	1	6	that has come to you. Just as it is bearing fruit and spreading all over the world, so it has been doing among you from the day you heard it and came to know the grace of God in truth.
B051C001V007	51	1	7	You learned about this gospel from Epaphras, our dear fellow servant, who is a faithful minister of Christ on your behalf.
B051C001V008	51	1	8	He has told us about your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	For this reason, since the day we heard about this, we have not stopped praying for you and asking that you may be filled with the full knowledge of God's will in all spiritual wisdom and understanding,
B051C001V010	51	1	10	so that you might live in a manner worthy of the Lord and be fully pleasing to him as you bear fruit in every good work and grow in the full knowledge of God.
B051C001V011	51	1	11	You are being strengthened with all power according to his glorious might, so that you might patiently endure everything with joy
B051C001V012	51	1	12	and might thank the Father, who has enabled us to share in the saints’ inheritance in the light.
B051C001V013	51	1	13	He has rescued us from the power of darkness and has brought us into the kingdom of the Son whom he loves.
B051C001V014	51	1	14	In him we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.
B051C001V015	51	1	15	He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn over all creation.
B051C001V016	51	1	16	For by him all things in heaven and on earth were created, things visible and invisible, whether they are kings, lords, rulers, or powers. All things have been created through him and for him.
B051C001V017	51	1	17	He himself existed before all things, and by him all things hold together.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	He is also the head of the body, which is the church. He is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, so that he himself might have first place in everything.
B051C001V019	51	1	19	For God was pleased to have all of his fullness live in him.
B051C001V020	51	1	20	Through him he also reconciled all things to himself, whether things on earth or things in heaven, thus making peace through the blood of his cross.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	You who were once alienated and hostile in mind, doing evil deeds,
B051C001V022	51	1	22	he has now reconciled by the death of his physical body so that he might present you holy, blameless, and without fault before him.
B051C001V023	51	1	23	However, you must remain firmly established and steadfast in the faith, without being moved from the hope of the gospel that you heard, which has been proclaimed to every creature under heaven and of which I, Paul, have become a servant.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	Now I am rejoicing in my sufferings for you and completing in my flesh whatever remains of Christ's sufferings on behalf of his body, which is the church.
B051C001V025	51	1	25	I became its servant according to God's commission that was given to me for you, so that I might fulfill the ministry of the word of God.
B051C001V026	51	1	26	This secret was hidden throughout the ages and generations but has now been revealed to his saints,
B051C001V027	51	1	27	to whom God wanted to make known the glorious riches of this secret among the Gentiles—which is Christ in you, the hope of glory.
B051C001V028	51	1	28	It is he whom we proclaim as we admonish everyone and teach everyone with all wisdom, so that we may present everyone mature in Christ.
B051C001V029	51	1	29	I work hard and struggle to do this according to his energy that powerfully works in me.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	For I want you to know how much I struggle for you, for those in Laodicea, and for all who have never seen me face to face.
B051C002V002	51	2	2	Because they are united in love, I pray that their hearts may be encouraged by all the riches that come from a complete understanding of the full knowledge of Christ, who is the secret of God.
B051C002V003	51	2	3	In him are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	I say this so that no one will mislead you with nice-sounding rhetoric.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For although I am absent in body, I am with you in spirit, rejoicing to see how stable you are and how firm your faith in Christ is.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	So then, just as you have received Christ Jesus the Lord, continue to live in him.
B051C002V007	51	2	7	For you have been rooted in him and are being built up and strengthened in the faith, just as you were taught, while you overflow with thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	See to it that no one enslaves you through philosophy and empty deceit according to human tradition, according to the basic principles of the world, and not according to Christ.
B051C002V009	51	2	9	For in him the whole fullness of God lives in bodily form.
B051C002V010	51	2	10	And you have been brought to fullness in him, who is the head of every ruler and authority.
B051C002V011	51	2	11	In him you were also circumcised with a circumcision performed without human hands by stripping off the corrupt nature in the circumcision performed by Christ.
B051C002V012	51	2	12	When you were buried with him in baptism, you were also raised with him through faith in the power of God, who raised him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	Even when you were dead because of your offenses and the uncircumcision of your flesh, God made you alive with him when he forgave us all of our offenses,
B051C002V014	51	2	14	having erased the charges that were brought against us with their decrees that were hostile to us. He took those charges away when he nailed them to the cross.
B051C002V015	51	2	15	And when he had disarmed the rulers and the authorities, he made a public spectacle of them, triumphing over them in the cross.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Therefore, let no one judge you in matters of food and drink or with respect to a festival, a new moon, or a Sabbath day.
B051C002V017	51	2	17	These are a shadow of the things to come, but the reality belongs to Christ.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no one who delights in humility and the worship of angels cheat you out of the prize by boasting about what he has seen. Such a person is puffed up without cause by his carnal mind.
B051C002V019	51	2	19	He does not hold on to the head, from whom the whole body, which is nourished and held together by its joints and ligaments, grows with a growth that comes from God.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	If you have died with Christ to the basic principles of the world, why are you submitting to its decrees as though you still lived in the world?
B051C002V021	51	2	21	“Don't handle this! Don't taste or touch that!”
B051C002V022	51	2	22	All of these things will be destroyed through use because they are based on human commands and teachings.
B051C002V023	51	2	23	These things have the appearance of wisdom in promoting self-made religion, humility, and harsh treatment of the body, but they have no value against self-indulgence.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	Therefore, if you have been raised with Christ, keep focusing on the things that are above, where Christ is seated at the right hand of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Keep your minds on things that are above, not on things that are on the earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you have died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	When Christ your life is revealed, then you, too, will be revealed with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	So put to death your worldly impulses: sexual sin, impurity, passion, evil desire, and greed (which is idolatry).
B051C003V006	51	3	6	It is because of these things that the wrath of God is coming on those who are disobedient.
B051C003V007	51	3	7	You used to behave like them when you were living among them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now you must also get rid of anger, wrath, malice, slander, obscene language from your mouth, and all such sins.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another, for you have stripped off the old man with its practices
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and have clothed yourselves with the new man, which is being renewed into full knowledge according to the image of the one who created it.
B051C003V011	51	3	11	Where this happens, there is no Greek or Jew, circumcised or uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave, or free person. Instead, Christ is all and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Therefore, as God's chosen ones, holy and loved, clothe yourselves with compassion, kindness, humility, meekness, and patience.
B051C003V013	51	3	13	Put up with one another and forgive each other if anyone has a complaint against another. Just as the Lord has forgiven you, you also should forgive.
B051C003V014	51	3	14	Above all, clothe yourselves with love, which ties everything together in unity.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	Let the peace of Christ also rule in your hearts, to which you were called in one body, and be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	Let the word of Christ dwell in you with all richness and wisdom, teaching and admonishing one another with psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, and singing to God with thankfulness in your hearts.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	And whatever you do, in word or deed, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, submit yourselves to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives, and do not be harsh with them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in everything, for this is pleasing to the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, do not make your children resentful, lest they become discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Slaves, obey your earthly masters in everything, not only while being watched in order to please them, but with a sincere heart, fearing the Lord.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	Whatever you do, work at it wholeheartedly as though you were doing it for the Lord and not merely for people.
B051C003V024	51	3	24	You know that it is from the Lord that you will receive the inheritance as a reward. It is the Lord Christ whom you are serving!
B051C003V025	51	3	25	For the person who does what is wrong will be paid back for what he has done, and there is no favoritism.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, treat your slaves with justice and fairness, for you know that you also have a Master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Devote yourselves to prayer. Be alert when you pray with thanksgiving.
B051C004V003	51	4	3	At the same time also pray for us—that God would open before us a door for the word so that we may tell the secret about Christ, for which I have been imprisoned.
B051C004V004	51	4	4	May I reveal it as clearly as I should!
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Behave wisely toward outsiders, making the best use of your time.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let your speech always be gracious, seasoned with salt, so that you may know how you ought to answer everyone.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	Tychicus will tell you everything that has happened to me. He is a dear brother, a faithful minister, and a fellow servant in the Lord.
B051C004V008	51	4	8	I am sending him to you for this very reason, so that you may know how we are doing and that he may encourage your hearts.
B051C004V009	51	4	9	He is coming with Onesimus, that faithful and dear brother, who is one of you. They will tell you everything that is happening here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, sends his greetings, as does Mark, the cousin of Barnabas. You have received instructions about him. If he comes to you, welcome him.
B051C004V011	51	4	11	Jesus, who is called Justus, also greets you. These are the only ones of the circumcision who are fellow workers for the kingdom of God. They have been an encouragement to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ Jesus, sends you his greetings. He is always wrestling in his prayers for you, so that you may stand mature and completely convinced of the entire will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I can testify on his behalf that he has a deep concern for you and for those in Laodicea and in Hieropolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas greet you.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Give my greetings to the brothers in Laodicea, especially to Nympha and the church that is in her house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	When this letter has been read among you, have it read also in the church of the Laodiceans. And be sure to read the one from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	Tell Archippus, “See that you complete the ministry you have received in the Lord.”
B051C004V018	51	4	18	This greeting is by my own hand—“Paul.” Remember my imprisonment. May grace be with you! Amen.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	From Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in union with God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We always thank God for all of you when we mention you in our prayers.
B052C001V003	52	1	3	In the presence of our God and Father, we constantly remember how your faith is active, your love is hard at work, and your hope in our Lord Jesus Christ is enduring.
B052C001V004	52	1	4	Brothers whom God loves, we know that he has chosen you,
B052C001V005	52	1	5	for the gospel we brought did not come to you in words only, but also with power, with the Holy Spirit, and with deep conviction. Indeed, you know what kind of people we proved to be while we were with you, acting on your behalf.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	You became imitators of us and of the Lord. In spite of a great deal of suffering, you welcomed the word with the joy that the Holy Spirit produces.
B052C001V007	52	1	7	As a result, you became a model for all the believers in Macedonia and Achaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	From you the word of the Lord has spread out not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but also in every place where your faith in God has become known. As a result, we do not need to say anything.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For people keep telling us what kind of welcome you gave us and how you turned away from idols to serve a living and true God
B052C001V010	52	1	10	and to wait for his Son whom he raised from the dead to come back from heaven. This Jesus is the one who rescues us from the coming wrath.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	For you yourselves know, brothers, that our visit to you was not a waste of time.
B052C002V002	52	2	2	As you know, we suffered persecution and were mistreated in Philippi. Yet we were encouraged by our God to tell you his gospel in spite of strong opposition.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our appeal does not spring from deceit, impure motives, or trickery.
B052C002V004	52	2	4	Rather, because we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the gospel, we speak as we do, not trying to please people but God, who tests our motives.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	As you know, we did not come with words of flattery or with a scheme to make money. God is our witness!
B052C002V006	52	2	6	We did not seek praise from people—from you or from anyone else—
B052C002V007	52	2	7	even though as apostles of Christ we might have made such demands. Instead, we were gentle among you, like a nursing mother tenderly caring for her own children.
B052C002V008	52	2	8	We cared so deeply for you that we were determined to share with you not only the gospel of God but our very lives. That is how dear you were to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	You remember, brothers, our labor and toil. We worked night and day so that we would not become a burden to any of you while we proclaimed the gospel of God to you.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You and God are witnesses of how pure, honest, and blameless our conduct was among you who believe.
B052C002V011	52	2	11	You know very well that we treated each of you the way a father treats his children.
B052C002V012	52	2	12	We comforted and encouraged you, urging you to live in a manner worthy of the God who calls you into his kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	Here is another reason why we constantly give thanks to God: When you received God's word, which you heard from us, you did not accept it as the word of humans but for what it really is—the word of God, which is at work in you who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you, brothers, became imitators of the churches of God in Judea that are in union with Christ Jesus. You suffered the same persecutions from the people of your own country as they did from those Jews
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed the Lord Jesus and the prophets and have persecuted us. They are displeasing to God and are the enemies of all people,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	because they try to keep us from telling the Gentiles how they can be saved. The result is that they are always adding to the measure of their sins. However, wrath has come on them at last!
B052C002V017	52	2	17	Brothers, although we have been separated from you for a little while—in person but not in heart—we desire with great eagerness to see you again face to face.
B052C002V018	52	2	18	That is why we wanted to come to you. Certainly I, Paul, time and again wanted to come, but Satan blocked our way.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	After all, who is our hope, joy, or reason for boasting in the presence of our Lord Jesus at his coming? It is you, isn't it?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	Yes, you are our glory and joy!
B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore, when we could stand it no longer, we decided to remain alone in Athens
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and send Timothy, our brother and fellow worker for God in the gospel of Christ, to strengthen and encourage you in your faith,
B052C003V003	52	3	3	so that no one would be shaken by these persecutions. Indeed, you yourselves know that we were destined for this.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	In fact, when we were with you, we told you ahead of time that we were going to suffer persecution. And as you know, that is what happened.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	But when I could stand it no longer, I sent Timothy to find out about your faith. I was afraid that the tempter had tempted you in some way, and that our work had been a waste of time.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But Timothy has just now come back to us from you and has told us the good news about your faith and love. He also told us that you always have fond memories of us and want to see us, just as we want to see you.
B052C003V007	52	3	7	That's why, brothers, in all our distress and persecution we have been encouraged about you by your faith.
B052C003V008	52	3	8	For now we can go on living, as long as you continue to stand firm in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	How can we thank God enough for you in return for all the joy that we have in God's presence because of you?
B052C003V010	52	3	10	We pray very hard night and day that we may see you again face to face, so that we may supply whatever is lacking in your faith.
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now may our God and Father and our Lord Jesus guide us to you.
B052C003V012	52	3	12	May the Lord greatly increase your love for each other and for all people, just as we love you.
B052C003V013	52	3	13	Then your hearts will be strong in holiness and blameless in the presence of our God and Father when our Lord Jesus comes with all his saints.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	Now then, brothers, you learned from us how you ought to live and to please God, as in fact you are doing. We ask and encourage you in the Lord to do so even more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	You know what instructions we gave you through the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For it is God's will that you be sanctified: You must abstain from sexual immorality;
B052C004V004	52	4	4	each of you must know how to control his own body in holiness and honor,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	not with passion and lust like the Gentiles who do not know God;
B052C004V006	52	4	6	and you must never take advantage of or exploit a brother in this regard. For the Lord is an avenger in all these things, just as we already told you and warned you.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For God did not call us to impurity but to holiness.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore, whoever rejects this instruction is not rejecting human authority but God, who gives you his Holy Spirit.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	Now you do not need anyone to write to you about brotherly love, since you have been taught by God to love each other.
B052C004V010	52	4	10	In fact, you are showing love to all the brothers throughout Macedonia. But we urge you, brothers, to do this even more.
B052C004V011	52	4	11	Also, make it your goal to live quietly, to mind your own business, and to work with your own hands, as we instructed you,
B052C004V012	52	4	12	so that you may win the respect of outsiders, and have need of nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	But we do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, about those who have died, so that you may not grieve like other people who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again, even so it is through Jesus that God will bring back with him those who have died.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	For this we declare to you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive and remain until the coming of the Lord will by no means precede those who have died.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	With a shout of command, with the archangel's call, and with the sound of God's trumpet, the Lord himself will come down from heaven, and the dead in Christ will rise first.
B052C004V017	52	4	17	Then we who are alive and remain will be caught up in the clouds together with them to meet the Lord in the air. And so we will be with the Lord forever.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	So then, encourage one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	Now you do not need to have anything written to you about times and dates, brothers,
B052C005V002	52	5	2	for you yourselves know very well that the Day of the Lord will come like a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	When people say, “There is peace and security,” destruction will strike them as suddenly as labor pains come to a pregnant woman, and they will not be able to escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	However, brothers, you are not in the darkness, in order that the day might surprise you like a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	For all of you are children of light and children of day. We do not belong to the night or to darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Therefore, let us not fall asleep like others do, but let us stay awake and be sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For people who go to sleep, go to sleep at night; and people who get drunk, get drunk at night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But since we belong to the day, let us be sober. We must put on the breastplate of faith and love, and the hope of salvation as a helmet.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For God has not destined us for wrath but for obtaining salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died for us in order that, whether we are awake or asleep, we may live together with him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	So then, encourage one another and build each other up, as you are doing.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	Brothers, we ask you to show your appreciation for those who work among you, set an example for you in the Lord, and instruct you.
B052C005V013	52	5	13	Hold them in the highest regard in love because of their work. Live in peace with each other.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	We urge you, brothers, to instruct those who are idle, cheer up those who are discouraged, and help those who are weak. Be patient with everyone.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	Make sure that no one pays back evil for evil. Instead, always pursue what is good for each other and for everyone else.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Always be joyful.
B052C005V017	52	5	17	Continually be prayerful.
B052C005V018	52	5	18	In everything be thankful, because this is God's will in Christ Jesus for you.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not put out the Spirit's fire.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophecies.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	Instead, test everything. Hold on to what is good,
B052C005V022	52	5	22	but keep away from every kind of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	May the God of peace himself make you holy in every way. And may your whole being—spirit, soul, and body—be kept blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	The one who calls you is faithful, and he will do this.
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brothers, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I order you by the Lord to have this letter read to all the brothers.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you! Amen.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	From Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in union with God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V002	53	1	2	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B053C001V003	53	1	3	At all times we are obligated to thank God for you, brothers. It is right to do this because your faith is growing all the time and the love of every one of you for each other is increasing.
B053C001V004	53	1	4	As a result, we boast about you among God's churches—about your endurance and faith through all the persecutions and afflictions you are experiencing.
B053C001V005	53	1	5	This is evidence of God's righteous judgment and is intended to make you worthy of God's kingdom, for which you are suffering.
B053C001V006	53	1	6	Certainly it is right for God to pay back those who afflict you with affliction
B053C001V007	53	1	7	and to give us who are afflicted relief when the Lord Jesus is revealed from heaven with his mighty angels
B053C001V008	53	1	8	in blazing fire. He will take revenge on those who do not know God and on those who refuse to obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus.
B053C001V009	53	1	9	Such people will suffer the punishment of eternal destruction by being separated from the Lord's presence and from his glorious power
B053C001V010	53	1	10	when he comes to be glorified by his saints and to be regarded with wonder on that day by all who have believed—including you, because you believed our testimony.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	With this in mind, we always pray for you, asking that our God might make you worthy of his calling and that through his power he might help you accomplish every good desire and faithful work.
B053C001V012	53	1	12	That way the name of our Lord Jesus will be glorified by you, and you by him, according to the grace of our God and Lord, Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	Now we ask you, brothers, regarding the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ and our gathering together to him,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	not to be so quickly upset or alarmed when someone claims that we said either by some spirit, conversation, or letter that the Day of the Lord has already come.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Do not let anyone deceive you in any way, for that day cannot come unless the rebellion takes place first and the man of sin, who is destined for destruction, is revealed.
B053C002V004	53	2	4	He opposes and exalts himself above every so-called god and object of worship. As a result, he seats himself in the sanctuary of God and declares himself to be God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Don't you remember that I repeatedly told you about these things when I was still with you?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	You know what it is that is now holding him back, so that he will be revealed when his time comes.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the secret of this lawlessness is already at work, but only until the person now holding it back gets out of the way.
B053C002V008	53	2	8	Then the lawless one will be revealed, whom the Lord will destroy with the breath of his mouth, rendering him powerless by the manifestation of his coming.
B053C002V009	53	2	9	The coming of the lawless one will be accompanied by the power of Satan. He will use every kind of power, including miraculous signs, lying wonders,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and every type of evil to deceive those who are dying, those who refused to love the truth that would save them.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	For this reason, God will send them a powerful delusion so that they will believe the lie.
B053C002V012	53	2	12	Then all who have not believed the truth but have taken pleasure in unrighteousness will be condemned.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	At all times we are obligated to thank God for you, brothers who are loved by the Lord, because God chose you to be the first fruits for salvation through sanctification by the Spirit and through faith in the truth.
B053C002V014	53	2	14	With this purpose in mind, he called you through our proclamation of the gospel so that you would obtain the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	So then, brothers, stand firm, and cling to the traditions that you were taught by us, either by word of mouth or by our letter.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	May our Lord Jesus Christ himself and God our Father, who loved us and by his grace gave us eternal comfort and good hope,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	encourage your hearts and strengthen you in every good work and word.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Finally, brothers, pray for us—that the word of the Lord may spread rapidly, and that it may be honored the way it is among you.
B053C003V002	53	3	2	Also pray that we may be rescued from worthless and evil people, since not everyone holds to the faith.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful and will strengthen you and protect you from the evil one.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	We have confidence in the Lord that you are doing and will continue to do what we command.
B053C003V005	53	3	5	May the Lord direct your hearts to the love of God and to the endurance of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ we command you, brothers, to keep away from every brother who is living in idleness and not living according to the tradition that they received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you yourselves know what you must do to imitate us. We did not live in idleness among you.
B053C003V008	53	3	8	We did not eat anyone's food without paying for it. Instead, with toil and labor we worked night and day in order not to be a burden to any of you.
B053C003V009	53	3	9	It is not as though we did not have that right, but, we wanted to give you an example to follow.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	While we were with you, we gave this order: “If anyone doesn't want to work, he shouldn't eat.”
B053C003V011	53	3	11	We hear that some of you are living in idleness. You are not busy working—you are busy interfering in other people's lives!
B053C003V012	53	3	12	We order and encourage such people by the Lord Jesus Christ to do their work quietly and to earn their own living.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	Brothers, do not get tired of doing what is right.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	If anyone does not obey what we say in this letter, take note of him. Have nothing to do with him so that he will feel ashamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Yet, don't treat him like an enemy, but warn him like a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	Now may the Lord of peace give you his peace at all times and in every way. May the Lord be with all of you.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	I, Paul, am writing this greeting with my own hand. This is the mark in every letter of mine. It is the way I write.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you. Amen.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the command of God our Savior and Christ Jesus our hope,
B054C001V002	54	1	2	to Timothy, my genuine child in the faith. May grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord be yours!
B054C001V003	54	1	3	When I was on my way to Macedonia, I urged you to stay in Ephesus so that you could instruct certain people to stop teaching false doctrine
B054C001V004	54	1	4	and occupying themselves with myths and endless genealogies. These things promote controversies rather than God's ongoing purpose, which involves faith.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	The goal of this instruction is love that flows from a pure heart, from a clear conscience, and from a sincere faith.
B054C001V006	54	1	6	Some people have left these qualities behind and have turned to fruitless discussion.
B054C001V007	54	1	7	They want to be teachers of the law, yet they do not understand either what they are talking about or the things about which they speak so confidently.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	Of course, we know that the law is good if a person uses it legitimately,
B054C001V009	54	1	9	that is, if he understands that the law is not intended for righteous people but for lawbreakers and rebels, for ungodly people and sinners, for those who are unholy and irreverent, for those who kill their fathers, their mothers, or other people,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	for those involved in sexual immorality, for homosexuals, for kidnappers, for liars, for false witnesses, and for whatever else goes against the healthy teaching
B054C001V011	54	1	11	that agrees with the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which he entrusted to me.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who gives me strength, that he has considered me faithful and has appointed me to his service.
B054C001V013	54	1	13	In the past I was a blasphemer, a persecutor, and a violent man. But I received mercy because I acted ignorantly in my unbelief,
B054C001V014	54	1	14	and the grace of our Lord overflowed toward me, along with the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	This saying is trustworthy and deserves complete acceptance:	To this world Christ Jesus came,Sinful people to reclaim.I am the worst of them.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	But for that very reason I received mercy, so that in me, as the worst sinner, Christ Jesus might demonstrate all of his patience as an example for those who would believe in him for eternal life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	Now to the King Eternal—the immortal, invisible, and only God—be honor and glory forever and ever! Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	Timothy, my child, I am giving you this instruction in keeping with the prophecies made earlier about you, so that by following them you may continue to fight the good fight
B054C001V019	54	1	19	with faith and a good conscience. By ignoring their consciences, some people have destroyed their faith like a wrecked ship.
B054C001V020	54	1	20	These include Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I handed over to Satan so that they may learn not to blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	First of all, then, I urge you to offer petitions, prayers, intercessions, and expressions of thanks for all people,
B054C002V002	54	2	2	for kings, and for everyone who has authority, so that we might lead a quiet and peaceful life with all godliness and dignity.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	This is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Savior,
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who wants all people to be saved and to come to a full knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	There is one God. There is also one mediator between God and human beings—a human, Christ Jesus.
B054C002V006	54	2	6	He gave himself as a ransom for all, a fact that was acknowledged at the right time.
B054C002V007	54	2	7	For this reason I was appointed to be a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth. (I am telling you the truth. I am not lying.)
B054C002V008	54	2	8	Therefore, I want the men to offer prayers in every place, lifting up holy hands without being angry or argumentative.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	Women, for their part, should display their beauty by dressing modestly and decently in appropriate clothes, not by braiding their hair or by wearing gold, pearls, or expensive clothes,
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but through good works. This is proper for women who claim to have reverence for God.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	A woman must learn quietly with full submission.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	Moreover, I do not allow a woman to teach or to have authority over a man. Instead, she is to be quiet.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam was formed first, then Eve.
B054C002V014	54	2	14	And it was not Adam who was deceived. It was the woman who was deceived and became a lawbreaker.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	However, women will be saved by having children, if they continue to have faith, love, and holiness, along with good judgment.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	This saying is trustworthy:	The one who would an elder be,		A noble task desires he.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	Therefore, an elder must be blameless, the husband of one wife, stable, sensible, respectable, a lover of strangers, and teachable.
B054C003V003	54	3	3	He must not drink excessively or be a violent person, but instead be gentle. He must not be argumentative or a lover of money.
B054C003V004	54	3	4	He must manage his own family well and have children who are submissive and respectful in every way.
B054C003V005	54	3	5	For if a man does not know how to manage his own family, how can he take care of God's church?
B054C003V006	54	3	6	He must not be a recent convert, or he might become arrogant and fall into the condemnation of the devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	He must be well thought of by outsiders, lest he fall into disgrace and the trap set for him by the devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Deacons, too, must be serious. They must not be two-faced, addicted to wine, or greedy for money.
B054C003V009	54	3	9	They must hold firmly to the secret of the faith with clear consciences.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	But they must first be tested. Then, if they prove to be blameless, they may become deacons.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	Their wives must also be serious. They must not be gossips, but instead be stable and trustworthy in everything.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	Deacons must be husbands of one wife and must manage their children and their families well.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	Those deacons who serve well gain an excellent reputation for themselves and will have great assurance in their faith in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	I hope to come to you soon. However, I'm writing this to you
B054C003V015	54	3	15	in case I am delayed so that you may know how one is to behave in God's household, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and foundation of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	By common confession, the secret of our godly worship is great:	In flesh was he revealed to sight,Kept righteous by the Spirit's might,Adored by angels singing.	To nations was he manifest,Believing souls found peace and rest,Our Lord in heaven reigning!
B054C004V001	54	4	1	Now the Spirit says clearly that in the last times some people will abandon the faith by following deceitful spirits, the teachings of demons,
B054C004V002	54	4	2	and the hypocrisy of liars, whose consciences have been burned by a hot iron.
B054C004V003	54	4	3	They will try to stop people from marrying and from eating certain foods, which God created to be received with thanksgiving by those who believe and know the truth.
B054C004V004	54	4	4	For everything God created is good, and nothing should be rejected if it is received with thanksgiving,
B054C004V005	54	4	5	because it is sanctified by the word of God and prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	If you continue to point these things out to the brothers, you will be a good servant of Christ Jesus, nourished by the words of the faith and the healthy teaching that you have followed closely.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	Do not have anything to do with godless myths and fables of old women, but train yourself in godliness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	Physical exercise is of limited value, but	Godliness is very dear,A pledge of life, both there and here.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	This saying is trustworthy and deserves complete acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	To this end we work hard and struggle, because we have set our hope on the living God, who is the Savior of all people, that is, of those who believe.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	These are the things you must insist on and teach.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Do not let anyone look down on you because you are young, but be an example for other believers in your speech, behavior, love, faithfulness, and purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I arrive, concentrate on the public reading of Scripture, on exhorting, and on teaching.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, which was given to you through prophecy, accompanied by the laying on of the elders’ hands.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Think on these things. Devote your life to them so that everyone can see your progress.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Pay close attention to your life and your teaching. Persevere in these things, for if you do this, you will save both yourself and those who listen to you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Never speak harshly to an older man, but appeal to him as if he were your father. Treat younger men like brothers,
B054C005V002	54	5	2	older women like mothers, and younger women like sisters, with absolutely purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honor widows who are really widows.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	But if a widow has children or grandchildren, they must first learn to respect their own family by repaying their parents, for this is pleasing in God's sight.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	A woman who is really a widow and is left all alone has placed her hope in God and devotes herself to petitions and prayers night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But the widow who lives for pleasure is dead while she lives.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	Continue to give these instructions so that they may be blameless.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	If anyone does not take care of his own relatives, especially his immediate family, he has denied the faith and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	A widow may be put on the widows' list if she is at least sixty years old and has been the wife of one husband.
B054C005V010	54	5	10	She must be well known for her good works as a woman who has raised children, welcomed strangers, washed the saints’ feet, helped the suffering, and devoted herself to doing good in every way.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But do not include younger widows on your list. For whenever their natural desires cause them to lose their devotion to Christ, they want to remarry.
B054C005V012	54	5	12	They receive condemnation because they have set aside their previous pledge.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	At the same time, they also learn how to be lazy while going from house to house. Not only this, but they even become gossips and keep busy by interfering in other people's lives, saying things they should not say.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	Therefore, I want younger widows to remarry, have children, manage their homes, and not give the enemy any chance to ridicule them.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For some widows have already turned away to follow Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any woman is a believer and has relatives who are widows, she should help them. The church should not be burdened so that it can help those who really are widows.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	Elders who handle their duties well should be considered worthy of double compensation, especially those who work hard at preaching and teaching.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the Scripture says, “You must not muzzle an ox while it is treading out grain,” and
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Do not accept an accusation against an elder unless it is supported by two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	As for those who keep on sinning, rebuke them in front of everyone so that the others will also be afraid.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	In the sight of God, Christ Jesus, and the chosen angels, I solemnly call on you to carry out these instructions without prejudice, doing nothing on the basis of partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Do not ordain anyone hastily. Do not participate in the sins of others. Keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	Stop drinking only water, but use a little wine for your stomach because of your frequent illnesses.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	The sins of some people are obvious, going ahead of them to judgment. The sins of others follow them there.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	In the same way, good works are obvious, and those that are not cannot remain hidden.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	All who are under the yoke of slavery should regard their own masters as deserving of the highest respect, so that the name of God and our teaching may not be discredited.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	Moreover, those who have believing masters should not be disrespectful to them because they are fellow believers. Instead, they must serve them even better, because those who benefit from their service are believers and dear to them. These are the things you must teach and exhort.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If anyone teaches false doctrine and refuses to agree with the healthy words of our Lord Jesus Christ and godly teaching,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	he is a conceited person and does not understand anything. He has an unhealthy craving for arguments and debates. This produces jealousy, rivalry, slander, evil suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	and incessant conflict between people who are depraved in mind and deprived of truth. They think that godliness is a way to make a profit.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	Of course, godliness with contentment does bring a great profit.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we did not bring anything into the world, and surely we cannot take anything out of it.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	So as long as we have food and clothes, we will be satisfied with these.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But people who want to get rich keep toppling into temptation and are trapped by many stupid and harmful desires that plunge them into destruction and ruin.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil. Some people, in their eagerness to get rich, have wandered away from the faith and pierced themselves with much pain.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But you, man of God, must flee from all these things. Instead, you must pursue righteousness, godliness, faithfulness, love, endurance, and gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Fight the good fight for the faith. Keep your hold on eternal life, to which you were called and about which you gave a good testimony in front of many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	In the sight of God, who gives life to everything, and in the sight of Christ Jesus, who gave a good testimony before Pontius Pilate, I solemnly charge you
B054C006V014	54	6	14	to keep this command stainless and blameless until the appearance of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B054C006V015	54	6	15	At the right time God will make him known. He is the blessed and only Ruler, the King of kings and Lord of lords.
B054C006V016	54	6	16	He alone has endless life and lives in inaccessible light. No one has ever seen him, nor can anyone see him. Honor and eternal power belong to him! Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Tell those who are rich in the present world not to be arrogant and not to place their confidence in anything as uncertain as riches. Instead, let them place their confidence in God, who lavishly provides us with everything for our enjoyment.
B054C006V018	54	6	18	They are to do good, to be rich in good works, to be generous, and to share.
B054C006V019	54	6	19	By doing this they store up a treasure for themselves that is a good foundation for the future, so that they can take hold of the life that is real.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	Timothy, guard what has been entrusted to you. Avoid the pointless discussions and contradictions of what is falsely called knowledge.
B054C006V021	54	6	21	Although some claim to have it, they have abandoned the faith. May grace be with all of you!
B055C001V001	55	1	1	From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by God's will in keeping with the promise of life that is in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	to Timothy, my dear child. May grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord be yours!
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I constantly thank my God—whom I serve with a clear conscience, as my ancestors did—when I remember you in my prayers night and day,
B055C001V004	55	1	4	recalling your tears and longing to see you so that I can be filled with joy.
B055C001V005	55	1	5	I am reminded of your sincere faith, which lived first in your grandmother Lois and your mother Eunice, and I am convinced that this faith also lives in you.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	For this reason, I am reminding you to fan into flames the gift of God that is within you through the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God did not give us a spirit of timidity but one of power, love, and self-discipline.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Therefore, never be ashamed of the testimony about our Lord or of me, his prisoner. Instead, by God's power, join me in suffering for the sake of the gospel.
B055C001V009	55	1	9	He saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our own works but according to his own purpose and the grace that was given to us in Christ Jesus before time began.
B055C001V010	55	1	10	Now, however, it has been revealed through the coming of our Savior Christ Jesus, who has destroyed death and through the gospel has brought life and release from death into full view.
B055C001V011	55	1	11	For the sake of this gospel I was appointed to be a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.
B055C001V012	55	1	12	That is why I suffer as I do. However, I am not ashamed, for I know the one in whom I have put my trust, and I'm convinced that he is able to protect what he has entrusted to me until that day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold on to the pattern of healthy teachings that you have heard from me, along with the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	With the help of the Holy Spirit who lives in us, protect the good treasure that has been entrusted to you.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	You know that everyone in Asia has abandoned me, including Phygelus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	May the Lord grant mercy to the family of Onesiphorus, for he often took care of me and was not ashamed that I was a prisoner.
B055C001V017	55	1	17	Instead, when he arrived in Rome he searched diligently for me and found me.
B055C001V018	55	1	18	May the Lord grant that he finds mercy from the Lord on that day. You know very well how much he assisted me in Ephesus.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	As for you, my child, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.
B055C002V002	55	2	2	What you have heard from me through many witnesses entrust to faithful people who will be able to teach others as well.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	Join me in suffering like a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No one serving in the military gets mixed up in civilian matters, for his aim is to please his commanding officer.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	Moreover, no one who is an athlete wins a prize unless he competes according to the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	Furthermore, it is the hard working farmer who should have the first share of the crops.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Think about what I am saying. The Lord will help you to understand all these things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Meditate on Jesus Christ, who was raised from the dead and is a descendant of David. This is the gospel I tell others.
B055C002V009	55	2	9	Because of it I am experiencing trouble, even to the point of being chained like a criminal. However, God's word is not chained.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	For that reason, I endure everything for the sake of those who have been chosen so that they, too, may receive the salvation that is in Christ Jesus, along with eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	This saying is trustworthy:	In dying with Christ,true life we gain.
B055C002V012	55	2	12	Enduring, we with him shall reign.Who him denies,he will disclaim.
B055C002V013	55	2	13	Our faith may fail,his never wanes—	For thus he is,he cannot change!
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind others about these things, and warn them in the sight of God not to argue over words. Arguing does not do any good but only destroys those who are listening.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Do your best to present yourself to God as an approved worker who has nothing to be ashamed of, handling the word of truth with precision.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	However, avoid pointless discussions. For people will become more and more ungodly,
B055C002V017	55	2	17	and what they say will spread everywhere like gangrene. Hymenaeus and Philetus are like that.
B055C002V018	55	2	18	They have abandoned the truth by claiming that the resurrection has already taken place, and so they destroy the faith of others.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	However, God's solid foundation still stands. It has this inscription on it: “The Lord knows those who belong to him,” and “Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord must turn away from evil.”
B055C002V020	55	2	20	In a large house there are not only utensils made of gold and silver, but also those made of wood and clay. Some are for special use, while others are for ordinary use.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	Therefore, if anyone stops associating with these people, he will become a special utensil, set apart for the owner's use, prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	Flee from youthful passions. Instead, pursue righteousness, faithfulness, love, and peace together with those who call on the Lord with a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	Do not have anything to do with foolish and stupid discussions, because you know they breed arguments.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	A servant of the Lord must not argue. Instead, he must be kind to everyone, teachable, willing to suffer wrong,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	and gentle in refuting his opponents. After all, maybe God will allow them to repent and to come to a full knowledge of the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	so that they might escape from the devil's snare, even though they've been held captive by him to do his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	You must realize, however, that in the last days difficult times will come.
B055C003V002	55	3	2	People will be lovers of themselves, lovers of money, boastful, arrogant, abusive, disobedient to their parents, ungrateful, unholy,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	unfeeling, uncooperative, slanderous, degenerate, brutal, hateful of what is good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	traitors, reckless, conceited, and lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God.
B055C003V005	55	3	5	They will hold to an outward form of godliness but deny its power. Stay away from such people.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For some of these men go into homes and deceive foolish women who are burdened with sins and swayed by all kinds of desires.
B055C003V007	55	3	7	These women are always studying but are never able to arrive at a full knowledge of the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	Just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these men oppose the truth. They are depraved in mind and their faith is a counterfeit.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they will not get very far because, as in the case of those two men, their stupidity will be plain to everyone.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	But you have observed my teaching, my way of life, my purpose, my faith, my patience, my love, my endurance,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	and my persecutions and sufferings that happened to me in Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra. What persecutions I endured! Yet the Lord rescued me from all of them.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	Indeed, all who want to live a godly life in union with Christ Jesus will be persecuted.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But evil people and impostors will go from bad to worse as they deceive others and are themselves deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But as for you, continue in what you have learned and found to be true, because you know from whom you learned it.
B055C003V015	55	3	15	From infancy you have known the Holy Scriptures that are able to give you the wisdom you need for salvation through faith in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	All Scripture is God-breathed and is useful for teaching, for reproof, for correction, and for training in righteousness,
B055C003V017	55	3	17	so that the man of God may be complete and thoroughly equipped for every good work.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	In the presence of God and Christ Jesus, who is going to judge those who are living and those who are dead, and in view of his appearing and his kingdom, I solemnly appeal to you
B055C004V002	55	4	2	to proclaim the message. Be ready to do this whether or not the time is convenient. Refute, warn, and encourage with the utmost patience when you teach.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For the time will come when people will not put up with healthy doctrine but with itching ears will surround themselves with teachers who cater to their own needs.
B055C004V004	55	4	4	They will refuse to listen to the truth and will turn to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But you must be clear-headed about everything. Endure suffering. Do the work of an evangelist. Devote yourself completely to your ministry.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being poured out as an offering, and the time for my departure has come.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have fought the good fight. I have completed the race. I have kept the faith.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	The victor's crown of righteousness is now waiting for me, which the Lord, the righteous Judge, will give to me on that day, and not only to me but also to all who eagerly wait for his appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Do your best to come to me soon.
B055C004V010	55	4	10	For Demas, having fallen in love with this present world, has abandoned me and has gone to Thessalonica. Crescens has gone to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Only Luke is with me. Get Mark and bring him with you, for he is useful in my ministry.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	I have sent Tychicus to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	When you come, bring the coat I left with Carpus in Troas, as well as the scrolls and especially the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the metalworker did me a great deal of harm. The Lord will pay him back for what he did.
B055C004V015	55	4	15	You, too, must watch out for him, for he violently opposed our message.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first trial no one came to my defense. Everyone abandoned me. May it not be held against them!
B055C004V017	55	4	17	However, the Lord stood by me and gave me strength so that through me the message might be fully proclaimed and all the Gentiles could hear it. I was rescued out of a lion's mouth.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	The Lord will rescue me from every evil attack and will take me safely to his heavenly kingdom. Glory belongs to him forever and ever! Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Greet Prisca and Aquila and the family of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus stayed in Corinth, and I left Trophimus in Miletus because he was sick.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Do your best to come to me before winter. Eubulus sends you greetings, as do Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	May the Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with all of you! Amen.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	From Paul, a servant of God, and yet an apostle of Jesus Christ for the faith of God's elect and the full knowledge of the truth that leads to godliness,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	which is based on the hope of eternal life that God, who cannot lie, promised before the world began.
B056C001V003	56	1	3	At the right time he revealed his message through the proclamation that was entrusted to me by the command of God our Savior.
B056C001V004	56	1	4	To Titus, a genuine child in the faith we share. May grace and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior be yours!
B056C001V005	56	1	5	The reason I left you in Crete was to complete what still needed to be done and to appoint elders in every city, as I myself commanded you.
B056C001V006	56	1	6	An elder must be blameless. He must be the husband of one wife and have children who are believers and who are not accused of having wild lifestyles or of being rebellious.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	Because an overseer is God's administrator, he must be blameless. He must not be arrogant or irritable. He must not drink too much, be a violent person, or use shameful ways to make money.
B056C001V008	56	1	8	Instead, he must be a lover of strangers, a lover of goodness, sensible, honest, moral, and self-controlled.
B056C001V009	56	1	9	He must be devoted to the trustworthy message that is in agreement with our teaching, so that he may be able to encourage others with healthy doctrine and refute those who oppose it.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are many people who are rebellious, especially those who are converts from Judaism. They speak utter nonsense and deceive people.
B056C001V011	56	1	11	They must be silenced, because they are the kind of people who ruin whole families by teaching what they should not teach in order to make money in a shameful way.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	One of their very own prophets said,	“Liars ever, men of Crete,Savage brutes that live to eat.”
B056C001V013	56	1	13	That testimony is true. For this reason, refute them sharply so that they may become healthy in the faith
B056C001V014	56	1	14	and not pay attention to Jewish myths or commands given by people who reject the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	Everything is clean to those who are clean, but nothing is clean to those who are corrupt and unbelieving. Indeed, their very way of thinking and their consciences have been corrupted.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They claim to know God, but they deny him by their actions. They are detestable, disobedient, and disqualified to do anything good.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But as for you, teach what is consistent with healthy doctrine.
B056C002V002	56	2	2	Older men are to be sober, serious, sensible, and sound in faithfulness, love, and endurance.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	Likewise, older women are to show their reverence for God by their behavior. They are not to be gossips or addicted to alcohol, but to be examples of goodness.
B056C002V004	56	2	4	They should encourage the younger women to be lovers of their husbands, lovers of their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	sensible, pure, managers of their households, and kind, and to submit themselves to their husbands, lest the word of God be discredited.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Likewise, encourage the younger men to be sensible.
B056C002V007	56	2	7	Always set an example of good works. When you teach, show integrity and dignity.
B056C002V008	56	2	8	Use wholesome speech that cannot be condemned. Then any opponent will be ashamed because he cannot say anything bad about us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Slaves are to submit themselves to their masters in everything, aiming to please them and not argue with them
B056C002V010	56	2	10	or steal from them. Instead, they are to show complete and perfect loyalty, so that in every way they may make the teaching about God our Savior more attractive.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the grace of God has appeared, bringing salvation to all people.
B056C002V012	56	2	12	It trains us to renounce ungodly living and worldly passions so that we might live sensible, honest, and godly lives in the present world
B056C002V013	56	2	13	as we wait for the blessed hope and the glorious appearance of our great God and Savior, Jesus Christ.
B056C002V014	56	2	14	He gave himself for us to set us free from every wrong and to cleanse us so that we could be his special people who are enthusiastic about good works.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	These are the things you should say. Encourage and refute with full authority. Do not let anyone look down on you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Remind believers to submit themselves to rulers and authorities, to be obedient, and to be ready to do any honorable kind of work.
B056C003V002	56	3	2	They are not to insult anyone or be argumentative. Instead, they are to be gentle and show perfect courtesy to everyone.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	After all, we ourselves were once foolish, disobedient, and misled. We were slaves to many kinds of lusts and pleasures, spending our days in malice and jealousy. We were despised, and we hated one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	However,	In grace our Savior God appeared,His love for mankind to make clear.
B056C003V005	56	3	5	‘Twas not for deeds that we had done, But by his steadfast love alone,	He saved us through a second birth,Renewed us by the Spirit's work,
B056C003V006	56	3	6	And poured him out upon us, too,Through Jesus Christ our Savior true.
B056C003V007	56	3	7	And so, made right by his own grace,Eternal life we now embrace.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	This saying is trustworthy. I want you to insist on these things, so that those who have put their faith in God may devote themselves to good works. These things are good and helpful to other people.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But avoid foolish controversies, arguments about genealogies, quarrels, and fights about the law. These things are useless and worthless.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	Have nothing to do with a person who causes divisions after you have warned him once or twice.
B056C003V011	56	3	11	For you know that a person like this is corrupt and keeps on sinning, being self-condemned.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	As soon as I send Artemas to you, or perhaps Tychicus, do your best to come to me at Nicopolis, for I have decided to spend the winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Do all you can to send Zenas the expert in the law and Apollos on their way, and see that they have everything they need.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	Our own people should also learn to devote themselves to good works when urgent needs arise, lest they be unproductive.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All who are with me send you greetings. Greet those who love us in the faith. May grace be with all of you! Amen.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	From Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon our dear friend and fellow worker,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	to Apphia our sister, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house.
B057C001V003	57	1	3	May grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ be yours!
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I always thank my God when I mention you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	because I keep hearing about your love and the faith that you have toward the Lord Jesus and for all the saints.
B057C001V006	57	1	6	I pray that the sharing of your faith may become effective as you fully acknowledge every blessing that is ours in Christ.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For I have received considerable joy and encouragement from your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed, brother, through you.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	For this reason, although in Christ I have complete freedom to order you to do what is proper,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	I prefer to make my appeal on the basis of love. I, Paul, as an old man and now a prisoner of Christ Jesus,
B057C001V010	57	1	10	appeal to you on behalf of my child Onesimus, whose father I have become during my imprisonment.
B057C001V011	57	1	11	Once he was useless to you, but now he is very useful both to you and to me.
B057C001V012	57	1	12	I am sending him, that is, my own heart, back to you.
B057C001V013	57	1	13	I wanted to keep him with me so that he could serve me in your place during my imprisonment for the gospel.
B057C001V014	57	1	14	Yet I did not want to do anything without your consent, so that your good deed might not be something forced, but voluntary.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	Perhaps this is why he was separated from you for a while, so that you could have him back forever,
B057C001V016	57	1	16	no longer as a slave but better than a slave—as a dear brother, especially to me, but even more so to you, both as a person and as a believer.
B057C001V017	57	1	17	So if you consider me a partner, welcome him as you would welcome me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	If he has wronged you in any way or owes you anything, charge it to my account.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, am writing this with my own hand: I will repay it. (I will not mention to you that you owe me your very life.)
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, I desire this favor from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ!
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Confident of your obedience, I am writing to you because I know that you will do even more than I ask.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	Meanwhile, prepare a guest room for me, too, for I am hoping through your prayers to be returned to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends you greetings,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	May the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit! Amen.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	God, having spoken in former times in fragmentary and varied fashion to our forefathers by the prophets,
B058C001V002	58	1	2	has in these last days spoken to us by a Son whom he appointed to be the heir of everything and through whom he also made the universe.
B058C001V003	58	1	3	He is the reflection of God's glory and the exact likeness of his being, and he holds everything together by his powerful word. After he had provided a cleansing from sins, he sat down at the right hand of the Highest Majesty
B058C001V004	58	1	4	and became as much superior to the angels as the name he has inherited is better than theirs.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels did God ever say, “You are my Son. Today I have become your Father”? Or again, “I will be his Father, and he will be my Son”?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	And again, when he brings his firstborn into the world, he says, “Let all God's angels worship him.”
B058C001V007	58	1	7	Now about the angels he says, 	“He makes his angels winds,and his servants flames of fire.”
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But about the Son he says,	“Your throne, O God,is forever and ever,	and the scepter of your kingdomis a righteous scepter.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	You have loved righteousnessand hated wickedness.	That is why God, your God,anointed you rather than your companionswith the oil of gladness.”
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And,	“In the beginning, Lord,you laid the foundation of the earth,and the heavens are the work of your hands.
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They will come to an end,but you will remain forever.They will all wear out like clothes.
B058C001V012	58	1	12	You will roll them up like a robe,and they will be changed like clothes.	But you remain the same,and your years will never end.”
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But to which of the angels did he ever say,	“Sit at my right handuntil I make your enemies a footstool for your feet”?
B058C001V014	58	1	14	All of them are spirits on a divine mission, sent to serve those who are about to inherit salvation, aren't they?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	For this reason we must pay closer attention to the things we have heard, or we may drift away.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the message spoken by angels was reliable, and every violation and act of disobedience received its just punishment,
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how will we escape if we neglect a salvation as great as this? It was first proclaimed by the Lord himself, and then it was confirmed to us by those who heard him,
B058C002V004	58	2	4	while God added his testimony through signs, wonders, various miracles, and gifts of the Holy Spirit distributed according to his will.
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For he did not put the coming world we are talking about under the control of angels.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	Instead, someone has declared somewhere,	“What is man that you should remember him,or the son of man that you should care for him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	You made him a little lower than the angels,yet you crowned him with glory and honor
B058C002V008	58	2	8	and put everything under his feet.”Now when God put everything under him, he left nothing outside his control. However, at the present time we do not yet see everything put under him.
B058C002V009	58	2	9	But we do see someone who was made a little lower than the angels. He is Jesus, who is crowned with glory and honor because he suffered death, so that by the grace of God he might experience death for everyone.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	In bringing many children to glory, it was fitting that God, for whom and through whom everything exists, should make the pioneer of their salvation perfect through suffering.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For both the one who sanctifies and those who are being sanctified all have the same Father. That is why Jesus is not ashamed to call them brothers
B058C002V012	58	2	12	when he says, “I will announce your name to my brothers. I will praise you within the congregation.”
B058C002V013	58	2	13	And again, “I will trust him.” And again, “I am here with the children God has given me.”
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Therefore, since the children have flesh and blood, he himself also shared the same things, so that by his death he might destroy the one who has the power of death (that is, the devil)
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and might free those who were slaves all their lives because they were terrified by death.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For it is clear that he did not come to help angels. No, he came to help Abraham's descendants.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Thus he had to become like his brothers in every way, so that he could be a merciful and faithful high priest in service to God and could atone for the people's sins.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	Because he himself suffered when he was tempted, he is able to help those who are being tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Therefore, holy brothers, partners in a heavenly calling, keep your focus on Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession.
B058C003V002	58	3	2	He was faithful to the one who appointed him, just as Moses was in all God's household.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For he is worthy of greater glory than Moses in the same way that the builder of a house has greater honor than the house itself.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	After all, every house is built by someone, but God is the builder of everything.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	Moses was faithful in all God's household as a servant who was to testify to what would be said later,
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but Christ was faithful as the Son in charge of God's household, and we are his household if we hold on to our courage and the hope that we boast about.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says,	“Today, if you hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	do not harden your heartsas they did when they provoked meduring the time of testing in the wilderness.
B058C003V009	58	3	9	There your ancestors tested me,even though they had seen my works
B058C003V010	58	3	10	for forty years.	That is why I was indignant with that generation and said,‘They are always going astray in their hearts,and they have not known my ways.’
B058C003V011	58	3	11	So in my anger I swore a solemn oaththat they would never enter my rest.”
B058C003V012	58	3	12	See to it, my brothers, that no evil, unbelieving heart is found in any of you, as shown by your turning away from the living God.
B058C003V013	58	3	13	Instead, continue to encourage one another every day, as long as it is called “Today,” so that none of you may be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we are Christ's partners only if we hold on to our original confidence to the end.
B058C003V015	58	3	15	As it is said,	“Today, if you hear his voice,do not harden your hearts as they didwhen they provoked me.”
B058C003V016	58	3	16	Now who heard him and provoked him? Was it not all those who came out of Egypt led by Moses?
B058C003V017	58	3	17	And with whom was he angry for forty years? Was it not with those who sinned and whose bodies fell in the wilderness?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	And to whom did he swear that they would never enter his rest, if not to those who disobeyed him?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	So we see that they were unable to enter because of their unbelief.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Therefore, as long as the promise of entering his rest remains valid, let us be afraid lest someone among you fails to reach it.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For we have had the good news told to us as well as to them, but the message they heard did not help them, because they were not united by faith with those who listened to it.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have believed are entering that rest, just as he has said,	“So in my anger I swore a solemn oaththat they would never enter my rest,”even though his works had been finished since the foundation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For somewhere he has spoken about the seventh day as follows: “On the seventh day God rested from all his works,”
B058C004V005	58	4	5	and again in this place, “They will never enter my rest.”
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Therefore, since it is still true that some will enter it, and since those who once heard the good news failed to enter it because of their disobedience,
B058C004V007	58	4	7	he again fixes a definite day—“Today”—saying long afterward through David, as already quoted,	“Today, if you hear his voice,do not harden your hearts.”
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had given them rest, he would not have spoken later about another day.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	There remains, therefore, a Sabbath rest for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For the one who enters God's rest has himself rested from his own works, just as God did from his.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Let us, therefore, make every effort to enter that rest, so that no one may fail by following their example of disobedience.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is living and active, sharper than any double-edged sword, piercing until it divides soul and spirit, joints and marrow, as it judges the thoughts and purposes of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	No creature can hide from him, but all are naked and helpless before the eyes of the one to whom we must give a word of explanation.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Therefore, since we have a great high priest who has gone through the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us continue to hold on to our confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we do not have a high priest who is unable to sympathize with our weaknesses, but one who in every respect has been tempted as we are, yet without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	So let us keep on coming with boldness to the throne of grace, so that we may obtain mercy and find grace to help us in our time of need.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest selected from among men is appointed to officiate on their behalf in matters relating to God, that is, to offer gifts and sacrifices for sins.
B058C005V002	58	5	2	He can deal gently with people who are ignorant and easily deceived, since he himself is subject to weakness.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	For that reason he is obligated to offer sacrifices for his own sins as well as for those of the people.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	No one takes this honor upon himself but he is called to it by God, just as Aaron was.
B058C005V005	58	5	5	In the same way, Christ did not take upon himself the glory of being a high priest. No, it was God who said to him,	“You are my Son.Today I have become your Father.”
B058C005V006	58	5	6	As he also says in another place,	“You are a priest foreveraccording to the order of Melchizedek.”
B058C005V007	58	5	7	In the days of his flesh, he offered up prayers and appeals with loud cries and tears to the one who was able to save him from death, and he was heard because of his devotion to God.
B058C005V008	58	5	8	Son though he was, he learned obedience through his sufferings
B058C005V009	58	5	9	and, once made perfect, he became the source of eternal salvation for all who obey him,
B058C005V010	58	5	10	having been designated by God to be a high priest according to the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	We have much to say about this, but it is difficult to explain because you have become too lazy to understand.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	In fact, though by now you should be teachers, you still need someone to teach you the basic truths of God's word. You have become people who need milk instead of solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For everyone who lives on milk is still a baby and is inexperienced in the message of righteousness.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food is for mature people, whose minds are trained by practice to distinguish good from evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore, leaving behind the elementary teachings about Christ, let us continue to be carried along to maturity, not laying again a foundation of repentance from dead works, faith toward God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	instruction about baptisms, the laying on of hands, the resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	And this we will do, if God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For it is impossible to keep on restoring to repentance time and again people who have once been enlightened, who have tasted the heavenly gift, who have become sharers of the Holy Spirit,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	who have tasted the goodness of God's word and the powers of the coming age,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	and who have fallen away, as long as they continue to crucify to themselves the Son of God and to expose him to public ridicule.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For when the ground soaks up rain that often falls on it and continues producing vegetation useful to those for whom it is cultivated, it receives a blessing from God.
B058C006V008	58	6	8	However, if it continues to produce thorns and thistles, it is worthless and in danger of being cursed, and in the end will be burned.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	Even though we speak like this, dear friends, we are convinced of better things in your case, things that point to salvation.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not so unjust as to forget your work and the love you have shown him as you have ministered to the saints and continue to minister to them.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	But we want each of you to continue to show this same diligence to the very end, in order to give full assurance to your hope.
B058C006V012	58	6	12	Then, instead of being lazy, you will become imitators of those who are inheriting the promises through faith and patience.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when God made his promise to Abraham, he swore an oath by himself, since he had no one greater to swear by.
B058C006V014	58	6	14	He said, “I will certainly bless you and give you many descendants.”
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so he obtained the promise, because he patiently waited for it.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For people swear by someone greater than themselves, and an oath given as confirmation puts an end to all argument.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	In the same way, when God wanted to make the unchangeable character of his purpose perfectly clear to the heirs of his promise, he guaranteed it with an oath,
B058C006V018	58	6	18	so that by these two unchangeable things, in which it is impossible for God to prove false, we who have taken refuge in him might have a strong encouragement to seize the hope set before us.
B058C006V019	58	6	19	We have this hope as an anchor for our souls, firm and secure, which reaches behind the curtain,
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where Jesus, our forerunner, has gone on our behalf, having become a high priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	Now this man Melchizedek, king of Salem and priest of the Most High God, met Abraham and blessed him when he was returning from slaughtering the kings.
B058C007V002	58	7	2	To him Abraham gave a tenth of everything. In the first place, his name means “king of righteousness,” and then he is also king of Salem, that is, “king of peace.”
B058C007V003	58	7	3	He has no father, mother, or genealogy, and has neither beginning of days nor end of life. Like the Son of God, he continues to be a priest forever.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	Just look at how great this man was! Even Abraham—the patriarch himself—gave him a tenth of what he had captured!
B058C007V005	58	7	5	The descendants of Levi who accept the priesthood have a commandment in the law to collect a tenth from the people, that is, from their own brothers, even though they are also descendants of Abraham.
B058C007V006	58	7	6	But this man, whose descent is not traced from them, collected a tenth from Abraham and blessed the man who had received the promises.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	It is beyond dispute that the less important person is blessed by the more important person.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	The men who collect the tenth die, but we are told that he keeps on living.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	One might even say that Levi, who collects the tenth, paid the tenth through Abraham,
B058C007V010	58	7	10	for he was still in the body of his ancestor when Melchizedek met him.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	Now if perfection could have been attained through the Levitical priesthood—for on this basis the people received the law—what further need would there be to speak of appointing another kind of priest according to the order of Melchizedek, not one according to the order of Aaron?
B058C007V012	58	7	12	For when a change in the priesthood takes place, there must also be a change in the law.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For the person we are talking about belonged to a different tribe, and no one from that tribe has ever served at the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is obvious that our Lord was a descendant of Judah, and Moses said nothing about priests coming from that tribe.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	This point is even more obvious in that another priest who is like Melchizedek has appeared
B058C007V016	58	7	16	who was appointed to be a priest, not on the basis of a regulation concerning his ancestry, but rather on the basis of the power of an indestructible life.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For it is declared about him,	“You are a priest foreveraccording to the order of Melchizedek.”
B058C007V018	58	7	18	Indeed, the cancellation of the former regulation has occurred because it was weak and ineffective
B058C007V019	58	7	19	(for the law made nothing perfect), and a better hope is introduced, by which we approach God.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	Now none of this happened without an oath. Others became priests without any oath,
B058C007V021	58	7	21	but Jesus became a priest with an oath when God said to him,	“The Lord has taken an oathand will not change his mind.	You are a priest forever.”
B058C007V022	58	7	22	In this way, Jesus has become the guarantor of a better covenant.
B058C007V023	58	7	23	There have been many priests, since they have been prevented by death from continuing in office.
B058C007V024	58	7	24	But because Jesus lives forever, he has a permanent priesthood.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	Therefore, because he always lives to intercede for them, he is able to save completely those who come to God through him.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	We need such a high priest—one who is holy, innocent, pure, set apart from sinners, exalted above the heavens.
B058C007V027	58	7	27	He has no need to offer sacrifices every day like those high priests, first for his own sins and then for those of the people, since he did this once for all when he sacrificed himself.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the law appoints as high priests men who are weak, but the word of the oath, which came after the law, appoints a Son who has been made perfect forever.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	Now the main point in what we are saying is this: we do have this kind of high priest, who sat down at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven
B058C008V002	58	8	2	and who serves in the sanctuary, the true tabernacle set up by the Lord and not by any human.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	For every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices. Therefore, this high priest had to offer something too.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	Now if he were on earth, he would not even be a priest, because other men offer the gifts prescribed by the law.
B058C008V005	58	8	5	They serve in a sanctuary that is a copy and shadow of the heavenly one. This is why Moses was warned when he was about to build the tabernacle: “See to it that you make everything according to the pattern that was shown you on the mountain.”
B058C008V006	58	8	6	However, Jesus has now obtained a ministry that is as superior to theirs as the covenant he mediates is founded on better promises.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if the first covenant had been faultless, there would have been no need to look for a second one.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	But God found something wrong with his people when he said,	“Look! The days are coming, declares the Lord, when I will establish a new covenantwith the house of Israeland with the house of Judah.
B058C008V009	58	8	9	It will not be like the covenant that I made with their ancestors at the timewhen I took them by the handand brought them out of the land of Egypt. 	Because they did not remain loyal to my covenant,I ignored them, declares the Lord.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israelafter those days, declares the Lord:	I will put my laws in their mindsand write them on their hearts.	I will be their God,and they will be my people.
B058C008V011	58	8	11	Never again will everyone teach his neighbor or his brother by saying, ‘Know the Lord,’	because all of them will know me,from the least important to the most important.
B058C008V012	58	8	12	For I will be merciful regarding their wrong deeds,and I will never again remember their sins.”
B058C008V013	58	8	13	In speaking of a “new” covenant, he has made the first one obsolete, and what is obsolete and aging will soon disappear.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	Now even first covenant had regulations for worship and an earthly sanctuary.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For a tabernacle was set up, and in the first part were the lampstand, the table, and the bread of the Presence. This was called the Holy Place.
B058C009V003	58	9	3	Behind the second curtain was the part of the tabernacle called the Holy of Holies,
B058C009V004	58	9	4	which had the gold altar for incense and the ark of the covenant completely covered with gold. In it were the gold jar holding the manna, Aaron's staff that had budded, and the tablets of the covenant.
B058C009V005	58	9	5	Above it were the cherubim of glory overshadowing the place of atonement. (We cannot discuss these things in detail now.)
B058C009V006	58	9	6	When everything had been arranged like this, the priests always went into the first part of the tabernacle to perform their duties.
B058C009V007	58	9	7	But only the high priest went into the second part, and then only once a year, and never without blood, which he offered for himself and for the sins committed by the people in ignorance.
B058C009V008	58	9	8	The Holy Spirit was indicating by this that the way into the Holy of Holies had not yet been disclosed as long as the first part of the tabernacle was still standing.
B058C009V009	58	9	9	This is an illustration of the present time, indicating that the gifts and sacrifices being offered could not make the conscience of the worshiper perfect,
B058C009V010	58	9	10	since they deal only with food, drink, and various washings, which are required for the body until the time when things would be set right.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But when Christ came as a high priest of the good things that have come, he went through the greater and more perfect tabernacle that was not made by human hands and that is not a part of this creation.
B058C009V012	58	9	12	Not with the blood of goats and calves, but with his own blood he went into the Holy of Holies once for all and secured our eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of goats and bulls and the ashes of a heifer sprinkled on those who are unclean purifies them with physical cleansing,
B058C009V014	58	9	14	how much more will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself unblemished to God, cleanse our consciences from dead works so that we may serve the living God!
B058C009V015	58	9	15	This is why he is the mediator of a new covenant; so that those who are called may receive the eternal inheritance promised them, since a death has occurred that redeems them from the offenses committed under the first covenant.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where there is a will, the death of the one who made it must be established.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For a will is in force only when somebody has died, since it never takes effect as long as the one who made it is alive.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	This is why even the first covenant was not put into effect without blood.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	For after every commandment in the law had been spoken to all the people by Moses, he took the blood of calves and goats, together with some water, scarlet wool, and branches of hyssop, and sprinkled the scroll and all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	saying, “This is the blood of the covenant that God ordained for you.”
B058C009V021	58	9	21	In the same way, he sprinkled with the blood both the tabernacle and everything used in worship.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	In fact, under the law almost everything is cleansed with blood, and without the shedding of the blood there is no forgiveness.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	Thus it was necessary for the copies of the things in heaven to be cleansed by these sacrifices, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For Christ did not go into a sanctuary made by human hands and just a copy of the true one, but into heaven itself, now to appear in God's presence on our behalf.
B058C009V025	58	9	25	Nor did he go into heaven to sacrifice himself again and again, the way the high priest goes into the Holy Place every year with blood that is not his own.
B058C009V026	58	9	26	Then he would have had to suffer repeatedly since the foundation of the world. But now, at the end of the ages, he has appeared once for all to remove sin by his sacrifice.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	Indeed, just as people are appointed to die once and after that to be judged,
B058C009V028	58	9	28	so Christ was sacrificed once to take away the sins of many people. And he will appear a second time, not to deal with sin, but to bring salvation to those who eagerly wait for him.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For the law, being only a reflection of the blessings to come and not their substance, can never, by the same sacrifices repeatedly offered year after year, make those who come near perfect.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	Otherwise, would they not have stopped offering them, because the worshipers, cleansed once for all, would no longer be aware of any sins?
B058C010V003	58	10	3	Instead, through those sacrifices there is a reminder of sins year after year,
B058C010V004	58	10	4	for it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	For this reason, when Christ came into the world, he said,	“You did not want sacrifices and offerings,but you prepared a body for me.
B058C010V006	58	10	6	In burnt offerings and sin offeringsyou never took delight.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then I said, ‘See, I have come to do your will, O God’(in the scroll of the Book this is written about me).”
B058C010V008	58	10	8	In this passage he says, “You never wanted or took delight in sacrifices, offerings, burnt offerings, and sin offerings,” which are offered according to the law.
B058C010V009	58	10	9	Then he says, “See, I have come to do your will.” He takes away the first in order to establish the second.
B058C010V010	58	10	10	By his will we have been sanctified once for all through the sacrifice of the body of Jesus Christ.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	Day after day every priest stands and repeatedly offers the same sacrifices that can never take away sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But when this priest had offered for all time one sacrifice for sins, “he sat down at the right hand of God.”
B058C010V013	58	10	13	Since that time, he has been waiting for his enemies to be made a footstool for his feet.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by a single offering he has perfected for all time those who are being sanctified.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	The Holy Spirit also assures us of this. For he said,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	“This is the covenant that I will make with themafter those days, declares the Lord:	I will put my laws in their heartsand will write them on their minds,”
B058C010V017	58	10	17	and,	“I will never again remember their sinsand their lawless deeds.”
B058C010V018	58	10	18	Now where there is forgiveness of these sins, there is no longer any offering for sin.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Therefore, my brothers, since we have confidence to enter the sanctuary by the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain (that is, through his flesh),
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and since we have a great high priest over the household of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	let us continue to come near with sincere hearts in full assurance of faith, because our hearts have been sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies have been washed with pure water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us continue to hold firmly to the hope that we confess without wavering, for the one who made the promise is faithful.
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us continue to consider how to stimulate one another to love and good deeds,
B058C010V025	58	10	25	not neglecting to meet together, as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another even more as you see the day coming nearer.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we choose to go on sinning after we have received the full knowledge of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice for sins,
B058C010V027	58	10	27	but only a terrifying prospect of judgment and a raging fire that will consume the enemies of God
B058C010V028	58	10	28	Anyone who violates the law of Moses dies without mercy “on the testimony of two or three witnesses.”
B058C010V029	58	10	29	How much more severe a punishment do you think that person deserves who tramples on God's Son, treats as common the blood of the covenant by which it was sanctified, and insults the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know the one who said, “Vengeance belongs to me; I will pay them back,” and again, “The Lord will judge his people.”
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God!
B058C010V032	58	10	32	But you must continue to remember those earlier days, how after you were enlightened you endured a hard and painful struggle.
B058C010V033	58	10	33	At times you were made a public spectacle through insults and persecutions, while at other times you associated with people who were treated this way.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you sympathized with the prisoners and cheerfully submitted to the violent seizure of your property, because you know that you have a better and more permanent possession.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	So do not throw away your confidence, since it holds a great reward for you.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	For you need endurance, so that after you have done God's will you can receive what he has promised.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	For	“in a very little whilethe one who is coming will returnand will not delay;
B058C010V038	58	10	38	but my righteous one will live by faith,and if he turns back,my soul will take no pleasure in him.”
B058C010V039	58	10	39	Now, we do not belong to those who turn back and are destroyed, but to those who have faith and are saved.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is the assurance of things we hope for, the certainty of things we cannot see.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by it our ancestors won approval.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	By faith we understand that the universe was prepared by the word of God, so that what is seen was made from things that are invisible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered to God a better sacrifice than Cain did, and by it he was declared to be righteous, since God himself accepted his offerings. And by faith he continues to speak, even though he is dead.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was taken away without experiencing death. He could not be found, because God had taken him away. For before he was taken, he won approval as one who pleased God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	Now without faith it is impossible to please God, for the one who comes to him must believe that he exists and that he rewards those who diligently search for him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, when warned about things not yet seen, reverently prepared an ark to save his family, and by it he condemned the world and became an heir of the righteousness that comes by faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham, when called to go to a place he would later receive as his inheritance, obeyed and went, even though he did not know where he was going.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he made his home in the promised land like a stranger, living in tents with Isaac and Jacob, who were heirs with him of the same promise.
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he was waiting for the city with permanent foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith Sarah, even though she was old and barren, received the strength to conceive, because she was convinced that the one who had made the promise was faithful.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Abraham was as good as dead, yet from this one man came descendants as numerous as the stars in the sky and as countless as the sand on the seashore.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	All these people died having faith. They did not receive the things that were promised, yet they saw them in the distant future and welcomed them, acknowledging that they were strangers and foreigners on earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For people who say such things make it clear that they are looking for a country of their own.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	If they had been thinking about what they had left behind, they would have had an opportunity to go back.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	Instead, they were longing for a better country, that is, a heavenly one. That is why God is not ashamed to be called their God, because he has prepared a city for them.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered Isaac. The man who had received the promises was about to offer his unique son,
B058C011V018	58	11	18	about whom it had been said, “It is through Isaac that descendants will be named for you.”
B058C011V019	58	11	19	He was certain that God could raise people from the dead, and figuratively speaking he did get him back in this way.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau in regard to their future.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob, when he was dying, blessed each of Joseph's sons “and worshiped while leaning on the top of his staff.”
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, when his end was near, spoke about the exodus of the Israelites and gave them instructions about burying his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses was hidden by his parents for three months after he was born, because they saw that he was a beautiful child and were not afraid of the king's order.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses, when he had grown up, refused to be called a son of Pharaoh's daughter,
B058C011V025	58	11	25	because he preferred being mistreated with God's people to enjoying the pleasures of sin for a short time.
B058C011V026	58	11	26	He thought that being insulted for the sake of Christ was of greater value than the treasures of Egypt, because he was looking ahead to his reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he left Egypt, without being afraid of the king's anger, and he persevered because he saw the one who is invisible.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith he established the Passover and the sprinkling of blood to keep the destroyer of the firstborn from touching the people.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they went through the Red Sea as if it were dry land. When the Egyptians tried to do this, they were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been encircled for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith Rahab the prostitute did not die with those who were disobedient, because she had welcomed the spies with a greeting of peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what more should I say? For time would fail me to tell you about Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, Samuel, and the prophets.
B058C011V033	58	11	33	Through faith they conquered kingdoms, administered justice, received promises, shut the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	put out raging fires, escaped death by the sword, found strength in weakness, became powerful in battle, and routed foreign armies.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received back their dead through a resurrection. Others were brutally tortured but refused to accept release, so that they might gain a better resurrection.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	Still others endured taunts and floggings, and even chains and imprisonment.
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned to death, sawed in half, and killed with swords. They went around in sheepskins and goatskins. They were needy, oppressed, and mistreated.
B058C011V038	58	11	38	The world wasn’t worthy of them. They wandered in deserts, mountains, caves, and holes in the ground.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	All these people won approval for their faith but did not receive what was promised,
B058C011V040	58	11	40	since God had planned something better for us so that they would not become perfect without us.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore, having so vast a cloud of witnesses surrounding us, and throwing off everything that hinders us and especially the sin that so easily entangles us, let us keep running with endurance the race set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	looking off to Jesus, the pioneer and perfecter of the faith, who, in view of the joy set before him endured the cross, despising its shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	Think about the one who endured such hostility from sinners, so that you may not become tired and give up.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	In your struggle against sin you have not yet resisted to the point of shedding your blood.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	You have forgotten the encouragement that is addressed to you as sons:	“My son, do not think lightly of the Lord's disciplineor give up when you are corrected by him.
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For the Lord disciplines the one he loves,and he punishes every son he accepts.”
B058C012V007	58	12	7	What you endure is for the sake of discipline. God is treating you as sons. Is there a son whom his father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	Now if you are without any discipline, in which all sons share, then you are illegitimate and not his sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore, we had earthly fathers who used to discipline us, and we respected them for it. We should even more submit to the Father of our spirits and live, shouldn't we?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For a short time they disciplined us as they thought best, but he does it for our good, so that we may share in his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	No discipline seems pleasant at the time, but painful. Later on, however, for those who have been trained by it, it produces a harvest of righteousness and peace.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore, strengthen your tired arms and your weak knees,
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that what is lame may not become worse but rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Pursue peace with everyone, as well as holiness, without which no one will see the Lord.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	See to it that no one fails to obtain the grace of God and that no bitter root grows up and causes you trouble, or many of you will become defiled.
B058C012V016	58	12	16	No one should be immoral or godless like Esau, who sold his birthright for a single meal.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that afterwards, when he wanted to inherit the blessing, he was rejected because he could not find any opportunity to repent, even though he begged for it with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to something that can be touched, to a blazing fire, to darkness, to gloom,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	to a trumpet's blast, or to a voice that made the hearers beg that not another word be spoken to them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not endure the command that was given: “If even an animal touches the mountain, it must be stoned to death.”
B058C012V021	58	12	21	Indeed, the sight was so terrifying that Moses said, “I am trembling with fear.”
B058C012V022	58	12	22	Instead, you have come to Mount Zion, to the city of the living God, to the heavenly Jerusalem, to tens of thousands of angels joyfully gathered together,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	to the assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, to a judge who is the God of all, to the spirits of righteous people who have been made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and to the sprinkled blood that speaks a better message than Abel's.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	See to it that you do not ignore the one who is speaking. For if they did not escape when they ignored the one who warned them on earth, how much less will we escape if we turn away from the one who is from heaven!
B058C012V026	58	12	26	At that time his voice shook the earth, but now he has promised, “Once more I will shake not only the earth but also heaven.”
B058C012V027	58	12	27	The expression “once more” signifies the removal of what can be shaken, that is, what he has made, so that what cannot be shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore, since we are receiving a kingdom that cannot be shaken, let us be thankful and worship God in reverence and fear in a way that pleases him.
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is an all-consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Stop neglecting to show hospitality to strangers, for by showing hospitality some have had angels as their guests without being aware of it.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Continue to remember those in prison as if you were in prison with them, as well as those who are mistreated, since they also are only mortal.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Let marriage be kept honorable in every way, and the marriage bed undefiled. For God will judge those who commit sexual sins, especially those who commit adultery.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Keep your lives free from the love of money, and be content with what you have, for God has said, “I will never leave you or abandon you.”
B058C013V006	58	13	6	Hence we can confidently say, “The Lord is my helper; I will not be afraid. What can anyone do to me?”
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders, those who have spoken God's word to you. Think about the impact of their lives, and imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today—and forever!
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Stop being carried away by all kinds of unusual teachings, for it is good that the heart be strengthened by grace, not by food laws that have never helped those who follow them.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar, and those who serve in the tabernacle have no right to eat at it.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of animals, whose blood is taken into the sanctuary by the high priest as an offering for sin, are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	That is why Jesus, in order to sanctify the people by his own blood, also suffered outside the city gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Therefore go to him outside the camp and endure the insults he endured.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For here we have no permanent city but are looking for the one that is coming.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Therefore, through him let us always bring God a sacrifice of praise, that is, the fruit of lips that confess his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	Do not neglect to do good and to be generous, for God is pleased with such sacrifices.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Continue to obey your leaders and to be submissive to them, for they watch over your souls as men who will have to give a word of explanation. Let them do this with joy and not with grief, for that would be harmful to you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us, for we are sure that we have a clear conscience and desire to live honorably in every way.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	I especially ask you to do this so that I may be brought back to you sooner.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may the God of peace, who by the blood of the eternal covenant brought back from the dead our Lord Jesus, the Great Shepherd of the sheep,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	equip you with everything good to do his will, accomplishing in us what pleases him through Jesus Christ. To him be glory forever and ever! Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	I urge you, brothers, to listen patiently to my encouraging message, for I have written you a short letter.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	You should know that our brother Timothy has been set free. If he comes soon, he will be with me when I see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all your leaders and all the saints. Those who are from Italy greet you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	May grace be with all of you!
B059C001V001	59	1	1	From James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes in the Dispersion. Greetings.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Consider it pure joy, my brothers, when you are involved in various trials,
B059C001V003	59	1	3	because you know that the testing of your faith produces endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	But you must let endurance have its full effect, so that you may be mature and complete, lacking nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	Now if any of you lacks wisdom, he should ask God, who gives to everyone generously without a rebuke, and it will be given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But he must ask in faith, without any doubts, for the one who has doubts is like a wave of the sea that is driven and tossed by the wind.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	Such a person should not expect to receive anything from the Lord.
B059C001V008	59	1	8	He is a double-minded man, unstable in all he undertakes.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	A brother of low status should boast in his exalted status,
B059C001V010	59	1	10	and a rich person in his lowliness, because he will fade away like a flower in the grass.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun comes up with its scorching heat and dries up the grass. The flower in it drops off, and its beauty is gone. That is how the rich person will fade away in his pursuits.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	How blessed is the man who endures temptation! When he has passed the test, he will receive the victor's crown of life that God has promised to those who keep on loving him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	When someone is tempted, he should not say, “I am being tempted by God,” because God cannot be tempted by evil, nor does he tempt anyone.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	Instead, each person is tempted by his own desire, being lured and trapped by it.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	When that desire becomes pregnant, it gives birth to sin; when that sin grows up, it gives birth to death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my dear brothers.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every generous act of giving and every perfect gift is from above and comes down from the Father who made the heavenly lights, in whom there is no inconsistency or shifting shadow.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	In accordance with his will he made us his children by the word of truth, so that we might become the most important of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	You must understand this, my dear brothers. Everyone should be quick to listen, slow to speak, and slow to get angry.
B059C001V020	59	1	20	For human anger does not produce God's righteousness.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore, rid yourselves of everything impure and every expression of wickedness, and with a gentle spirit welcome the word planted in you that can save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	Keep on being doers of the word, and not merely hearers who deceive themselves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, he is like a man who looks at himself in a mirror.
B059C001V024	59	1	24	For he studies himself carefully and then goes off and immediately forgets what he looks like.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But the one who looks at the perfect law of freedom and remains committed to it—thus proving that he is not a forgetful hearer but a doer of what it requires—will be blessed in what he does.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If anyone thinks that he is religious and does not bridle his tongue, but instead deceives his own heart, his religion is worthless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	A religion that is pure and stainless in the sight of God the Father is this: to take care of orphans and widows in their suffering, and to keep oneself unstained by the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brothers, do not practice your faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ by showing partiality.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	Suppose a man wearing gold rings and fine clothes comes into your assembly, and a poor man in dirty clothes also comes in.
B059C002V003	59	2	3	If you give special attention to the man wearing fine clothes and say, “Please take this seat,” but you say to the poor man, “Stand over there” or “Sit on the floor at my feet,”
B059C002V004	59	2	4	you have made false distinctions among yourselves and have become judges with evil motives, haven't you?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my dear brothers! God has chosen the poor in the world to become rich in faith and to be heirs of the kingdom that he promised to those who love him, has he not?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have humiliated the man who is poor. Are not rich people the ones who oppress you and drag you into court?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Are not they the ones who blaspheme the excellent name by which you have been called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	Nevertheless, you are doing the right thing if you obey the royal law in keeping with the Scripture, “You must love your neighbor as yourself.”
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you show partiality, you are committing sin and will be convicted by the law as violators.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whoever keeps the whole law but fails in one point is guilty of breaking all of it.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For the one who said, “Never commit adultery,” also said, “Never murder.” Now if you do not commit adultery but you murder, you become a violator of the law.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	You must make it your habit to speak and act like people who are going to be judged by the law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For merciless judgment will come to the one who has shown no mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What good does it do, my brothers, if someone claims to have faith but does not have any works? This kind of faith cannot save him, can it?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	Suppose a brother or sister does not have any clothes or daily food
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you tells them, “Go in peace! Stay warm and eat heartily.” If you do not provide for their bodily needs, what good does it do?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	In the same way, faith by itself, if it does not have any works, is dead.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	But someone may say, “You have faith, and I have works.” Show me your faith without any works, and I will show you my faith by my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that there is one God. That's fine! Even the demons believe that and tremble with fear.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	Do you want proof, you foolish person, that faith without works is worthless?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Our ancestor Abraham was justified by works when he offered his son Isaac on the altar, wasn't he?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You see that his faith was active with his works, and by his works faith was made complete.
B059C002V023	59	2	23	And so the Scripture was fulfilled that says, “Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.” And so he was called God's friend.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	Likewise, Rahab the prostitute was justified by works when she welcomed the messengers and sent them away on a different road, wasn't she?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For just as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is also dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	Not many of you should become teachers, my brothers, because you know that we who teach will be judged more severely.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For all of us make many mistakes. If someone does not make any mistakes when he speaks, he is perfect and able to control his whole body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	Now if we put bits into horses’ mouths to make them obey us, we can guide their whole bodies as well.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	And look at ships! They are so big that it takes strong winds to drive them, yet they are steered wherever the pilot pleases by a tiny rudder.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	In the same way, the tongue is a small part of the body, yet it can boast of great achievements. A huge forest can be set on fire by a little flame.
B059C003V006	59	3	6	The tongue is a fire, a world of evil. Placed among the parts of our bodies, the tongue contaminates the whole body and sets on fire the course of life, and is itself set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For all kinds of animals, birds, reptiles, and sea creatures can be or have been tamed by the human species,
B059C003V008	59	3	8	but no one can tame the tongue. It is an uncontrollable evil filled with deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless the Lord and Father, and with it we curse those who are made in God's likeness.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	From the same mouth come blessing and cursing. It should not be like this, my brothers!
B059C003V011	59	3	11	A spring cannot pour both fresh and brackish water from the same opening, can it?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	My brothers, a fig tree cannot produce olives, nor a grapevine figs, can it? Neither can a salt spring produce fresh water.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who among you is wise and understanding? Let him show by his good life that his works are done in humility born of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter jealousy and rivalry in your hearts, stop boasting and lying against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	That kind of wisdom does not come from above. No, it is worldly, self-centered, and demonic.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For wherever jealousy and rivalry exist, there is disorder and every kind of evil.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	However, the wisdom that comes from above is first of all pure, then peace-loving, gentle, willing to yield, full of compassion and good fruits, and without a trace of partiality or hypocrisy.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	And a harvest of righteousness is grown from the seed of peace planted by peacemakers.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	Where do those fights and quarrels among you come from? They come from your selfish desires that are at war in your bodies, don't they?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You want something but do not get it, so you commit murder. You covet something but cannot obtain it, so you quarrel and fight. You do not get things because you do not ask for them!
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask for something but do not get it because you ask for it for the wrong reason—for your own pleasure.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You adulterers! Don't you know that friendship with the world means hostility with God? So whoever wants to be a friend of this world is an enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you think the Scripture means nothing when it says that the Spirit that God caused to live in us jealously yearns for us?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But he gives all the more grace. And so he says,	“God opposes the arrogantbut gives grace to the humble.”
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Therefore, submit yourselves to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Come close to God, and he will come close to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Be miserable, mourn, and cry. Let your laughter be turned into mourning, and your joy into gloom.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not criticize each other, brothers. Whoever makes it his habit to criticize his brother or to judge his brother is judging the law and condemning the law. But if you condemn the law, you are not a doer of the law but its judge.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	There is only one Lawgiver and Judge—the one who can save and destroy. So who are you to judge your neighbor?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Now listen, you who say, “Today or tomorrow we will go to such and such a town, stay there a year, conduct business, and make money.”
B059C004V014	59	4	14	You do not know what tomorrow will bring. What is your life? You are a mist that appears for a little while and then vanishes.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	Instead you should say, “If the Lord wants us to, we will live—and do this or that.”
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But you boast about your proud intentions. All such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	Therefore, anyone who knows what is right but fails to do it is guilty of sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Now listen, you rich people! Cry and moan over the miseries that are overtaking you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches are rotten, your clothes have been eaten by moths,
B059C005V003	59	5	3	your gold and silver are corroded, and their corrosion will be used as evidence against you and will eat your flesh like fire. You have stored up treasures in these last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Look! The wages that you kept back from the workers who harvested your fields are shouting out against you, and the cries of the reapers have reached the ears of the Lord of the Heavenly Armies.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived in luxury and pleasure on earth. You have fattened your hearts for the day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned and murdered the one who is righteous, even though he did not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	So be patient, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. See how the farmer waits for the precious crop from his land, being patient with it until it receives the fall and the spring rains.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You, too, must be patient. Strengthen your hearts, because the coming of the Lord is near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not complain about each other, brothers, or you will be condemned. Look! The Judge is standing at the door!
B059C005V010	59	5	10	As an example of suffering and patience, brothers, take the prophets, who spoke in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	We consider those who endured to be blessed. You have heard about Job's endurance and have seen the purpose of the Lord—that the Lord is compassionate and merciful.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	Above all, brothers, do not swear oaths by heaven, by earth, or by any other object. Instead, let your “Yes” mean yes and your “No” mean no, lest you fall under condemnation.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is anyone of you suffering? He should keep on praying. Is anyone cheerful? He should keep on singing psalms.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is anyone of you sick? He should call for the elders of the church, and they should pray for him and anoint him with oil in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer offered in faith will save the person who is sick. The Lord will raise him up, and if he has committed any sins, he will be forgiven.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Therefore, make it your habit to confess your sins to one another and to pray for one another, so that you may be healed. The prayer of a righteous person is powerful and effective.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man just like us, and he prayed earnestly for it not to rain, and it did not rain on the ground for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	Then he prayed again, and heaven sent rain, and the ground produced its crops.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	My brothers, if one of you wanders away from the truth and somebody brings him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	you may be sure that whoever brings a sinner back from his wrong path will save his soul from death and cover a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	From Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the exiles of the Dispersion in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	the people chosen according to the foreknowledge of God the Father through the sanctifying work of the Spirit to be obedient to Jesus Christ and to be sprinkled with his blood. May grace and peace be yours in abundance!
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ! Because of his great mercy he has given us a new birth to an ever-living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead
B060C001V004	60	1	4	and to an inheritance kept in heaven for you that can't be destroyed, corrupted, or changed.
B060C001V005	60	1	5	Through faith you are being protected by God's power for a salvation that is ready to be revealed at the end of time.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	In this you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while you have to suffer various kinds of trials,
B060C001V007	60	1	7	so that the genuineness of your faith, which is more valuable than gold that perishes when it is tested by fire, may result in praise, glory, and honor when Jesus Christ is revealed.
B060C001V008	60	1	8	Though you have not seen him, you love him. And even though you do not see him now, you believe in him and rejoice with an indescribable and glorious joy,
B060C001V009	60	1	9	because you are receiving the goal of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Even the prophets, who prophesied about the grace that was to be yours, carefully researched and investigated this salvation.
B060C001V011	60	1	11	They tried to find out what era or specific time the Spirit of Christ in them kept referring to when he predicted the sufferings of Christ and the glories that would follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	It was revealed to them that they were not serving themselves but you in regard to the things that have now been announced to you by those who brought you the good news through the Holy Spirit sent from heaven. These are things that even the angels desire to look into.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore, prepare your minds for action, keep a clear head, and set your hope completely on the grace to be given you when Jesus Christ is revealed.
B060C001V014	60	1	14	As obedient children, do not be shaped by the desires that you once had in your ignorance.
B060C001V015	60	1	15	Instead, just as the one who called you is holy, be holy in every aspect of your life.
B060C001V016	60	1	16	For it is written, “You must be holy, because I am holy.”
B060C001V017	60	1	17	If you call “Father” the one who judges everyone impartially according to what he has done, you must live in the fear of the Lord as long as you are strangers here.
B060C001V018	60	1	18	For you know that it was not with perishable things like silver or gold that you have been ransomed from the worthless way of life handed down to you by your ancestors,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with the precious blood of Christ, like that of a lamb without blemish or defect.
B060C001V020	60	1	20	On the one hand, he was foreknown before the foundation of the world, but on the other hand, he was revealed at the end of time for your sake.
B060C001V021	60	1	21	Through him you believe in God, who raised him from the dead and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope might be in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Now that you have obeyed the truth and have purified your souls to love your brothers sincerely, you must love one another intensely and with a pure heart.
B060C001V023	60	1	23	For you have been born again, not by a seed that perishes but by one that cannot perish—by the living and everlasting word of God.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For	“All human life is like grass,and all its glory is like a flower in the grass.	The grass dries up and the flower drops off,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of the Lord lasts forever.”Now this word is the good news that was announced to you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Therefore, rid yourselves of every kind of evil and deception, hypocrisy, jealousy, and every kind of slander.
B060C002V002	60	2	2	Like newborn babies, thirst for the pure milk of the word so that by it you may grow in your salvation.
B060C002V003	60	2	3	Surely you have tasted that the Lord is good!
B060C002V004	60	2	4	As you come to him, the living stone who was rejected by people but was chosen and precious in God's sight,
B060C002V005	60	2	5	you, too, as living stones, are building yourselves up into a spiritual house and a holy priesthood, so that you may offer spiritual sacrifices that are acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	This is why it says in Scripture:	“Look! I am laying a chosenand precious cornerstone in Zion.			The one who believes in him will never be ashamed.”
B060C002V007	60	2	7	Therefore he is precious to you who believe, but to those who do not believe,	“The stone that the builders rejectedhas become the cornerstone,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	a stone they stumble over and a rock they trip on.”They keep on stumbling because they disobey the word, as they were destined to do.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen people, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people to be his very own and to proclaim the wonderful deeds of the one who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light.
B060C002V010	60	2	10	Once you were not a people,but now you are the people of God.	Once you had not received mercy,but now you have received mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Dear friends, I urge you as aliens and exiles to keep on abstaining from the desires of the flesh that wage war against the soul.
B060C002V012	60	2	12	Continue to live such upright lives among the Gentiles that, when they slander you as evildoers, they may see your good works and glorify God when he visits them in judgment.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	For the Lord's sake submit yourselves to every human authority: whether to the king as supreme,
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to governors who are sent by him to punish those who do wrong and to praise those who do right.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For it is God's will that by doing right you should silence the ignorant talk of foolish people.
B060C002V016	60	2	16	Live like free people, and do not use your freedom as an excuse for doing evil. Instead, be God's servants.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Show honor to everyone. Keep on loving the brothers, fearing God, and honoring the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	You household servants must submit yourselves to your masters with all fear, not only to those who are kind and fair, but also to those who are unjust.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For it is a fine thing if, when moved by your conscience to please God, you suffer patiently when wronged.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	What credit is it if you sin and patiently receive a beating for it? But if you suffer for doing good and take it patiently, you have God's approval.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	This is, in fact, what you were called to do, because Christ also suffered for you and left an example for you to follow in his steps.
B060C002V022	60	2	22	“He never committed a sin, and no deceit was found in his mouth.”
B060C002V023	60	2	23	When he was insulted, he did not retaliate. When he suffered, he did not threaten but made it his habit to commit the matter to the one who judges fairly.
B060C002V024	60	2	24	He himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, so that we might die to those sins and live for righteousness. By his wounds you have been healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were like sheep that kept going astray, but now you have returned to the Shepherd and Overseer of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	In a similar way, you wives must submit yourselves to your husbands so that, even if some of them refuse to obey the word, they may be won over without a word through your conduct as wives
B060C003V002	60	3	2	when they see your pure and reverent lives.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Your beauty should not be an external one, consisting of braided hair or the wearing of gold ornaments and dresses.
B060C003V004	60	3	4	Instead, it should be the inner disposition of the heart, consisting in the imperishable quality of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is of great value in the sight of God.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	After all, this is how holy women who set their hope on God used to make themselves beautiful in the past. They submitted themselves to their husbands,
B060C003V006	60	3	6	just as Sarah obeyed Abraham and called him lord. You have become her daughters by doing good and by not letting anything terrify you.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	In a similar way, you husbands must live with your wives in an understanding manner, as with a most delicate vessel. Honor them as heirs with you of the gracious gift of life, so that nothing may interfere with your prayers.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, all of you must live in harmony, be sympathetic, love as brothers, and be compassionate and humble.
B060C003V009	60	3	9	Do not pay others back evil for evil or insult for insult. Instead, bless them, because you were called to inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For	“the person who wants to love lifeand see good days	must keep his tongue from eviland his lips from speaking deceit.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	He must turn away from evil and do good.He must seek peace and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous,and his ears are attentive to their prayer.	But the face of the Lord is against those who do wrong.”
B060C003V013	60	3	13	Who will harm you if you are devoted to doing what is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you should suffer for doing what is right, you are blessed. Never be afraid of their threats, and never get upset.
B060C003V015	60	3	15	Instead, exalt Christ as Lord in your hearts. Always be prepared to give a defense to everyone who asks you to explain the hope you have.
B060C003V016	60	3	16	But do this with gentleness and respect, keeping a clear conscience, so that those who speak evil of your good conduct in Christ will be ashamed of slandering you.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	After all, if it is the will of God, it is better to suffer for doing right than for doing wrong.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ also suffered for sins once for all, an innocent person for the guilty, so that he could bring you to God. He was put to death in the sphere of the flesh but was made alive in the sphere of the spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	in which he went and made a proclamation to those imprisoned spirits
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who disobeyed long ago in the days of Noah, when God waited patiently while the ark was being built. In it a few, that is, eight persons, were saved by water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	Baptism, which is symbolized by that water, now saves you also, not by removing dirt from the body, but by asking God for a clear conscience based on the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who has gone to heaven and is at the right hand of God, where angels, authorities, and powers have been made subject to him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Therefore, since Christ suffered in the sphere of the flesh, you, too, must arm yourselves with the same determination. For the person who has suffered in the sphere of the flesh has stopped sinning,
B060C004V002	60	4	2	so that he can live the rest of his time in the flesh guided, not by human desires, but by the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For you spent enough time in the past doing what the Gentiles like to do, living in sensuality, sinful desires, drunkenness, wild celebrations, drinking parties, and detestable idolatry.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	They insult you now because they are surprised that you are no longer joining them in the same excesses of wild living.
B060C004V005	60	4	5	They will give an account to the one who is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	Indeed, this is why the gospel was proclaimed even to those who have died, so that they could be judged in the realm of the flesh like all humans and live in the realm of the spirit like God.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	The end of everything is near; so be sensible and clear-headed for the sake of your prayers.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all, continue to love each other deeply, because love covers a multitude of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Show hospitality to one another without complaining.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	As good managers of God's grace in its various forms, serve one another with the gift each of you has received.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	Whoever speaks must speak God's words. Whoever serves must serve with the strength that God supplies, so that in every way God may be glorified through Jesus Christ. Glory and power belong to him forever and ever! Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Dear friends, do not be surprised by the fiery ordeal that is taking place among you to test you, as though something strange were happening to you.
B060C004V013	60	4	13	Instead, because you are participating in the sufferings of Christ, keep on rejoicing, so that you may be glad and shout for joy when his glory is revealed.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you are insulted because of the name of Christ, you are blessed, for the glorious Spirit of God is resting on you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	Of course, none of you should suffer for being a murderer, thief, criminal, or troublemaker.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	But if you suffer for being a Christian, do not feel ashamed, but glorify God with that name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time has come for judgment to begin with the household of God. And if it begins with us, what will be the outcome for those who refuse to obey the gospel of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	“If it is hard for the righteous person to be saved,what will happen to the ungodly and sinful person?”
B060C004V019	60	4	19	So then, those who suffer according to God's will should entrust their souls to a faithful Creator and continue to do what is good.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	Therefore, as a fellow elder, a witness of Christ's sufferings, and one who shares in the glory to be revealed, I appeal to the elders among you:
B060C005V002	60	5	2	Be shepherds of God's flock that is among you, watching over it, not because you must but because you want to, and not greedily but eagerly, as God desires.
B060C005V003	60	5	3	Do not lord it over the people entrusted to you, but be examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	Then, when the Chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the victor's crown of glory that will never fade away.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	In a similar way, you young people must be submissive to the elders. All of you must put on the apron of humility before one another, because	“God opposes the arrogant,but gives grace to the humble.”
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Therefore, humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God, so that at the proper time he may exalt you.
B060C005V007	60	5	7	Throw all your worry on him, because he cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be clear-minded and alert. Your opponent the devil is prowling around like a roaring lion, looking for someone to devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Resist him and be firm in the faith, because you know that your brothers throughout the world are undergoing the same kinds of suffering.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	After you have suffered for a little while, the God of all grace, who called you in Christ Jesus to his eternal glory, will restore you, establish you, strengthen you, and support you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	Power belongs to him forever and ever! Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	Through Silvanus, whom I regard as a faithful brother, I have written this short letter to encourage you and to testify that this is the true grace of God. Stand firm in it!
B060C005V013	60	5	13	Your sister church in Babylon, chosen along with you, sends you greetings, as does my son Mark.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace be to all of you who are in Christ!
B061C001V001	61	1	1	From Simeon Peter, a servant and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who have obtained a faith that is as valuable as ours through the righteousness of our God and Savior, Jesus Christ.
B061C001V002	61	1	2	May grace and peace be yours in abundance through the full knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord!
B061C001V003	61	1	3	His divine power has given us everything we need for life and godliness through the full knowledge of the one who called us by his own glory and excellence.
B061C001V004	61	1	4	Through these he has given us his precious and wonderful promises, so that through them you may participate in the divine nature, seeing that you have escaped the corruption that is in the world caused by evil desires.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	For this very reason, you must make every effort to supplement your faith with moral character, your moral character with knowledge,
B061C001V006	61	1	6	your knowledge with self-control, your self-control with endurance, your endurance with godliness,
B061C001V007	61	1	7	your godliness with brotherly kindness, and your brotherly kindness with love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if you possess these qualities, and if they continue to increase among you, they will keep you from being ineffective and unproductive in attaining a full knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For the person who lacks these qualities is blind and shortsighted, and has forgotten the cleansing that he has received from his past sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	So then, my brothers, be all the more eager to make your calling and election certain, for if you keep on doing this you will never fail.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For in this way you will be generously granted entry into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore, I intend to keep on reminding you about these things, even though you already know them and are firmly established in the truth that you now have.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	Yet I think it is right to refresh your memory as long as I am living in this bodily tent,
B061C001V014	61	1	14	because I know that the removal of my bodily tent will come soon, as indeed our Lord Jesus Christ has shown me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	And I will make every effort to see that you will always remember these things after I am gone.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	When we told you about the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, we did not follow any clever myths. Rather, we were eyewitnesses of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received honor and glory from God the Father when the voice of the Majestic Glory was conveyed to him as follows: “This is my Son, whom I love. I am pleased with him.”
B061C001V018	61	1	18	We ourselves heard this voice that came from heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	Thus we regard the message of the prophets as confirmed beyond doubt, and you will do well to pay attention to it, as to a lamp that is shining in a gloomy place, until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts.
B061C001V020	61	1	20	First of all, you must understand this: No prophecy in Scripture is a matter of one's own interpretation,
B061C001V021	61	1	21	because no prophecy ever originated through a human decision. Instead, men spoke from God as they were carried along by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	Now there were false prophets among the people, just as there also will be false teachers among you, who will secretly introduce destructive heresies and even deny the Master who bought them, bringing swift destruction on themselves.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	Many people will follow their immoral ways, and because of them the way of truth will be maligned.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	In their greed they will exploit you with deceptive words. The ancient verdict against them is still in force, and their destruction is not asleep.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare angels when they sinned, but threw them into hell and committed them to chains of deepest darkness to be kept for judgment;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and if he did not spare the ancient world but protected Noah, a preacher of righteousness, and seven others when he brought the flood on the world of ungodly people;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	and if he condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah and destroyed them by burning them to ashes, making them an example to ungodly people of what is going to happen to them;
B061C002V007	61	2	7	and if he rescued Lot, a righteous man who was greatly distressed by the immoral conduct of lawless people—
B061C002V008	61	2	8	for as long as that righteous man lived among them, day after day he was being tortured in his righteous soul by what he saw and heard in their lawless actions—
B061C002V009	61	2	9	then the Lord knows how to rescue godly people from their trials and to hold unrighteous people for punishment on the day of judgment,
B061C002V010	61	2	10	especially those who satisfy their flesh by indulging in its passions and who despise authority.Being bold and arrogant, they are not afraid to slander glorious beings.
B061C002V011	61	2	11	Yet even angels, although they are greater in strength and power, do not bring a slanderous accusation against them from the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	These people, like irrational animals, are mere creatures of instinct that are born to be caught and killed. They insult what they don't understand, and like animals they, too, will be destroyed,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	suffering wrong as punishment for their wrongdoing. They take pleasure in wild parties in broad daylight. They are stains and blemishes, reveling in their deceitful pleasures while they eat with you.
B061C002V014	61	2	14	With eyes full of adultery, they cannot get enough of sin. They seduce unsteady souls and have had their hearts expertly trained in greed. They are doomed to a curse.
B061C002V015	61	2	15	They have left the straight path and wandered off to follow the path of Balaam, the son of Bosor, who loved the reward he got for doing wrong.
B061C002V016	61	2	16	But he was rebuked for his offense. A donkey that normally cannot talk spoke with a human voice and restrained the prophet's insanity.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These men are dried-up springs, mere clouds driven by a storm. Gloomy darkness is reserved for them.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	By talking high-sounding nonsense and using sinful cravings of the flesh, they entice people who have just escaped from those who live in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	Promising them freedom, they themselves are slaves to depravity, for a person is a slave to whatever conquers him.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after escaping the world's corruptions through a full knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, they are again entangled and conquered by them, then their last condition is worse than their former one.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	It would have been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness than to know it and turn their backs on the holy commandment that was committed to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	The proverb is true that describes what has happened to them: “A dog returns to its vomit,” and “A pig that is washed goes back to wallow in the mud.”
B061C003V001	61	3	1	Dear friends, this is now the second letter I am writing to you. In them I have been trying to stimulate your pure minds by reminding you
B061C003V002	61	3	2	to recall the words spoken in the past by the holy prophets and the commandment of our Lord and Savior spoken through your apostles.
B061C003V003	61	3	3	First of all you must understand this: In the last days mockers will come and, following their own desires, will ridicule us
B061C003V004	61	3	4	by saying, “What happened to his promise to return? Ever since our ancestors died, everything continues as it did from the beginning of creation.”
B061C003V005	61	3	5	But they deliberately ignore the fact that long ago the heavens existed and the earth was formed by God's word out of water and with water,
B061C003V006	61	3	6	by which the world at that time was deluged with water and destroyed.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	Now by the same word the present heavens and earth have been reserved for fire and are being kept for the day when ungodly people will be judged and destroyed.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	Don't forget this fact, dear friends: With the Lord a single day is like a thousand years, and a thousand years are like a single day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slow about his promise, as some people understand slowness, but is being patient with you. He does not want anyone to perish, but wants everyone to come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the Day of the Lord will come like a thief. On that day the heavens will disappear with a roaring sound, the elements will be destroyed by fire, and the earth and everything done on it will be exposed.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Since everything will be destroyed in this way, think of the kind of holy and godly people you ought to be
B061C003V012	61	3	12	as you look forward to and hasten the coming of the day of God, by which the heavens will be set ablaze and dissolved and the elements will melt with fire.
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But in keeping with his promise, we are looking forward to new heavens and a new earth, where righteousness is at home.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	So then, dear friends, since you are looking forward to this, make every effort to have him find you without spot or fault and at peace.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	Think of our Lord's patience as salvation, just as our dear brother Paul also wrote to you according to the wisdom given him.
B061C003V016	61	3	16	He speaks about this subject in all his letters. Some things in them are hard to understand, which ignorant and unstable people distort to their own destruction, as they do the rest of the Scriptures.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	And so, dear friends, since you already know these things, continually be on your guard not to be carried away by the deception of lawless people, lest you fall from your secure position.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	Instead, continue to grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. Glory belongs to him both now and on that eternal day! Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	What existed from the beginning, what we have heard, what we have seen with our eyes, what we observed and touched with our own hands—this is the Word of life!
B062C001V002	62	1	2	This life was revealed to us, and we have seen it and testify about it. We declare to you this eternal life that was with the Father and was revealed to us.
B062C001V003	62	1	3	What we have seen and heard we declare to you so that you, too, can have fellowship with us. Now this fellowship of ours is with the Father and with his Son, Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	We are writing these things so that our joy may be full.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This is the message that we have heard from him and declare to you: God is light, and in him there is no darkness—none at all!
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we claim that we have fellowship with him but keep living in the darkness, we are lying and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we keep living in the light as he himself is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say that we do not have any sin, we are deceiving ourselves and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we make it our habit to confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us those sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say that we have never sinned, we make him a liar and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, I'm writing these things to you so that you might not sin. Yet if anyone does sin, we have an advocate with the Father—Jesus Christ, one who is righteous.
B062C002V002	62	2	2	It is he who is the atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the whole world's.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	This is how we can be sure that we have come to know him: if we continually keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	The person who says, “I have come to know him,” but does not continually keep his commandments is a liar, and the truth is not in that person.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever continually keeps his word is the kind of person in whom God's love has truly been perfected. This is how we can be sure that we are in union with him:
B062C002V006	62	2	6	The one who says that he abides in him must live the same way he himself lived.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Dear friends, I am not writing to you a new commandment, but an old commandment that you have had from the beginning. This old commandment is the word you have heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	On the other hand, I am writing to you a new commandment that is true in him and in you. For the darkness is fading away, and the true light is already shining.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	The person who says that he is in the light but hates his brother is still in the darkness.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	The person who loves his brother abides in the light, and there is no reason for him to stumble.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But the person who hates his brother is in the darkness and lives in the darkness. He does not know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I am writing to you, little children,because your sins have been forgivenon account of his name.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers,because you have known the one whohas existed from the beginning.	I am writing to you, young people,because you have overcome the evil one.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, little children,because you have known the Father.	I have written to you, fathers,because you have known the one whohas existed from the beginning.	I have written to you, young people,because you are strongand because God's word remains in youand you have overcome the evil one.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Stop loving the world and the things that are in the world. If anyone persists in loving the world, the Father's love is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For everything that is in the world—the desire for fleshly gratification, the desire for possessions, and worldly arrogance—is not from the Father but is from the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world and its desires are fading away, but the person who does God's will remains forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, it is the last hour. Just as you heard that an antichrist is coming, so now many antichrists have appeared. This is how we know it is the last hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They left us, but they were not part of us, for if they had been part of us, they would have stayed with us. They simply made it clear that none of them was really part of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	You have an anointing from the Holy One and know all things.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written to you because you do not know the truth, but because you do know it and because no lie comes from the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar but the person who denies that Jesus is the Christ? The person who denies the Father and the Son is the antichrist.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	No one who denies the Son has the Father. The person who acknowledges the Son also has the Father.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	What you have heard from the beginning must abide in you. If what you have heard from the beginning abides in you, you will also abide in the Son and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	The message that he himself declared to us is eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	I have written to you about those who are trying to deceive you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	The anointing you received from him abides in you, and you do not need anyone to teach you. Instead, because his anointing teaches you about everything and is true and not a lie, abide in him, as he taught you to do.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	Even now, little children, abide in him. Then, when he appears, we will have confidence and will not turn away from him in shame at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you also know that everyone who practices righteousness has been born from God.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	See what kind of love the Father has given us in letting us be called God's children! Yet that is what we are. For this reason the world does not recognize us, because it did not recognize him either.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Dear friends, we are now God's children, but what we will be like has not been revealed yet. We know that when Christ is revealed we will be like him, because we will see him as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And everyone who has this hope based on him keeps himself pure, just as he is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Everyone who keeps living in sin also practices disobedience. In fact, sin is disobedience.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	You know that he was revealed to take away sins, and there is not any sin in him.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	No one who remains in him goes on sinning. The one who goes on sinning hasn't seen him or known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, don't let anyone deceive you. The person who practices righteousness is righteous, just as he is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	The person who practices sin belongs to the evil one, because the devil has been sinning since the beginning. The reason that the Son of God was revealed was to destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	No one who has been born from God practices sin, because God's seed abides in him. Indeed, he cannot go on sinning, because he has been born from God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	This is how God's children and the devil's children are distinguished. No person who fails to practice righteousness and to love his brother is from God.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	This is the message that you have heard from the beginning: We should love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	Do not be like Cain, who was from the evil one and murdered his brother. And why did he murder him? Because his own deeds were evil and his brother's were righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	So do not be surprised, brothers, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death to life, because we love one another. The person who does not love remains in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Everyone who hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life remaining in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	This is how we have come to know love: Christ gave his life for us. We, too, ought to give our lives for our brothers.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	Whoever has earthly possessions and notices a brother in need and yet withholds his compassion from him, how can the love of God remain in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	Little children, we must stop loving in word and in tongue, but instead love in action and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And this is how we will know that we belong to the truth and how we will be able to establish our hearts in his presence.
B062C003V020	62	3	20	If our hearts condemn us, God is greater than our hearts and knows everything.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Dear friends, if our hearts do not condemn us, we have confidence in the presence of God.
B062C003V022	62	3	22	Whatever we request we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do what pleases him.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his commandment: to believe in the name of his Son, Jesus Christ, and to love one another as he commanded us.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	The person who keeps his commandments abides in God, and God abides in him. This is how we can be sure that he remains in us: he has given us his Spirit.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Dear friends, stop believing every spirit. Instead, test the spirits to see whether they are from God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	This is how you can recognize God's Spirit: Every spirit who acknowledges that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is from God.
B062C004V003	62	4	3	But every spirit who does not acknowledge Jesus is not from God. This is the spirit of the antichrist. You have heard that he is coming, and now he is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	Little children, you belong to God and have overcome them, because the one who is in you is greater than the one who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	These people belong to the world. That is why they speak from the world's perspective, and the world listens to them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We belong to God. The person who knows God listens to us. Whoever does not belong to God does not listen to us. This is how we know the Spirit of truth and the spirit of deceit.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Dear friends, let us continually love one another, because love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born from God and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	The person who does not love does not know God, because God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	This is how God's love was revealed among us: God sent his unique Son into the world so that we might live through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	This is love: not that we have loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son to be the atoning sacrifice for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Dear friends, if this is the way God loved us, we must also love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has ever seen God. If we love one another, God lives in us, and his love is perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	This is how we know that we abide in him and he in us: he has given us his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	We have seen for ourselves and can testify that the Father has sent his Son to be the Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	God abides in the one who acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God, and he abides in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	We have come to know and believe in the love that God has for us. God is love, and the person who abides in love abides in God, and God abides in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	This is how love has been perfected among us: we will have confidence on the day of judgment because, while we are in this world, we are just like him.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear where love exists. Rather, perfect love banishes fear, for fear involves punishment, and the person who lives in fear has not been perfected in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	Whoever says, “I love God,” but hates his brother is a liar. The one who does not love the brother whom he has seen cannot love a God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this is the commandment that we have from him: the person who loves God must also love his brother.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born from God, and everyone who loves the parent also loves the child.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	This is how we know that we love God's children: we love God and keep his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God: that we keep his commandments; and his commandments are not difficult,
B062C005V004	62	5	4	because everyone who is born from God has overcome the world. Our faith is the victory that overcomes the world.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who overcomes the world? Is it not the person who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This man, Jesus Christ, is the one who came by water and blood—not with water only, but with water and with blood. The Spirit is the one who verifies this, because the Spirit is the truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three witnesses—
B062C005V008	62	5	8	the Spirit, the water, and the blood—and these three are one.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we accept human testimony, God's testimony is greater, because it is the testimony of God and because he has testified about his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	The person who believes in the Son of God has this testimony in himself. The person who does not believe God has made him a liar by not believing the testimony that God has given about his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	This is the testimony: God has given us eternal life, and this life is found in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	The person who has the Son has this life. The person who does not have the Son of God does not have this life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	I have written these things to you who believe in the name of the Son of God so that you may know that you have eternal life.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the confidence that we have in him: if we ask for anything according to his will, he listens to us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he listens to our requests, we can be sure that we have what we ask him for.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If anyone sees his brother committing a sin that does not lead to death, he should pray that God would give him life. This applies to those who commit sins that do not lead to death. There is a sin that leads to death. I am not telling you to pray about that.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	Every kind of wrongdoing is sin, yet there are sins that do not lead to death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that the person who has been born from God does not go on sinning. Rather, the Son of God protects them, and the evil one cannot harm them.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are from God and that the whole world lies under the control of the evil one.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	We also know that the Son of God has come and has given us understanding so that we may know the true God. We are in union with the one who is true, his Son Jesus Christ. He is the true God and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, guard yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	From the elder to the chosen lady and her children, whom I love in the truth, and not only I but also all who know the truth,
B063C001V002	63	1	2	because of the truth that abides in us and will be with us forever.
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, and peace will be with us from God the Father and from Jesus Christ, the Father's Son, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I was overjoyed to find some of your children living in the truth, just as the Father has commanded us.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	I am now requesting you, dear lady, that we continue to love each other. It is not as though I am writing to give you a new commandment, but one that we have had from the beginning.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	And this is love: that we live according to his commandments. This is his commandment, just as you have heard it from the beginning. You must live by it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have gone out into the world. They refuse to acknowledge Jesus Christ as coming in the flesh. Any such person is a deceiver and an antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	See to it that you don't destroy what we have worked for, but that you receive your full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Everyone who does not abide in the teaching of Christ but goes beyond it does not have God. The person who abides in the teaching of Christ has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If anyone comes to you and does not bring this teaching, do not take him into your home or even greet him,
B063C001V011	63	1	11	for the one who greets him shares in his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Although I have a great deal to write to you, I would prefer not to use paper and ink. Instead, I hope to come to you and talk with you face to face, so that our joy may be complete.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your chosen sister greet you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	From the elder to my dear friend Gaius, whom I love in truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Dear friend, I pray that you are doing well in every way and that you are healthy, just as your soul is healthy.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I was overjoyed when some brothers arrived and testified about your truthfulness and how you live according to the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than to hear that my children are living according to the truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Dear friend, you are faithful in whatever you do for the brothers, especially when they are strangers.
B064C001V006	64	1	6	They have testified before the church about your love. You will do well to send them on their way in a manner worthy of God.
B064C001V007	64	1	7	After all, they went on their trip for the sake of Christ's name, accepting no support from the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	Therefore, we ought to support such people so that we can become their helpers in spreading the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote a letter to the church, but Diotrephes, who loves to be in charge, will not accept us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	For this reason, when I come I will call attention to what he is doing in spreading false charges against us. And not content with that, he refuses to accept the brothers. He even tries to stop those who want to accept them and throws them out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Dear friend, do not imitate what is evil, but what is good. The person who does what is good is from God. The person who does what is evil has never seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius has received a good report from everyone, including the truth itself. We, too, can testify to this, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	Although I have a great deal to write to you, I would rather not write with pen and ink.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	Instead, I hope to see you soon and talk face to face.May peace be with you! Your friends greet you. Greet each of our friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	From Jude, a servant of Jesus Christ and yet a brother of James, to those who have been called, who are loved by God the Father and kept safe by Jesus Christ.
B065C001V002	65	1	2	May mercy, peace, and love be yours in abundance!
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Dear friends, although I was eager to write to you about the salvation we share, I found it necessary to write to you and urge you to continue your vigorous defense of the faith that was passed down to the saints once and for all.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For some people have slipped in among you unnoticed. They were written about long ago as being deserving of this condemnation because they are ungodly. They turn the grace of our God into uncontrollable lust and deny our only Master and Lord, Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	Now I want to remind you, even though you are fully aware of these things, that the Lord who once saved his people from the land of Egypt later destroyed those who did not believe.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	He has also held in eternal chains those angels who did not keep their own position but abandoned their assigned place. They are held in deepest darkness for judgment on the great day.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	Likewise, Sodom and Gomorrah and the cities near them, which like them committed sexual sins and engaged in homosexual activities, serve as an example of the punishment of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	In a similar way, these dreamers also defile their flesh, reject the Lord's authority, and slander his glorious beings.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	Even the archangel Michael, when he argued with the devil and fought over the body of Moses, did not dare to bring a slanderous accusation against him but said, “May the Lord rebuke you!”
B065C001V010	65	1	10	Whatever these people do not understand, they slander. Like irrational animals, they are destroyed by the very things they know by instinct.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	How terrible it will be for them! For they followed the path of Cain, rushed headlong into Balaam's error to make a profit, and destroyed themselves in Korah's rebellion.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These people are stains on your love feasts. They feast with you without any sense of awe. They are shepherds who care only for themselves. They are waterless clouds blown about by the winds. They are autumn trees that are fruitless, twice dead, and uprooted.
B065C001V013	65	1	13	They are wild waves of the sea, churning up the foam of their own shame. They are wandering stars for whom the deepest darkness has been reserved forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	Enoch, in the seventh generation from Adam, prophesied about these people when he said,“Look! The Lord has come with countless thousands of his holy ones.
B065C001V015	65	1	15	He will execute judgment on all people and convict everyone of all the ungodly things that they have done in such an ungodly way, including all the harsh things that these ungodly sinners have said about him.”
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These people are complainers and faultfinders, following their own desires. Their mouths speak arrogant things, and they flatter people in order to take advantage of them.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, dear friends, must remember the statements and predictions of the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B065C001V018	65	1	18	They kept telling you, “In the last times mockers will appear, following their own ungodly desires.”
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are the people who cause divisions. They are worldly, devoid of the Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, dear friends, must continue to build yourselves up on your most holy faith. Pray in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	and remain in God's love as you look for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ that brings eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	Show mercy to those who have doubts.
B065C001V023	65	1	23	Save others by snatching them from the fire. To others, show mercy, but with fear, hating even the clothes stained by their sinful lives.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now to the one who is able to keep you from falling and to make you stand faultless in his glorious presence with rejoicing,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	to the only God, our Savior, through Jesus Christ our Lord, be glory, majesty, power, and authority before all time and for all eternity! Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	This is the revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave him to show his servants the things that must happen soon. He made it known by sending his angel to his servant John,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who testified to what he saw: the word of God and the testimony about Jesus Christ.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	How blessed is the one who reads aloud and those who hear the words of this prophecy and keep what is written in it, for the time is near!
B066C001V004	66	1	4	From John to the seven churches in Asia. May grace and peace be yours from the one who is, who was, and who is coming, from the seven spirits who are in front of his throne,
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ, the witness, the faithful one, the firstborn from the dead, and the ruler over the kings of the earth. To the one who loves us and has freed us from our sins by his blood
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and has made us a kingdom, priests for his God and Father, be glory and power forever and ever! Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Look! He is coming in the clouds.Every eye will see him, even those who pierced him,and all the tribes of the earth will mourn because of him.So be it! Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	
        
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I am John, your brother and partner in suffering, ruling, and enduring because of Jesus. I was on the island called Patmos because of the word of God and the testimony about Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I came to be in the Spirit on the Day of the Lord, when I heard a loud voice behind me like a trumpet,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	saying,
B066C001V012	66	1	12	Then I turned to see the voice that was talking to me, and when I turned I saw seven gold lampstands.
B066C001V013	66	1	13	Among the lampstands there was someone like the Son of Man. He was wearing a long robe with a gold belt around his waist.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and his hair were white like wool, in fact, as white as snow. His eyes were like flames of fire,
B066C001V015	66	1	15	his feet were like glowing bronze refined in a furnace, and his voice was like the sound of raging waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	In his right hand he held seven stars, and out of his mouth came a sharp, two-edged sword. His face was like the sun when it shines with full force.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	When I saw him, I fell down at his feet like a dead man. But he placed his right hand on me and said,
