B066C004V001	66	4	1	After these things I saw a door standing open in heaven. The first voice, which I had heard speaking to me like a trumpet, said,
B066C004V002	66	4	2	Instantly I was in the Spirit, and I saw a throne in heaven with a person seated on the throne.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	The person sitting there looked like jasper and carnelian, and there was a rainbow around the throne that looked like an emerald.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	Around the throne were twenty-four other thrones, and on these thrones sat twenty-four elders wearing white robes and gold victor's crowns on their heads.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	Flashes of lightning, noises, and peals of thunder came from the throne. Burning in front of the throne were seven flaming torches, which are the seven spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	In front of the throne was something like a sea of glass as clear as crystal. In the center of the throne and on each side of the throne were four living creatures full of eyes in front and in back.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	The first living creature was like a lion, the second living creature was like an ox, the third living creature had a face like a human, and the fourth living creature was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	Each of the four living creatures had six wings and were full of eyes inside and out. Without stopping day or night they were singing,	“Holy, holy, holyis the Lord God Almighty,who was, who is, and who is coming.”
B066C004V009	66	4	9	Whenever the living creatures give glory, honor, and thanks to the one who sits on the throne, who lives forever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the twenty-four elders bow down in front of the one who sits on the throne and worship the one who lives forever and ever. They throw their victor's crowns in front of the throne and say,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	“You are worthy, our Lord and God,to receive glory, honor, and power,because you created all things,				and they came into existence				and were created because of your will.”
B066C005V001	66	5	1	Then I saw in the right hand of the one who sits on the throne a scroll written on the inside and on the outside, sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	I also saw a powerful angel proclaiming with a loud voice, “Who is worthy to open the scroll and break its seals?”
B066C005V003	66	5	3	No one in heaven, on earth, or under the earth could open the scroll or look inside it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	I began to cry bitterly because no one was found worthy to open the scroll or look inside it.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	Then one of the elders said to me, “Stop crying. Look! The Lion from the tribe of Judah, the Root of David, has conquered. He can open the scroll and its seven seals.”
B066C005V006	66	5	6	Then I saw a lamb standing in the middle of the throne, the four living creatures, and the elders. He looked like he had been slaughtered. He had seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven spirits of God sent into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	He went and took the scroll from the right hand of the one who sits on the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	When the lamb had taken the scroll, the four living creatures and the twenty-four elders bowed down in front of him. Each held a harp and a gold bowl full of incense, the prayers of the saints.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	They sang a new song:	“You are worthy to take the scroll and open its seals,because you were slaughtered.	With your blood you purchased people for Godfrom every tribe, language, people, and nation.
B066C005V010	66	5	10	You made them a kingdom and priests for our God,and they will reign on the earth.”
B066C005V011	66	5	11	Then I looked, and I heard the voices of many angels, the living creatures, and the elders surrounding the throne. They numbered ten thousands times ten thousand and thousands times thousands.
B066C005V012	66	5	12	They sang with a loud voice,	“Worthy is the lamb who was slaughteredto receive power, wealth, wisdom, strength, honor, glory, and praise!”
B066C005V013	66	5	13	I heard every creature in heaven, on earth, under the earth, and on the sea, and everything that is in them, saying,	“To the one who sits on the throne and to the lambbe praise, honor, glory, and powerforever and ever!”
B066C005V014	66	5	14	Then the four living creatures said, “Amen!”, and the elders bowed down and worshiped.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	Then I saw the lamb open the first of the seven seals. I heard one of the four living creatures say with a voice like thunder, “Go!”
B066C006V002	66	6	2	Then I looked, and there was a white horse! Its rider had a bow, and a victor's crown had been given to him. He went out as a conqueror to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	When the lamb opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature say, “Go!”
B066C006V004	66	6	4	A second horse went out. It was fiery red, and its rider was given permission to take peace away from the earth and to make people slaughter one another. So he was given a large sword.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	When the lamb opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature say, “Go!” I looked, and there was a black horse! Its rider held a scale in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	I heard what sounded like a voice from among the four living creatures, saying, “A quart of wheat for a denarius, or three quarts of barley for a denarius. But don't damage the olive oil or the wine!”
B066C006V007	66	6	7	When the lamb opened the fourth seal, I heard the voice of the fourth living creature say, “Go!”
B066C006V008	66	6	8	I looked, and there was a pale horse! Its rider's name was Death, and Hades followed him. They were given authority over one-fourth of the earth to kill people using wars, famines, plagues, and the wild animals of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	When the lamb opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls of those who had been slaughtered because of the word of God and the testimony they had given.
B066C006V010	66	6	10	They cried out in a loud voice, “Holy and true Sovereign, how long will it be before you judge and take revenge on those living on the earth who shed our blood?”
B066C006V011	66	6	11	Each of them was given a white robe. They were told to rest a little longer until the number of their fellow servants and their brothers was completed, who would be killed as they had been killed.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	Then I saw the lamb open the sixth seal. There was a powerful earthquake. The sun turned as black as sackcloth made of hair, and the full moon turned as red as blood.
B066C006V013	66	6	13	The stars in the sky fell to the earth like a fig tree drops its fruit when it is shaken by a strong wind.
B066C006V014	66	6	14	The sky vanished like a scroll being rolled up, and every mountain and island was moved from its place.
B066C006V015	66	6	15	Then the kings of the earth, the important people, the generals, the rich, the powerful, and all the slaves and free people hid themselves in caves and among the rocks in the mountains.
B066C006V016	66	6	16	They said to the mountains and rocks, “Fall on us and hide us from the face of the one who sits on the throne and from the wrath of the lamb.
B066C006V017	66	6	17	For the great day of their wrath has come, and who is able to endure it?”
B066C007V001	66	7	1	After this I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth. They were holding back the four winds of the earth so that no wind could blow on the land, on the sea, or on any tree.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	I saw another angel coming from the east having the seal of the living God. He cried out in a loud voice to the four angels who had been permitted to harm the land and sea,
B066C007V003	66	7	3	“Don't harm the land, the sea, or the trees until we have marked the servants of our God with a seal on their foreheads.”
B066C007V004	66	7	4	I heard the number of those who were sealed: 144,000. Those who were sealed were from every tribe of Israel:
B066C007V005	66	7	5	12,000 from the tribe of Judah were sealed, 12,000 from the tribe of Reuben, 12,000 from the tribe of Gad,
B066C007V006	66	7	6	12,000 from the tribe of Asher, 12,000 from the tribe of Naphtali, 12,000 from the tribe of Manasseh,
B066C007V007	66	7	7	12,000 from the tribe of Simeon, 12,000 from the tribe of Levi, 12,000 from the tribe of Issachar,
B066C007V008	66	7	8	12,000 from the tribe of Zebulun, 12,000 from the tribe of Joseph, and 12,000 from the tribe of Benjamin were sealed.
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After these things I looked, and there was a large crowd that no one was able to count! They were from every nation, tribe, people, and language. They were standing in front of the throne and the lamb and were wearing white robes, with palm branches in their hands.
B066C007V010	66	7	10	They cried out in a loud voice,	“Salvation belongs to our God,who sits on the throne,and to the lamb!”
B066C007V011	66	7	11	All the angels stood around the throne and around the elders and the four living creatures. They fell on their faces in front of the throne and worshiped God,
B066C007V012	66	7	12	saying,	“Amen! Praise, glory, wisdom, thanks, honor, power, and strengthbe to our God forever and ever! Amen!”
B066C007V013	66	7	13	Then one of the elders said to me, “Who are these people wearing white robes, and where did they come from?”
B066C007V014	66	7	14	I said to him, “Sir, you know.”Then he told me, “These are the people who are coming out of the terrible suffering. They have washed their robes and made them white in the blood of the lamb.
B066C007V015	66	7	15	That is why:	“They are in front of the throne of Godand worship him night and day in his temple.	The one who sits on the throne will shelter them.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They will never be hungry or thirsty again.Neither the sun nor any burning heat will ever strike them,
B066C007V017	66	7	17	for the lamb in the center of the throne will be their shepherd.	He will lead them to springs filled with the water of life,and God will wipe every tear from their eyes.”
B066C008V001	66	8	1	When the lamb opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	Then I saw the seven angels who stand in God's presence, and seven trumpets were given to them.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	Another angel came with a gold censer and stood at the altar. He was given a large quantity of incense to offer on the gold altar before the throne, along with the prayers of all the saints.
B066C008V004	66	8	4	The smoke from the incense and the prayers of the saints went up from the angel's hand to God.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	The angel took the censer, filled it with fire from the altar, and threw it on the earth. Then there were peals of thunder, noises, flashes of lightning, and an earthquake.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	The seven angels who had the seven trumpets got ready to blow them.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	When the first angel blew his trumpet, hail and fire were mixed with blood and thrown on the earth. One-third of the earth was burned up, one-third of the trees was burned up, and all the green grass was burned up.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	When the second angel blew his trumpet, something like a huge mountain burning with fire was thrown into the sea. One-third of the sea turned into blood,
B066C008V009	66	8	9	one-third of the creatures that were living in the sea died, and one-third of the ships was destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	When the third angel blew his trumpet, a huge star blazing like a torch fell from heaven. It fell on one-third of the rivers and on the springs of water.
B066C008V011	66	8	11	The name of the star is Wormwood. One-third of the water turned into wormwood, and many people died from the water because it had turned bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	When the fourth angel blew his trumpet, one-third of the sun, one-third of the moon, and one-third of the stars were struck so that one-third of them turned dark. One-third of the day was kept from shining, and also the night.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	Then I looked, and I heard an eagle flying overhead say in a loud voice, “How terrible, how terrible, how terrible for those living on the earth, because of the blasts of the remaining trumpets that the three angels are about to blow!”
B066C009V001	66	9	1	When the fifth angel blew his trumpet, I saw a star that had fallen to earth from the sky. The star was given the key to the shaft of the bottomless pit.
B066C009V002	66	9	2	It opened the shaft of the bottomless pit, and smoke came out of the shaft like the smoke from a large furnace. The sun and the air were darkened with the smoke from the shaft.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	Locusts came out of the smoke onto the earth, and they were given power like the power of earthly scorpions.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	They were told not to harm the grass on the earth, any green plant, or any tree. They could harm only the people who do not have the seal of God on their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	They were not allowed to kill them, but were only allowed to torture them for five months. Their torture was like the pain of a scorpion when it stings someone.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	In those days people will look for death and never find it. They will long to die, but death will escape them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	The locusts looked like horses prepared for battle. On their heads were victor's crowns that looked like gold, and their faces were like human faces.
B066C009V008	66	9	8	They had hair like women's hair and teeth like lions’ teeth.
B066C009V009	66	9	9	They had breastplates like iron, and the noise of their wings was like the roar of chariots with many horses rushing into battle.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	They had tails and stingers like scorpions, and they had the power to hurt people with their tails for five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	They had the angel of the bottomless pit ruling over them as king. In Hebrew he is called Abaddon, and in Greek he is called Apollyon.
B066C009V012	66	9	12	The first catastrophe is over. After these things there are still two more catastrophes to come.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	When the sixth angel blew his trumpet, I heard a voice from the four horns of the gold altar in front of God.
B066C009V014	66	9	14	It said to the sixth angel who had the trumpet, “Release the four angels who are held at the great Euphrates River.”
B066C009V015	66	9	15	So the four angels who were ready for that hour, day, month, and year were released to kill one-third of humanity.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	The number of cavalry troops was 200,000,000. I heard how many there were.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	This was how I saw the horses in my vision: The riders wore breastplates that had the color of fire, sapphire, and sulfur. The heads of the horses were like lions’ heads, and fire, smoke, and sulfur came out of their mouths.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	By these three plagues—the fire, the smoke, and the sulfur that came out of their mouths—one-third of humanity was killed.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	For the power of these horses is in their mouths and their tails. Their tails have heads like snakes, which they use to inflict pain.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	The rest of the people who survived these plagues did not repent of the works of their hands or stop worshiping demons and idols made of gold, silver, bronze, stone, and wood, which cannot see, hear, or walk.
B066C009V021	66	9	21	They did not repent of their murders, their deeds of witchcraft, their acts of sexual immorality, or their thefts.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	Then I saw another powerful angel come down from heaven. He was dressed in a cloud, and there was a rainbow over his head. His face was like the sun, and his legs were like columns of fire.
B066C010V002	66	10	2	He held a small, opened scroll in his hand. Setting his right foot on the sea and his left foot on the land,
B066C010V003	66	10	3	he shouted in a loud voice as a lion roars. When he shouted, the seven thunders spoke with voices of their own.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	When the seven thunders spoke, I was going to write, but I heard a voice from heaven say, “Seal up what the seven thunders have said, and don't write it down.”
B066C010V005	66	10	5	Then the angel whom I saw standing on the sea and on the land raised his right hand to heaven.
B066C010V006	66	10	6	He swore an oath by the one who lives forever and ever, who created heaven and everything in it, the earth and everything in it, and the sea and everything in it: “There will be no more delay.
B066C010V007	66	10	7	In the days when the seventh angel is ready to blow his trumpet, the secret of God will be fulfilled, as he had announced to his servants, the prophets.”
B066C010V008	66	10	8	Then the voice that I had heard from heaven spoke to me again, saying, “Go and take the opened scroll from the hand of the angel who is standing on the sea and on the land.”
B066C010V009	66	10	9	So I went to the angel and asked him to give me the small scroll. He said to me, “Take it and eat it. It will be bitter in your stomach, but it will be as sweet as honey in your mouth.”
B066C010V010	66	10	10	So I took the small scroll from the angel's hand and ate it. It was as sweet as honey in my mouth, but when I had eaten it, my stomach was bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	Then the seven thunders told me, “Again you must prophesy about many peoples, nations, languages, and kings.”
B066C011V001	66	11	1	Then I was given a stick like a measuring rod. I was told, “Stand up and measure the temple of God and the altar, and count those who worship there.
B066C011V002	66	11	2	But don't measure the courtyard outside the temple. Leave that out, because it is given to the nations, and they will trample the Holy City for forty-two months.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	I will give my two witnesses who wear sackcloth the authority to prophesy for 1,260 days.”
B066C011V004	66	11	4	These witnesses are the two olive trees and the two lampstands standing in the presence of the Lord of the earth.
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if anyone should want to hurt them, fire comes out of their mouths and burns up their enemies. If anyone wants to hurt them, he must be killed in the same way.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	These witnesses have authority to shut the sky in order to keep rain from falling during the days of their prophesying. They also have authority over the waters to turn them into blood and to strike the earth with any plague as often as they desire.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	When they have finished their testimony, the beast that comes up from the bottomless pit will wage war against them, conquer them, and kill them.
B066C011V008	66	11	8	Their dead bodies will lie in the street of the great city that is spiritually called Sodom and Egypt, where their Lord was crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	For three and a half days some members of the peoples, tribes, languages, and nations will look at their dead bodies and will not allow them to be placed in a tomb.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	Those living on earth will gloat over them, celebrate, and send gifts to each other, because these two prophets had tormented those living on earth.
B066C011V011	66	11	11	But after the three and a half days, the breath of life from God entered them, and they stood on their feet. Those who watched them were terrified.
B066C011V012	66	11	12	Then the witnesses heard a loud voice from heaven calling to them, “Come up here!” So they went up to heaven in a cloud, and their enemies watched them.
B066C011V013	66	11	13	At that moment a powerful earthquake struck. One-tenth of the city collapsed, 7,000 people were killed by the earthquake, and the rest were terrified and gave glory to the God of heaven.
B066C011V014	66	11	14	The second catastrophe is over. The third catastrophe is coming very soon.
B066C011V015	66	11	15	When the seventh angel blew his trumpet, there were loud voices in heaven, saying,	“The kingdom of the world has become the kingdom of our Lord and of his Christ,and he will rule forever and ever.”
B066C011V016	66	11	16	Then the twenty-four elders who were sitting on their thrones in God's presence fell on their faces and worshiped God.
B066C011V017	66	11	17	They said,	“We give thanks to you, Lord God Almighty,who is and who was,because you have taken your great powerand have begun to rule.
B066C011V018	66	11	18	The nations were angry,but your wrath has come.	It is time for the dead to be judged—to reward your servants, the prophets, the saints, and all who fear your name,both unimportant and important,and to destroy those who destroy the earth.”
B066C011V019	66	11	19	Then the temple of God in heaven was opened, and the ark of his covenant was seen inside his temple. There were flashes of lightning, noises, peals of thunder, an earthquake, and heavy hail.
B066C012V001	66	12	1	A spectacular sign appeared in the sky: a woman dressed with the sun, who had the moon under her feet and a victor's crown of twelve stars on her head.
B066C012V002	66	12	2	She was pregnant and was crying out from labor pains and the agony of giving birth.
B066C012V003	66	12	3	Then another sign appeared in the sky: a huge red dragon with seven heads, ten horns, and seven royal crowns on its heads.
B066C012V004	66	12	4	Its tail swept away one-third of the stars in the sky and threw them down to the earth. Then the dragon stood in front of the woman who was about to give birth so that it could devour her child when it was born.
B066C012V005	66	12	5	She gave birth to a son, a boy, who is to rule all the nations with an iron scepter. But her child was snatched away and taken to God and to his throne.
B066C012V006	66	12	6	Then the woman fled into the wilderness, where a place had been prepared for her by God so that she might be taken care of for 1,260 days.
B066C012V007	66	12	7	Then a war broke out in heaven. Michael and his angels fought with the dragon, and the dragon and its angels fought back.
B066C012V008	66	12	8	But it was not strong enough, and there was no longer any place for them in heaven.
B066C012V009	66	12	9	The huge dragon was thrown down. That ancient serpent, called devil and Satan, the deceiver of the whole world, was thrown down to the earth, and its angels were thrown down with it.
B066C012V010	66	12	10	Then I heard a loud voice in heaven say,	“Now the salvation, the power,the kingdom of our God,and the authority of his Christ have come.	For the one accusing our brothers,the one who accuses them day and nightin the presence of our God, has been thrown out.
B066C012V011	66	12	11	They conquered him by the blood of the lamband by the word of their testimony,for they did not love their life even in the face of death.
B066C012V012	66	12	12	So be glad, heavens, and those who live in them!	How terrible it is for the earth and the sea,because the devil has come down to you with great wrath,knowing that his time is short!”
B066C012V013	66	12	13	When the dragon saw that it had been thrown down to the earth, it persecuted the woman who had given birth to the boy.
B066C012V014	66	12	14	However, the woman was given the two wings of a large eagle so that she could fly away from the serpent to her place in the wilderness, where she could be taken care of for a time, times, and half a time.
B066C012V015	66	12	15	From its mouth the serpent poured water like a river behind the woman in order to sweep her away with the flood.
B066C012V016	66	12	16	But the earth helped the woman by opening its mouth and swallowing the river that the dragon had poured from its mouth.
B066C012V017	66	12	17	Then the dragon became angry with the woman and went away to do battle against the rest of her children, the ones who keep God's commandments and hold on to the testimony about Jesus.
B066C013V001	66	13	1	Then the dragon stood on the sand of the seashore.I saw a beast coming out of the sea. It had ten horns, seven heads, and ten royal crowns on its horns. On its heads were blasphemous names.
B066C013V002	66	13	2	The beast that I saw was like a leopard. Its feet were like bear's feet, and its mouth was like a lion's mouth. The dragon gave it his power, his throne, and complete authority.
B066C013V003	66	13	3	One of the beast's heads looked like it had a fatal wound, but its fatal wound was healed. And in amazement the whole world followed the beast.
B066C013V004	66	13	4	They worshiped the dragon because it had given authority to the beast. They also worshiped the beast, saying, “Who is like the beast, and who can fight a war with it?”
B066C013V005	66	13	5	The beast was allowed to speak arrogant and blasphemous things, and it was given authority for forty-two months.
B066C013V006	66	13	6	It opened its mouth to utter blasphemies against God and to blaspheme his name and his residence, that is, those who are living in heaven.
B066C013V007	66	13	7	It was allowed to wage war against the saints and to conquer them. It was also given authority over every tribe, people, language, and nation.
B066C013V008	66	13	8	All those living on earth will worship it, everyone whose name is not written in the Book of Life belonging to the lamb that was slaughtered from the foundation of the world.
B066C013V009	66	13	9	Let anyone who has an ear listen:
B066C013V010	66	13	10	If anyone is to be taken captive,he must go into captivity.	If anyone is to be killed with a sword,he must be killed with a sword.This is what the endurance and faith of the saints means.
B066C013V011	66	13	11	Then I saw another beast coming up out of the earth. It had two horns like a lamb and it talked like a dragon.
B066C013V012	66	13	12	It uses all the authority of the first beast on its behalf, and it makes the earth and those living on it worship the first beast, whose fatal wound was healed.
B066C013V013	66	13	13	It performs spectacular signs, even making fire come down from heaven to earth in front of people.
B066C013V014	66	13	14	It deceives those living on earth with the signs that it is allowed to do on behalf of the first beast, telling them to make an image for the beast who was wounded by a sword and yet lived.
B066C013V015	66	13	15	The second beast was allowed to give breath to the image of the first beast so that the image of the beast could talk and put to death those who would not worship the image of the beast.
B066C013V016	66	13	16	The second beast forces all people—important and unimportant, rich and poor, free and slaves—to be marked on their right hands or on their foreheads,
B066C013V017	66	13	17	so that no one may buy or sell unless he has the mark, which is the beast's name or the number of its name.
B066C013V018	66	13	18	This calls for wisdom: Let the person who has understanding figure out the number of the beast, because it is the number of a person. Its number is 666.
B066C014V001	66	14	1	Then I looked, and there was the lamb standing on Mount Zion! With him were 144,000 people who had his name and his Father's name written on their foreheads.
B066C014V002	66	14	2	Then I heard a voice from heaven like the sound of many waters and like the sound of loud thunder. The voice I heard was like the sound of harpists playing on their harps.
B066C014V003	66	14	3	They were singing a new song in front of the throne, the four living creatures, and the elders. No one could learn the song except the 144,000 who had been redeemed from the earth.
B066C014V004	66	14	4	They have not defiled themselves with women, for they are virgins, and they follow the lamb wherever he goes. They have been redeemed from among humanity as the first fruits for God and the lamb.
B066C014V005	66	14	5	In their mouth no lie was found. They are blameless.
B066C014V006	66	14	6	Then I saw another angel flying overhead with the eternal gospel to proclaim to those who live on earth—to every nation, tribe, language, and people.
B066C014V007	66	14	7	He said in a loud voice, “Fear God and give him glory, because the hour of his judgment has come. Worship the one who made heaven and earth, the sea and springs of water.”
B066C014V008	66	14	8	Then another angel, a second one, followed him, saying, “Fallen! Babylon the Great has fallen! She has made all the nations drink the wine of the wrath of her sexual sins.”
B066C014V009	66	14	9	Then another angel, a third one, followed them, saying in a loud voice, “Whoever worships the beast and its image and receives a mark on his forehead or his hand
B066C014V010	66	14	10	will drink the wine of God's wrath, which has been poured unmixed into the cup of his anger. He will be tortured with fire and sulfur in the presence of the holy angels and the lamb.
B066C014V011	66	14	11	The smoke from their torture goes up forever and ever. There is no rest day or night for those who worship the beast and its image or for anyone who receives the mark of its name.”
B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is a call for the endurance of the saints, who keep the commandments of God and hold on to the faithfulness of Jesus.
B066C014V013	66	14	13	I heard a voice from heaven say, “Write this: How blessed are the dead who die in the Lord from now on!”“Yes,” says the Spirit. “Let them rest from their labors, for their deeds follow them.”
B066C014V014	66	14	14	Then I looked, and there was a white cloud! On the cloud sat someone who was like the Son of Man, with a gold victor's crown on his head and a sharp sickle in his hand.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	Another angel came out of the temple, crying out in a loud voice to the one who sat on the cloud, “Swing your sickle, and gather the harvest, for the hour has come to gather it, because the harvest on the earth is fully ripe.”
B066C014V016	66	14	16	The one who sat on the cloud swung his sickle over the earth, and the earth was harvested.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	Then another angel came out of the temple in heaven. He, too, had a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	From the altar came another angel who had authority over fire. He called out in a loud voice to the angel who had the sharp sickle, “Swing your sharp sickle, and gather the bunches of grapes from the vine of the earth, because those grapes are ripe.”
B066C014V019	66	14	19	So the angel swung his sickle on the earth and gathered the grapes from the earth and threw them into the great winepress of God's wrath.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	The wine press was trampled outside the city, and blood flowed out of the wine press as high as a horse's bridle for 200 miles.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	I saw another sign in heaven. It was spectacular and amazing. There were seven angels with the seven last plagues. With them God's wrath has come to its completion.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	Then I saw what looked like a sea of glass mixed with fire. Those who had conquered the beast, its image, and the number of its name were standing on the sea of glass holding God's harps in their hands.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	They sang the song of God's servant Moses and the song of the lamb:	“Your deeds are spectacular and amazing, Lord God Almighty.	Your ways are just and true, King of the nations.
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Lord, who won't fear and praise your name?For you alone are holy,and all the nations will come and worship you because your judgments have been revealed.”
B066C015V005	66	15	5	After these things I looked, and the temple of the tent of witness in heaven was open!
B066C015V006	66	15	6	The seven angels with the seven plagues came out of the temple wearing clean, shining linen with gold belts around their waists.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	One of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels seven gold bowls full of the wrath of God, who lives forever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	The temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God and his power, and no one could enter the temple until the seven plagues of the seven angels came to an end.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	Then I heard a loud voice from the temple saying to the seven angels, “Go and pour the seven bowls of God's wrath on the earth.”
B066C016V002	66	16	2	So the first angel went and poured his bowl on the earth. A horrible, painful sore appeared on the people who had the mark of the beast and worshiped the image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	The second angel poured his bowl into the sea. It became like the blood of a dead body, and every living thing in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	The third angel poured his bowl into the rivers and the springs of water, and they turned into blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	Then I heard the angel of the water say,	“You are just. You are the one who isand who was, the Holy One,because you have judged these things.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	You have given them blood to drinkbecause they have poured out the blood of saints and prophets.This is what they deserve.”
B066C016V007	66	16	7	Then I heard the altar reply,	“Yes, Lord God Almighty,your judgments are true and just.”
B066C016V008	66	16	8	The fourth angel poured his bowl on the sun. It was allowed to burn people with fire,
B066C016V009	66	16	9	and they were burned by the fierce heat. They cursed the name of God, who has the authority over these plagues. They did not repent and give him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	The fifth angel poured his bowl on the throne of the beast. Its kingdom was plunged into darkness. People gnawed on their tongues in anguish
B066C016V011	66	16	11	and cursed the God of heaven because of their pains and sores. But they did not repent of their deeds.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	The sixth angel poured his bowl on the great Euphrates River. Its water was dried up to prepare the way for the kings from the east.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	Then I saw three disgusting spirits like frogs come out of the mouth of the dragon, out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	They are demonic spirits that perform signs. They go to the kings of the whole earth and gather them for the war of the great day of God Almighty.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	
        
B066C016V016	66	16	16	The spirits gathered the kings at the place that is called Armageddon in Hebrew.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	The seventh angel poured his bowl into the air. A loud voice came from the throne in the temple and said, “It has happened!”
B066C016V018	66	16	18	There were flashes of lightning, noises, peals of thunder, and a powerful earthquake. There has never been such a powerful earthquake since people have been on the earth.
B066C016V019	66	16	19	The great city was split into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell. God remembered to give Babylon the Great the cup of wine filled with the fury of his wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	Every island vanished, and the mountains could no longer be found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	Huge hailstones, each weighing about 100 pounds, fell from the sky on people. They cursed God because the plague of hail was such a terrible plague.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	Then one of the seven angels who held the seven bowls came and said to me, “Come, I will show you the judgment of the notorious prostitute who sits on many waters.
B066C017V002	66	17	2	The kings of the earth committed sexual immorality with her, and those living on earth became drunk with the wine of her immorality.”
B066C017V003	66	17	3	Then the angel carried me away in the Spirit into a wilderness. I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet beast that was filled with blasphemous names. It had seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	The woman wore purple and scarlet clothes and was adorned with gold, gems, and pearls. In her hand she was holding a gold cup filled with detestable things and the impurities of her immorality.
B066C017V005	66	17	5	On her forehead was written a secret name:BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF PROSTITUTES AND DETESTABLE THINGS OF THE EARTH.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	I saw that the woman was drunk with the blood of the saints and the blood of the witnesses to Jesus. I was very surprised when I saw her.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	The angel said to me, “Why are you surprised? I will tell you the secret of the woman and the beast with the seven heads and the ten horns that carries her.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw once was, is no longer, and is going to come from the bottomless pit and go to its destruction. Those living on earth, whose names were not written in the Book of Life from the foundation of the world, will be surprised when they see the beast because it was, is no longer, and will come again.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	This calls for a mind that has wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains on which the woman is sitting. They are also seven kings.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	Five of them have fallen, one is living, and the other has not yet come. When he comes, he must remain for a little while.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	The beast that was and is no longer is the eighth king, but it belongs with the seven kings and goes to its destruction.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	The ten horns that you saw are ten kings who have not yet received a kingdom. They will receive authority to rule as kings with the beast for one hour.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	They have one purpose: to give their power and authority to the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	They will wage war against the lamb, but the lamb will conquer them because he is Lord of lords and King of kings. Those who are called, chosen, and faithful are with him.”
B066C017V015	66	17	15	The angel also said to me, “The waters you saw, on which the prostitute is sitting, are peoples, multitudes, nations, and languages.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	The ten horns and the beast you saw will hate the prostitute. They will leave her abandoned and naked. They will eat her flesh and burn her up with fire,
B066C017V017	66	17	17	for God has put it into their hearts to carry out his purpose. And so they will give their kingdom to the beast until God's words are fulfilled.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	The woman you saw is the great city that rules over the kings of the earth.”
B066C018V001	66	18	1	After these things I saw another angel coming down from heaven. He had great authority, and the earth was made bright by his splendor.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	He cried out in a powerful voice,	“Fallen! Babylon the Great has fallen!She has become a home for demons.	She is a prison for every unclean spirit,a prison for every unclean bird,and a prison for every uncleanand hated beast.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all the nations have drunkfrom the wine of her sexual immorality,	and the kings of the earth have committed sexual immorality with her.	The merchants of the earth have become richfrom the power of her luxury.”
B066C018V004	66	18	4	Then I heard another voice from heaven saying,	“Come out of her, my people,so that you don't participate in her sinsand suffer from her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins are piled as high as heaven,and God has remembered her crimes.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Do to her as she herself has done.Give her double for her deeds.	Mix a double drink for her in the cup she mixed.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	Just as she glorified herself and lived in luxury,so give her just as much torture and misery.	In her heart she says,‘I am a queen on a throne, not a widow.I will never see misery.’
B066C018V008	66	18	8	For this reason her plagues of death, misery, and famine will come in a single day.	She will be burned up in a fire,because powerful is the Lord God who judges her.”
B066C018V009	66	18	9	The kings of the earth, who committed sexual immorality with her and lived in luxury with her, will cry and mourn over her when they see the smoke rising from her fire.
B066C018V010	66	18	10	Frightened by her torture, they will stand far away and say,	“How terrible, how terrible it is for that great city,the powerful city Babylon!For in one hour your judgment has come!”
B066C018V011	66	18	11	The merchants of the earth cry and mourn over her, because no one buys their cargo anymore—
B066C018V012	66	18	12	cargo of gold, silver, gems, pearls, fine linen, purple cloth, silk, scarlet cloth, all kinds of scented wood, all articles made of ivory, all articles made of very costly wood, bronze, iron, marble,
B066C018V013	66	18	13	cinnamon, spice, incense, myrrh, frankincense, wine, olive oil, flour, wheat, cattle, sheep, horses, chariots, and slaves (that is, human souls).
B066C018V014	66	18	14	“The fruit for which your soul craved has left you.All your dainties and your splendor are lost to you. No one will ever find them again.”
B066C018V015	66	18	15	Frightened by her torture, the merchants of these wares who had become rich from her will stand far away. They will cry and mourn,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	saying,	“How terrible, how terrible it is for the great citythat was clothed in fine linen, purple, and scarletand was adorned with gold, gems, and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	For in one hour all this wealth has been destroyed!”Every ship's captain, everyone who traveled by ship, sailors, and everyone who made a living by the sea stood far away.
B066C018V018	66	18	18	When they saw the smoke from her fire, they began to cry out, “What city was like the great city?”
B066C018V019	66	18	19	Then they threw dust on their heads and shouted while crying and mourning,	“How terrible, how terrible it is for the great city,where all who had ships at sea became richbecause of her wealth!		For in one hour she has been destroyed!
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Gloat over her, heaven, saints, apostles, and prophets!For God has condemned her for you.”
B066C018V021	66	18	21	Then a powerful angel picked up a stone that was like a large millstone and threw it into the sea, saying,	“The great city Babylon will be thrown down with violent force—and will never be found again.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	The sound of harpists, musicians, flutists, and trumpeterswill never be heard in you again.	No artisan of any tradewill ever be found in you again.	The sound of a millstonewill never be heard in you again.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	The light from a lamp will never shine in you again.	The voice of a bridegroom and bridewill never be heard in you again.	For your merchants were the important people of the world,and all the nations were deceived by your witchcraft.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	The blood of prophets, saints, and all who had been murderedon earth was found in her.”
B066C019V001	66	19	1	After these things I heard what sounded like the loud voice of a large crowd in heaven, saying,	“Hallelujah!	Salvation, glory, and power belong to our God.
B066C019V002	66	19	2	His judgments are true and just.He has condemned the notorious prostitutewho corrupted the world with her immorality.	He has taken revenge on herfor the blood of his servants.”
B066C019V003	66	19	3	A second time they said,	“Hallelujah!The smoke goes up from her forever and ever.”
B066C019V004	66	19	4	The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures bowed down and worshiped God, who was sitting on the throne. They said, “Amen! Hallelujah!”
B066C019V005	66	19	5	A voice came from the throne, saying,	“Praise our God,all who serve and fear him,from the least importantto the most important.”
B066C019V006	66	19	6	Then I heard what sounded like the voice of a large crowd, like the sound of raging waters, and like the sound of powerful thunderclaps, saying,	“Hallelujah!The Lord our God, the Almighty, is reigning.
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice, be glad, and give him glory,because the marriage of the lamb has comeand his bride has made herself ready.
B066C019V008	66	19	8	She has been given the privilege of wearing fine linen,dazzling and pure.”(The fine linen represents the righteous deeds of the saints.)
B066C019V009	66	19	9	Then the angel said to me, “Write this: ‘How blessed are those who are invited to the marriage supper of the lamb!’” He also told me, “These are the true words of God.”
B066C019V010	66	19	10	I bowed down at his feet to worship him, but he told me, “Don't do that! I am a fellow servant with you and with your brothers who hold on to the testimony of Jesus. Worship God, because the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy!”
B066C019V011	66	19	11	Then I saw heaven standing open, and there was a white horse! Its rider is named Faithful and True, and in righteousness he judges and wages war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	His eyes are like a flame of fire, and on his head are many royal crowns. He has a name written on him that nobody knows except himself.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	He is dressed in a robe dipped in blood, and his name is called the Word of God.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	The armies of heaven, wearing fine linen, white and pure, follow him on white horses.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	A sharp sword comes out of his mouth to strike down the nations. He will rule them with an iron rod and tread the winepress of the fury of the wrath of God Almighty.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	On his robe and his thigh he has a name written:KING OF KINGS AND LORD OF LORDS.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	Then I saw an angel standing in the sun. He cried out in a loud voice to all the birds flying overhead, “Come! Gather for the great supper of God.
B066C019V018	66	19	18	Eat the flesh of kings, the flesh of commanders, the flesh of warriors, the flesh of horses and their riders, and the flesh of all people, both free and slaves, both unimportant and important.”
B066C019V019	66	19	19	Then I saw the beast, the kings of the earth, and their armies gathered to wage war against the rider on the horse and his army.
B066C019V020	66	19	20	The beast was captured, along with the false prophet who had performed signs on its behalf. By these signs the false prophet had deceived those who had received the mark of the beast and worshiped its image. Both of them were thrown alive into the lake of fire that burns with sulfur.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	The rest were killed by the sword that belonged to the rider on the horse and that came from his mouth. And all the birds gorged themselves on their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven, holding the key to the bottomless pit and a large chain in his hand.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	He captured the dragon, that ancient serpent, who is the devil and Satan, and tied him up for a thousand years.
B066C020V003	66	20	3	He threw him into the bottomless pit, locked it, and sealed it over him to keep him from deceiving the nations anymore until the thousand years were over. After that he must be set free for a little while.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	Then I saw thrones, and those who sat on them were given authority to judge. I also saw the souls of those who had been beheaded because of their testimony about Jesus and because of the word of God. They had not worshiped the beast or its image and had not received its mark on their foreheads or hands. They came back to life and ruled with Christ for a thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	The rest of the dead did not come back to life until the thousand years were over. This is the first resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	How blessed and holy are those who participate in the first resurrection! The second death has no power over them. They will be priests of God and Christ, and will rule with him for a thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	When the thousand years are over, Satan will be freed from his prison.
B066C020V008	66	20	8	He will go out to deceive Gog and Magog, the nations at the four corners of the earth, and gather them for war. They are as numerous as the sands of the seashore.
B066C020V009	66	20	9	They marched over the broad expanse of the earth and surrounded the camp of the saints and the beloved city. Fire came from God out of heaven and burned them up,
B066C020V010	66	20	10	and the devil who deceived them was thrown into the lake of fire and sulfur, where the beast and the false prophet were. They will be tortured day and night forever and ever.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	Then I saw a large, white throne and the one who was sitting on it. The earth and the heavens fled from his presence, and no place was found for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	I saw the dead, both unimportant and important, standing in front of the throne, and books were open. Another book was opened—the Book of Life. The dead were judged according to their works, as recorded in the books.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	The sea gave up the dead that were in it, and Death and Hades gave up the dead that were in them, and all were judged according to their works.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	Death and Hades were thrown into the lake of fire. (This is the second death—the lake of fire.)
B066C020V015	66	20	15	Anyone whose name was not found written in the Book of Life was thrown into the lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth, because the first heaven and the first earth had disappeared, and the sea was gone.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	I also saw the holy city, New Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven, prepared like a bride adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	I heard a loud voice from the throne say, “See, the tabernacle of God is among humans! He will make his home with them, and they will be his people. God himself will be with them, and he will be their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	He will wipe every tear from their eyes. There won't be death anymore. There won't be any grief, crying, or pain, because the first things have disappeared.”
B066C021V005	66	21	5	The one sitting on the throne said,
B066C021V006	66	21	6	Then he said to me,
B066C021V007	66	21	7	
        
B066C021V008	66	21	8	
        
B066C021V009	66	21	9	Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues came to me and said, “Come! I will show you the bride, the wife of the lamb.”
B066C021V010	66	21	10	He carried me away in the Spirit to a large, high mountain and showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven.
B066C021V011	66	21	11	It had the glory of God, and its light was like a valuable gem, like jasper, as clear as crystal.
B066C021V012	66	21	12	It had a large, high wall with twelve gates. Twelve angels were at the gates, and the names of the twelve tribes of Israel were written on the gates.
B066C021V013	66	21	13	There were three gates on the east, three gates on the north, three gates on the south, and three gates on the west.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	The wall of the city had twelve foundations, and the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the lamb were written on them.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	The angel who was talking to me had a gold measuring rod to measure the city, its gates, and its walls.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	The city was square: its length was the same as its width. He measured the city with his rod, and it was 12,000 stadia long. Its length, width, and height were the same.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	He also measured its wall. According to the human measurement that the angel was using it was 144 cubits.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	Its wall was made of jasper. The city was made of pure gold, as clear as glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	The foundations of the city wall were decorated with all kinds of gems: The first foundation was jasper, the second sapphire, the third agate, the fourth emerald,
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the fifth onyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth, and the twelfth amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	The twelve gates were twelve pearls, and each gate was made of a single pearl. The street of the city was made of pure gold, as clear as glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	I saw no temple in it, because the Lord God Almighty and the lamb are its temple.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	The city doesn't need any sun or moon to give it light, because the glory of God gave it light, and the lamb was its lamp.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	The nations will walk in its light, and the kings of the earth will bring their glory into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	Its gates will never be shut by day, because there won't be any night there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	People will bring the glory and wealth of the nations into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	Nothing unclean, or anyone who does anything detestable, and no one who tells lies will ever enter it. Only those whose names are written in the lamb's Book of Life will enter it.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	Then the angel showed me the river of the water of life, as clear as crystal. It was flowing from the throne of God and the lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	Between the street of the city and the river there was the tree of life visible from both sides. It produced twelve kinds of fruit, each month having its own fruit. The leaves of the tree are for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	There will no longer be any curse. The throne of God and the lamb will be in the city. His servants will worship him
B066C022V004	66	22	4	and see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	There will be no more night, and they will not need any light from lamps or the sun because the Lord God will shine on them. They will rule forever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	He said to me, “These words are trustworthy and true. The Lord God of the spirits and of the prophets has sent his angel to show his servants the things that must happen soon.”
B066C022V007	66	22	7	
        
B066C022V008	66	22	8	I, John, heard and saw these things. When I had heard and seen them, I bowed down to worship at the feet of the angel who had been showing me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	But he told me, “Don't do that! I am a fellow servant with you, your brothers the prophets, and those who keep the words in this book. Worship God!”
B066C022V010	66	22	10	Then he said to me, “Don't seal up the words of the prophecy in this book, because the time is near.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	Let the one who does what is evil continue to do evil, and let the filthy person continue to be filthy, and the righteous person continue to do what is right, and the holy person continue to be holy.”
B066C022V012	66	22	12	
        
B066C022V013	66	22	13	
        
B066C022V014	66	22	14	How blessed are those who wash their robes so that they may have the right to the tree of life and may go through the gates into the city!
B066C022V015	66	22	15	Outside are dogs, sorcerers, immoral people, murderers, idolaters, and everyone who loves and practices falsehood.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	
        
B066C022V017	66	22	17	The Spirit and the bride say, “Come!” Let everyone who hears this say, “Come!” Let everyone who is thirsty come! Let anyone who wants the water of life take it as a gift!
B066C022V018	66	22	18	I warn everyone who hears the words of the prophecy in this book: If anyone adds anything to them, God will strike him with the plagues that are written in this book.
B066C022V019	66	22	19	If anyone takes away any words from the book of this prophecy, God will take away his portion of the tree of life and the holy city that are described in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	The one who is testifying to these things says,
B066C022V021	66	22	21	May the grace of the Lord Jesus be with all the saints. Amen.
